(23, 'Master Your Own SERP Result with Core Web Vitals in 2021', 'Google Updates', 'core-web-vitals-in-2021-1024x536.png', NULL, '<!-- wp:heading -->\r\n<h2><strong>Core Web Vitals in 2021</strong></h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>In the previous article of <a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/core-web-vitals\">What is google core Web vitals</a>, we did talk about the various core web vitals and how they are measured. This article would try to help you better understand how you can master your Google page ranking by keeping in mind the vitals. In addition, this would help you understand what you would need to keep in mind when trying to put the vitals in place.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\\\"level\\\":3} -->\r\n\r\n<h3>Largest Contentful Paint (LCP) In <strong>Core Web Vitals</strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Let us now try to get the first Google Vital metric in place, which is the Largest Contentful Paint (LCP). A quick recap, this metric measures the time lag as when a link is clicked and the page open. So, here are a few key points that you should keep in mind which would help you have a better LCP score.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\\\"level\\\":4} -->\r\n\r\n<h4>1. Remove third Party Scripts.</h4>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>This is something that can make your website slow. One of the surveys shows that with every third-party script you have on your page, your page loading time would increase by around 34 milliseconds. So, get rid of the third-party scripts at the earliest that you can.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\\\"level\\\":4} -->\r\n\r\n<h4>2. Go for a Better Web Host.</h4>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>If you think that your website should not be that slow, but it is, then it is more than just possible that it is because of the host that you are using. The reason your website is slowing down may be because of a slow host. There are just way too many options when it comes to choosing a host. So, get the one that suits all your needs.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\\\"level\\\":4} -->\r\n\r\n<h4>3. Lazy loading helps.</h4>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Set up lazy loading on your website. This means that the pictures on your website that would come upon scrolling would not load all at once. So, the loading would occur as and when you scroll the page. This would help you meet your target LCP scores much faster and with few issues. This is an excellent technique as, in many cases, the heavy images cause the delay.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\\\"level\\\":4} -->\r\n\r\n<h4>4. Reduce CSS.</h4>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Well, you might be in love with CSS, but that is not something that would help you have a better LCP time. All you would have to do is make sure that you reduce the CSS in your site. Remember, the CSS delays the loading speed significantly. Get rid of them, and you would have a faster website.<br />\r\nThese would help you have a better LCP score.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph {\\\"textColor\\\":\\\"vivid-red\\\"} -->\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:list --><!-- wp:heading {\\\"level\\\":3} -->\r\n\r\n<h3>First Input Delay (FID)</h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>The next matric checks how early the users can interact with your website when they are on your site&mdash;the First Input Delay (FID) metric. Let us try to understand what you would need to keep in mind for this particular metric.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\\\"level\\\":4} -->\r\n\r\n<h4>1. Reduce the JavaScript:</h4>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Well, this might seem like a challenge, but then you can hardly help. However, this is a crucial point. Reduce the JavaScript that you are having on the website and see you win over this particular metric. You might also differ your JavaScript; that would help as well.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\\\"level\\\":4} -->\r\n\r\n<h4>2. Third Party scripts should be removed:</h4>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>For FID, third-party scripts removal would be magical. This would help you have the best effects in the shortest period. So, if you have a third-party script that you can do without, get rid of them at the earliest that you can.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\\\"level\\\":4} -->\r\n\r\n<h4>3. Browser Cache:</h4>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Browser caches help load the pages faster. This means that your website would load faster on the client-server. Your FID would be significantly improved with this.<br />\r\nWell, we hope that you are getting a hack of how exactly you can get the most out of your website by tweaking the changes above.<br />\r\nHowever, tweaking the changes is not an easy task, and an experienced team with a holistic knowledge of the technology and the processes would help you immensely. If you are looking for one such company, then for sure, <a href=\"\\\">iDotcommers</a> is one you should lay your eyes on. They are ideally well suited to help you with your needs, and the great reviews that we have got from various people showcase their professionalism and dedication.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\\\"level\\\":3} -->\r\n\r\n<h3>Cumulative Layout Shift (CLS)</h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>We would help you out with the final metric, which is the Cumulative Layout Shift (CLS) which helps depicts the visual stability of the website when it loads. So, let us see what you can do to have the best ratings in this metric!</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\\\"level\\\":4} -->\r\n\r\n<h4>1. Use size attributes:</h4>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>This would help your browser gauge precisely how much space you would need to showcase your media. This would mean that the elements would not keep moving while the page loads.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\\\"level\\\":4} -->\r\n\r\n<h4>2. Reserve spaces for ad elements:</h4>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>If you are having a login or sign-up page, it would be advised that you should not get many advertisements there. It would eat on your credibility. However, having said that, if you still wish to put in your ads, then confine them within a given space so that they do not float about, disturbing your matric.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\\\"level\\\":4} -->\r\n\r\n<h4>3. New UI elements should be added below the fold.</h4>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>New UI elements should be added below the fold. This means that you can have the elements added below the fold. This would help the users to not click on other places, and they would get the expected results at the desired position.<br />\r\nThese three things would help you immensely to get a better marking in the CLS. Try them out, and you would see the difference almost instantly.<br />\r\nWell, these are a few tips that would help you have the best results for yourself. I would agree if someone claims them to be a bit technical; well, if you find it outside your range, you can get in touch with <a href=\"\\\">iDotcommers.</a> All in all, these pointers are the key factors that would help you have the best ranking on Google.<br />\r\nWith that, we would like to conclude the article, do let us know if we were able to help you and if you have any more suggestions. Please feel free to let us know if we could help you in any way!</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Core Web Vitals in 2021 | how exactly you can master your Google page ranking by keeping in mind the vitals.', 'core-web-vitals-in-2021', 'Core Web Vitals,Google Core Web Vitals,Core Web Vitals 2021', 'Jewel', '2021-07-24 08:48:51', '2021-08-07 14:10:18'),
(24, 'Ways To Increase Your Google Search Ranking | SEO Tips', 'SEO', 'increase-your-google-search-ranking-1024x536.png', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>Increase Your Google Search Ranking</strong>. When you have a website, the sole thing that you would be worried about is getting the website ranking. Among the millions of websites that we have online, it is essential to make your way on the first page. This would help you to have the highest views. So, there are a few crucial points that you should keep in mind to make sure that the website ranks well.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>This article will try to understand the checkboxes you would need to tick to get your website ranked higher than all your competitors in your niche. So, let us check the pointers.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Content Tips For Google Search Ranking :&nbsp;</strong></h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Well, content is king. Remember, at the end of the day, the only reason someone is on your website is to get some relevant information about something related to your genre. If your website can well serve the cause for your viewers, then you would be able to win over a loyal subscriber. So, remember that your content matters the most.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Apart from your viewers, the search engines also take note of each word published on your website. A well-researched, SEO optimized content is something that the search engine would love showcasing to the viewers.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Thus, the first thing you need to keep an eye on to improve your rankings is the content you publish on your website.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Google Core Web Vitals:&nbsp;</strong></h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Now, your vitals play a major role in deciding the Google Search rankings of your website.<a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/google-core-web-vitals-ratings/\"> Keep a very close eye on your web vitals. </a>Most of the web vitals are related to the website loading speed and the functionality of the website.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>All these help improve the user experience for the viewers, and also, Google keeps a real sharp eye on the metrics. Various tools can help you understand your vital scores. You can also keep a few pointers in mind that would help you understand the metrics better. These together would let you make the websites as per the requirements.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Backlinks:&nbsp;</strong></h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Google uses an algorithm to check the amount of trust that people have in your website. So, when it comes to this metric, your <a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/purpose-of-backlinks/\" target=\"_blank\">backlinks play a real important role.</a> The pages that have the largest number of backlinks are the ones that feature at the top of the search results.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>The simple reason behind this is that when Google algorithm crawls across the world wide web, it checks every website and whenever there is one that backlinks your website, your website\\&#39;s reputation goes up. Over a longer period, the website with the best reputation features at the top of the search results.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph {\\\"textColor\\\":\\\"vivid-red\\\"} -->\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:list --><!-- wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>No Broken Links:</strong></h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>If you put in any link on your website or put up the broken links on your website in the past. Make sure that you keep getting back to them and check them if they are still active. Time and again, the website owners generally tend to forget to keep an eye on the backlinks.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>This costs them heavily in the longer run. The broken links on your website are a complete no-no for your website ranking. Apart from Google, which takes note of the broken link, the user experience takes a hit when you have broken links on your page. Thus, keep a close eye on your links and update them as and when necessary.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Optimize For Voice Search:</strong></h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>The new big thing that the blogging industry is about to go through is the voice search feature. The searches in recent years are shifting to voice searches. This means that you would get your searches by vocal inputs.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>This is necessary to understand here that voice search optimization is unique. Here you would have to understand that the way we search something over voice is not the same as how we searched it over text. That is exactly what makes all the difference.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Use Headings and Alt tags:&nbsp;</strong></h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>The SEO techniques you would have to go forward with for your website would largely depend on the alt tags and the headings you would use. The H2 and H3 tags that you have plays a real important role in your Google Search ranking.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>So, make sure that you include your keywords in the headings. The alt tags, on the other hand, would come from the images. They provide you with the perfect way to help you promote and use your keyword. Thus, make sure that your alt tags for the images are always taken care of.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>These are just some of the ways you can have a website with the best rankings. Yet, it must be understood here that SEO is a long-time game. At times, the websites with perfectly everything that one would need for a good SEO score would take months to rank.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>So, if you are not sure about the SEO skills and the others that would help you have the website featured in the best place possible, you would have to get in touch with some of the experienced individuals in the industry. One of the relevant and dependable names in this particular sector is <a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/\">iDotcommers.</a> If you want to get in touch with them, they will take care of your needs. Well, you might have to spend a little, but the time and effort that you would save yourself from would make this the perfect decision!</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>With that, we would like to conclude this article. We hope that now you have a fundamental idea about how exactly you can have your website perform at its best. If you still have any questions that you think would help you in your conquest, then you can write to us. Also, do let us know if there is anything that you would want us to add in the article. We hope that you would have got something out of this, and it would help you have a better website with a better ranking for yourself.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'When you have a website, then you would be solely worried about improving google search ranking of your website', 'increase-your-google-search-ranking', 'Google Search Ranking,SEO Tips,Increase Google Search Ranking', 'Jewel', '2021-07-24 08:48:51', '2021-08-25 13:07:52'),
(25, 'How To Get The Best Google Core Web Vitals Ratings', 'Google Updates', 'get-the-best-google-core-web-vitals-ratings-1024x536.png', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>Core Web Vitals Ratings</strong> Being on top of the search results is something that perfectly every website or blog owner always wishes for. However, since everyone wishes for the top, the fight for the apex is tough. There are a few things that you would have to keep in mind which would help you stay ahead and beat your competitors with ease. So, in this article, we would be talking about the various pointers that you would have to keep in mind when you work on your website or your blog as a whole. Let\\&#39;s delve into the pointers!</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<h2>1. Largest Contentful Paint (LCP) for <strong>Core Web Vitals Ratings</strong></h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>By now, you already know what this means, right. So, we would not waste your time with the description again! But then, let\\&#39;s try to understand how exactly you can have the best LCP scores. <strong>Try to make sure that your website loads at the fastest rate possible.</strong> You can do this by simply making sure that the pages are not too heavy. This also means that you should take note of the codes that you use and the images and videos that you share on the page. Overall, this has to be mandated that your page loads within 2.5 seconds cause that is all that it takes for a user to leave your website and walk on to another one. So, yeah, 2.5 seconds, light codes, and light content are all you would need in this!</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<h2>2. First Input Delay(FID) for <strong>Core Web Vitals Ratings</strong></h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>When it comes to FID, it\\&#39;s simple! Your website needs to be really responsive from the word go. Well, you might not have much of an issue if you are on a blog or website page unless your FID is painfully low. However, the real problem begins when you are on a log-in or register page. <strong>Make sure that these pages are kept the lightest among all</strong>. Do not include anything but just the most important and required stuff, possibly, the placeholders and the button. Yes, keep it that simple! Trust me; you have the blog or the website to put your skills to the test. This is just not the right place!</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<h2>3. Cumulative Layout Shift (CLS) for <strong>Core Web Vitals Ratings</strong></h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>When you get a website or blog ready, the layout must remain constant. This can mainly be because of the dimensionless images, ads, frames without dimensions, and much more. While there are tons of stuff that can be the case, we would suggest that you should keep everything on your page with a proper dimension, even the advertisements, and the other images. This would help you have a higher CLS score.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<h2>4. SSL Certificates:</h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>SSL stands for secure sockets layer. This means that Well, this is an absolute necessity that we have for your website. <strong>This helps the users have the most secure and safe browsing experience</strong> that we can have. SSL these days are cheap, and in some cases, they are even offered for free with your domain or hosting plan. This means that you would have an added advantage for your website without even paying for it. SSL is a need that you should never ignore if you want to be at the helm of your genre.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph {\\\"textColor\\\":\\\"vivid-red\\\"} -->\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:list --><!-- wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<h2>5. No intrusive interstitials:</h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Well, that is something that might make you feel a bit insecure about your knowledge. But trust me, it\\&#39;s not so, in fact, it is something that you are really very well aware of. This simply means that you do not put useless or unnecessary elements on your website. This would also help you with the LCP and also help you have a fast load time. So, reduce the number of irrelevant elements that you have in your website or blog.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Well, these are five of the things that would help make sure that you stay on top of your search results! But then, are you a bit unsure about any of them? Well, do not worry, it is not the first time I have heard one get a bit dizzy with those requirements. So, the best thing that we can do here is to make sure that you can hire someone who can help you with these!</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>And the best option that you have is that of an enterprise or an agency. The most hardworking and technically sound agency would help you have a great website that you would be able to showcase right at the top of the search results! If you are looking for one such agency, then definitely <a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/\">iDotcommers</a> can be one of them. They are really skilled at what they do, and I assure you, they are a master!</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\\\"level\\\":3} -->\r\n\r\n<h3>FAQ</h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:yoast/faq-block {\\\"questions\\\":[{\\\"id\\\":\\\"faq-question-1623651049431\\\",\\\"question\\\":[\\\"1. How do I pass the core Web Vitals?\\\"],\\\"answer\\\":[\\\"Simple, work hard to keep the FID, CLS, and LCP perfectly straight. If you are not sure if you have a done a good job in any of them, you definitely can check out your rankings on some of the available online tools. You would also get a few recommendations on how exactly you can mend the ways.\\\",{\\\"type\\\":\\\"br\\\",\\\"props\\\":{\\\"children\\\":[]}}],\\\"jsonQuestion\\\":\\\"1. How do I pass the core Web Vitals?\\\",\\\"jsonAnswer\\\":\\\"Simple, work hard to keep the FID, CLS, and LCP perfectly straight. If you are not sure if you have a done a good job in any of them, you definitely can check out your rankings on some of the available online tools. You would also get a few recommendations on how exactly you can mend the ways.\\\\u003cbr/\\\\u003e\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"faq-question-1623651612355\\\",\\\"question\\\":[\\\"2. What are the most important Web Vitals?\\\"],\\\"answer\\\":[\\\"The most crucial web vitals are Largest Contentful Paint(LCP), Cumulative Layout Shift (CLS), and First Input Delay(FID). These vitals are almost always referred to it by search engines. These would help you have the proper ranking and thus help you in having better visibility.\\\",{\\\"type\\\":\\\"br\\\",\\\"props\\\":{\\\"children\\\":[]}}],\\\"jsonQuestion\\\":\\\"2. What are the most important Web Vitals?\\\",\\\"jsonAnswer\\\":\\\"The most crucial web vitals are Largest Contentful Paint(LCP), Cumulative Layout Shift (CLS), and First Input Delay(FID). These vitals are almost always referred to it by search engines. These would help you have the proper ranking and thus help you in having better visibility.\\\\u003cbr/\\\\u003e\\\"}]} -->\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div><strong>1. How do I pass the core Web Vitals?</strong>\r\n\r\n<p>Simple, work hard to keep the FID, CLS, and LCP perfectly straight. If you are not sure if you have a done a good job in any of them, you definitely can check out your rankings on some of the available online tools. You would also get a few recommendations on how exactly you can mend the ways.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>2. What are the most important Web Vitals?</strong>\r\n\r\n<p>The most crucial web vitals are Largest Contentful Paint(LCP), Cumulative Layout Shift (CLS), and First Input Delay(FID). These vitals are almost always referred to it by search engines. These would help you have the proper ranking and thus help you in having better visibility.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<!-- /wp:yoast/faq-block --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>In this article, we tried to help you perfectly with everything you would have to keep in mind when looking forward to having your website ranked right on top. We have also listed the essential points, and at the same time, we have tried to answer the most relevant questions that are asked by the audience at large. This helps us provide you the most important pointers that you might be needing.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Please let us know if there is anything that we missed including. Also, please let us know if there is anything else you want to know about them, and we would try to make sure that you have the perfect solution for all your needs.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'In this article, we will cover how you can get the best google core web vitals ratings, by keeping various pointers in your mind.', 'google-core-web-vitals-ratings', 'Core Web Vitals,Google Core Web Vitals,Core Web Vitals Ratings', 'Jewel', '2021-07-24 08:48:51', '2021-08-04 12:27:37'),
(26, 'What Is SEO And How It Has Changed Over The Years', 'SEO', 'how-seo-changed-over-the-years-1024x536.png', NULL, '<!-- wp:heading -->\r\n<h2>What Is SEO</h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>SEO is a buzzword that anyone having a website must have come across at some point in life or the other. The important thing is understanding<strong> what is SEO </strong>and how exactly you can gain from it. So, this article would make sure that you have ideally no doubt about SEO whatsoever and help you with some of the changes that it has gone through in the past. So, let us get started.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>To start with, <strong>SEO stands for Search Engine Optimization.</strong> This can well be regarded as the process by which the website owners and the bloggers try to stay at the top of their game by being visible to the most significant number of people possible. And when we say the most significant number of people, it simply means the best ranking! So, there are a few essential pointers like the content, the keywords, and a few others that one would have to keep in mind to be at the top of their SEO game.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Well, we can discuss at length and breadth the needs to master your SEO scores. However, here, we would try to discuss how the SEO techniques have changed over the years, and right now, what are some of those things that you might need to keep in mind. So, let us now check the timeline of this particular technique and how it has evolved.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\\\"level\\\":3} -->\r\n\r\n<h3>1. Understanding \\&quot;Good Content\\&quot;:&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Over the years, Google has understood <a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/content-writing/\">what exactly is good content</a> and has tweaked what is called \\&quot;Good content\\&quot; almost a decade back. What was considered by Google as good content was the one better in quantity. However, the quality of the content beats the quantity. Thus, the length of the content is not what matters the most.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\\\"level\\\":3} -->\r\n\r\n<h3>2. No More Link Buddies:&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Almost a decade back, most bloggers and other website owners would get along and start posting the other person\\&#39;s link on their website. This means that the genre or the topic of the websites were not important. Just imagine someone sharing the best pet breakfast idea links on a pregnancy website! Completely irrelevant, right? In its initial days, Google did not understand that, and they kept promoting the links. However, these days Google pretty much understands what played on with them and sometimes banning the websites.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\\\"level\\\":3} -->\r\n\r\n<h3>3. Mobile Priority:&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Ten years back, how many people do you remember carrying a mobile? Well, now how many mobiles do you possess? Some of my friends have even more than one device. This simply shows the amount of dependency that people have on mobile phones. This has also led to a different style of SEO, and that is mobile SEO.<br />\r\nPeople have now started realizing that mobile searches are much more in number than website searches. Also, the websites and content, along with the pictures and all, are made keeping the mobile users in mind. Thus, this is a huge shift from the initial computer users to the recent year\\&#39;s mobile users.<br />\r\nMake sure that you have a lighter website that is easy to load. This would also help in the web core vitals and thus help you in the rankings.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\\\"level\\\":3} -->\r\n\r\n<h3>4. Keywords:&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Rather than understanding the meaning, the initial days of the SEO were to understand the use of the keyword term, the exact fit. This means that the results shown to the users were many times irrelevant. However, Google changed this with one of the most popular updates.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Now, you would have to make sure that the keyword is fairly used and used correctly. Thus, make sure that you do not stuff your website with keywords. Make sure that you use keywords only when you need to, and also do not overdo them. Try and understand that they are essential and appreciated but not out of proportion.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph {\\\"textColor\\\":\\\"vivid-red\\\"} --><!-- /wp:list --><!-- wp:heading {\\\"level\\\":3} -->\r\n\r\n<h3>5. Faster and better updates:&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Well, this is something that has not exactly changed SEO but has changed how we see it. Over the years, it seems that SEO techniques have started changing faster. So, to make sure that you stay at the top of your business, you need to make sure that you keep an eye on everything you need to have. Also, the changing SEO techniques every day helps make sure that people make an honest effort to put in well-researched articles. This completely omits just stuffing in on a format that works. The only thing that works in SEO is good content and excellent research!</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\\\"level\\\":3} -->\r\n\r\n<h3>6. Google Web Vitals:</h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>When you talk about the ranking of a particular website, there is precisely no way that you can do away with the <a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/core-web-vitals/\">web vitals.</a> These are the parameters that help make sure that your website is ranked higher than others. The three parameters considered as the web vitals are loading time, interactivity and visual page stability.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>These indicators mainly deal with your website presence and also helps you gauge how good your website performs. These matrices are on the harder side to master, and thus, almost always, people prefer getting in touch with professionals to get this sorted. Thus, if you are not sure about what exactly you want to do with your website or handle it yourself for the Google Web Vitals, our advice would be to hire an expert.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/\">iDotcommers is one of the forerunners when it comes to experience. </a>They have seen many of the changes stated above, and they have adapted themselves perfectly well to deliver the best to their clients. Thus, if you need someone who would always assist you, iDotcommers is the best option for you.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\\\"level\\\":4} -->\r\n\r\n<h4>Why are core web vitals essential for SEO?</h4>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Well, the core web vitals helps the pages to be way more responsive. As a result of the same, the audience\\&#39;s attention and presence in any website increase manifolds. It is seen that more than half the number of visitors in any particular website is lost if the core web vitals are not upto the mark.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>These were some of the most popular SEO changes that have happened over the last ten years. However, there are so many more that have changed SEO forever, but they are omitted here. We hope that you can now understand that keeping up with SEO is not an easy task as it is almost constantly changing itself.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>I hope that I have been able to help you with the basic knowledge of SEO and how it has changed. Understanding the origin of the technique and how the technique has walked on all these years would help you understand how much we have walked as a civilization. You would also get a better understanding of all the needs that you might have.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>So, if this article would help you with something new, please feel free to write to us. Also, do let us know if there is something that you would want us to include in the article. Also, if you feel that there are some significant updates that we have missed in the article, then please feel free to let us know about them too!</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\\\"level\\\":5} -->\r\n\r\n<h5>&nbsp;</h5>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'SEO is a buzzword that anyone having a website must know. if you don\'t then today we will see what is seo and it has changed over the years.', 'what-is-seo', 'SEO,SEO Strategy,What Is SEO', 'Jewel', '2021-07-24 08:48:51', '2021-08-04 12:31:35'),
(27, '8 Ways To Rank Higher On Google Search Results', 'Ranking Factors', 'ways-to-rank-higher-on-google-1-1024x536.png', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p>Starting off with your journey to<strong> Rank Higher On Google Search Results</strong> is something that every website or blog owner has done over the years. However, while it\\&#39;s challenging to be among the top searches, it is even more challenging to hold to your position.&nbsp;So, in this article, we would try to understand how exactly one can <strong>Rank Higher On Google Search Engine</strong> exactly every time and maintain the same for yourselves. Here are a few pointers that you should keep in mind.&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<h2>1. Understand the keywords to rank higher on google search results:&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Try to understand the keywords you are ranking for and then analyze the keywords. Were you trying to rank for these keywords, or are you planning to rank for anything else? In that case, try to understand what are the keywords that you should work on. The analysis would help you understand what keywords you should pay more emphasis on. Also, you might have to twist your topics and write-ups as per the requirement to make sure that the readers are happy with the content you produce.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<h2>2. Keep a close eye on the google web vitals:&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>This is important. As you would keep posting your articles, it is quite possible that you might end up ranking a bit lower on the <a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/google-core-web-vitals-ratings/\">Google Web Vital Ratings.</a> So, the possible reasons behind this could be the heavy images you would put up from time to time or might even be the advertisements you start receiving and putting in on the website. The essential parameters of the <strong>Web Vitals may be affected.</strong> To ensure that they are always at best, you should always keep checking the scores and rankings and tweak your website as per the needs. This is a vital step to have the best ranking and retain it for the longest time.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<h2>3. Produce quality content to rank higher on google search results :&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Well, you may have <a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/content-writing/\">produced quality content</a> right from the very first day that you started the website. It is probably the only reason why you are at the top of the search results. So, make sure that you are at your best when you are working on the content. Also, with time, try to understand and analyze the type of content that your readers love and start writing accordingly. This would also make sure that you have the largest pool of like-minded people on your website.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph {\\\"textColor\\\":\\\"vivid-red\\\"} --><!-- /wp:list --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Here are some of the most relevant questions that you might have for us related to your ranking, and we are here to help you out with the same.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\\\"level\\\":3} -->\r\n\r\n<h3>Does Backlinking help in better ranking?</h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/purpose-of-backlinks/\" target=\"_blank\">Backlinking does help!</a> However, outbound links for your website is something that you cannot control. But then you can control the inbound links right. You would have to create the topics that can be inter-twined and then link them with each other. This would help you have a better outreach and, thus, in turn, help you grow! Also, visitors would then read other content that excites them.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\\\"level\\\":3} -->\r\n\r\n<h3>Why do i have to make my website mobile-friendly to rank higher on google?</h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>More than half of the searches these days are on mobile devices. Thus, you would have to <strong>make sure that your website is mobile-friendly.</strong> This also has a significant impact on your website ranking. <strong>Mobile-friendly websites are way easier to rank on the search engine than the ones that are not.</strong> At the same time, you would have to make sure that you tweak the website design as per the need. Overall, these would help you have the best effect on your SEO.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\\\"level\\\":3} -->\r\n\r\n<h3>What are the most basic things that one has to keep in mind for better ranking in Google?</h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p><strong>SSL is something that you must have.</strong> If you do not, then this is the first thing that you should do for your website, and <strong>that would help you have the best ranking and allow you to acquire more readers for your website. </strong>You can get the SSL certificates at low rates, and you can well have yourself a well-secured website. A more secure website would also mean fewer attacks and malware.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Title Tags and Meta text would be the other thing that you should keep in mind.</strong> Remember that the title you put and the meta-text are the only things that users would read before they jump into your website. So, this is your first and last opportunity to help users decide if they want to be on your page or do not want to. This would also be the case in case your website is shared on any social media. So, make sure that you have an enticing and exciting description and title that would have everyone\\&#39;s attention.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\\\"level\\\":3} -->\r\n\r\n<h3>Does the segregation and organization of the articles help in SEO?</h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Organizing your website is not exactly something that would help you in SEO, but something that would help your readers move across and gauge your website faster. <strong>You should segregate and organize your websit</strong>e. The categories and the subcategories, along with the tags, should be well plotted out. So, that people having an interest in one particular sub-nice in your niche would have the best options readily available.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Well, these things might have taken a toll on you. Do you think that these would be just a bit too much to handle? If that is the case, then all I want is to ensure that you have these with ease. My suggestion would be to get someone or rather hire an agency that would help you with these. If I am asked to recommend, then the best option for you would be <a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/\">iDotcommers. </a>They have their own unique and hugely successful ways of helping a website get across any adversity, and they have succeeded in perfectly everything. So, if you need help, they are the best option.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>With that, we hope that we could help you have your website on <strong>Rank Higher On Google</strong> Search Results. They are some of the essential pointers that one would always have to keep in mind for being the best in business. We hope that you would implement them and let us know about the results that you have.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Let us know if you feel that something else should have made its way into the list. Also, do let us know what worked for you in the past.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Starting off with your journey to rank higher on google search results is something that every website or blog owner has done over the years.', 'rank-higher-on-google', 'Rank Higher On Google,Google Ranking,Google Ranking Factors', 'Jewel', '2021-07-24 08:48:51', '2021-08-25 13:04:49');
INSERT INTO `blog` (`id`, `blog_title`, `blog_category`, `image1`, `image2`, `description`, `description1`, `blog_url`, `tags`, `author_name`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(28, 'What Is The Google Algorithm | How Does The Google Algorithm Work', 'Google Algorithm', 'what-is-the-google-algorithm-1024x576.png', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>What Is The Google Algorithm</strong> 2,000,000,000,000. That, my dear readers, is the number of searches that Google has to cater every year. This translates to somewhere about <strong>40,000 searches every second.</strong> When the search volume is that huge, definitely the algorithm that works behind it would be quite complex, and definitely complex it is. It takes bloggers and website owners months and years to understand how exactly the system works. This exact way how the system works is called the algorithm, in the simplest term.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>However, once the algorithm was cracked, it became really easy for owners to list their website or blog. This meant that they were at the top of the search result even when their website was not the most informative or the most engaging. So, to help make sure that the end-users have the best experience, Google keeps upgrading this algorithm from time to time.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>So, it becomes really important for you to understand this if you own a website or a blog. <strong>So, in this article, we would be talking about the Google algorithm.</strong> We will try and understand exactly everything that we can about algorithms and how they affect us.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>How does the Google algorithm work?</strong></h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Well, there are five important factors in which the algorithm works. These are just some of the most basic features. So, here are they:</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\\\"level\\\":3} -->\r\n\r\n<h3>1. Understanding the query:</h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>When a user puts in a query, the algorithm tries to make sure that it understands the query. The same word can have various meanings in various queries. This makes it important for the algorithm to be smart enough to understand what the visitors are looking forward to. Thus, the <strong>algorithm tries to understand what the query actually intends</strong> to and thus shows the results.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\\\"level\\\":3} -->\r\n\r\n<h3>2. Webpage Relevance:</h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>This becomes important for bloggers. This is just where you should be careful. Try to make sure that <strong>the type of content that you post on your page is of the same genre.</strong> This would help your website be more relevant than the others in the trade. This would help make you stand out and <a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/rank-higher-on-google/\">rank faster than others.</a> Also, make sure that the blogs or posts have the right keywords in the headings and the title.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\\\"level\\\":3} -->\r\n\r\n<h3>3. Content is King:</h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Having the keywords in place alone would not help. This is something that you would have to understand. Having the keywords would only help you tick off one important factor of the list. But well, you need to understand that if a query is \\&quot;dehydration\\&quot;, it means that the user is looking forward to something about the term. It might be the cures, causes or treatments, or something else. But then, they are not looking for a page that had the word written a thousand times with exactly no information. Thus, the content should be rich in information.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\\\"level\\\":3} -->\r\n\r\n<h3>4. Website Usability:</h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Make sure that the website is user-friendly. </strong>A user-friendly website is something that always helps in ranking. Also, over a larger period of time, the page\\&#39;s overall ranking for one that has really refreshing usability gets better. A few tips here would be to make sure that the website is as light as it can be. This would make sure that the website would show up even when the internet connection is not that great. Also, make sure that the functionalities in the website are working as per expectations.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\\\"level\\\":3} -->\r\n\r\n<h3>5. Context and Setting:</h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Google uses various information of the user who searches the query. These include the likes of the location, previous search history, and much more. With all these perfectly placed, it becomes easier for Google to understand what the searches might usually be for. And thus, overall, gives a better understanding of the query and what the user might be looking forward to. This is just one of the many reasons why Google rankings differ from one geographical location to another.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>These are the 5 main criteria defined by Google on which it frames its algorithm. Now that you have a better understanding of the algorithm, you also do understand the basic rule. It is only to make sure that the visitors have the best experience while in Google. They have the best search results that are most meaningful to them.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>If you want to study all the factors that would affect the search result, which would need you to understand the algorithm even better. There are as many as 200 ranking factors outlined by Google. Well, yes, 200! So, it\\&#39;s just not possible to keep 200 pointers in mind for a 500-word blog post. Thus, it\\&#39;s most important that you remember to keep the above 5 factors in shape. This would help make sure that you have most of the other 200 pointers met.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Why does Google keep changing the algorithm?</strong></h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>The question that should be most obvious right now is why does Google make so many changes to their algorithm? Well, the reasons are simple. The first one, because Google constantly tries to upgrade itself as all good companies should, to serve their customers in the best way possible. Secondly, Google tries to outdo the wrongdoers. This means that Google tries to make sure that nobody gets accustomed to a particular algorithm and thus makes sure that only the genuine sites that care about their visitors are at the top of the search result.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>This means that the changes in the algorithm do not only help keep away the wrongdoers but also helps keep the visitors satisfied, which in a way helps increase the number of users for the company.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>What would you need To Keep In Mind Being A Website Owner?</strong></h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Now that you know almost everything you need to know about the Google search engine algorithm, the very last and most important thing you need to know about this is what you should keep in mind as a website or blog owner. So, here are some of the things that you should keep in mind which would help make sure that you stay relevant irrespective of whatever update comes up in the algorithm of the search engine.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>To start with, make sure that your website is light. There is just no way that Google would value you more for having a heavy website instead of a light one. You should try to achieve this with the simplest of codes and the lightest of images.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Next up, keep a regular check on all the functionalities of your website. Do also check if they are working fine in every screen size and they are as per expectation. This is something that would not only help you in ranking but would also help you in retaining your visitors for longer periods of time on your website or blog.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>The most important pointers that you should keep in mind is making sure that you have the most informative and detailed content available on your blog. This simply would help you be at the top no matter what!</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>The very last pointer that we would like to emphasize does not try to outsmart Google. Well, you can! So, just do not try it. Cause in an attempt to do so, you will definitely hurt yourself in the longer run.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\\\"level\\\":4} -->\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>Conclusion</strong></h4>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>We hope that now you have a real good idea about what exactly an algorithm is, how it affects you, why it\\&#39;s needed, and last but not least, what would help an owner be resistant to these changes. Overall, this is something that you should know before you go on to master the search engine results. We hope that we could help you with your queries and questions that you might have had about the search engine algorithm. Please feel free to get in touch with us if you need our assistance with anything else.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Understanding the Google Algorithm is a tough job. Thus, if you do not have much knowledge in the same, you can definitely refer to<a href=\"https://idotcommers.com\"> iDotcommers.</a> They are professional, innovative, and have the perfect solution to all your needs.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'What is the google algorithm, how does the algorithm work, and why does google keep changing the algorithm.', 'what-is-the-google-algorithm', 'Algorithm,Google Algorithm,Google Algorithm 2021, Google Update', 'Jewel', '2021-07-24 08:48:51', '2021-08-04 12:34:41'),
(29, 'Negative Impact On Any Website Due To Google Algorithm Update', 'Google Algorithm', 'negative-impact-of-google-algorithm-update-1024x576.jpg', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>Google Algorithm Update</strong> In this article, we would try to understand some practices that almost always get penalized by Google in every update. This would mean that you would understand all the things that you should keep yourself away from if you want to make sure that your website is at the top of the list. So, let us get started and try to be as detailed as we possibly can.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<h2>1. Keyword stuffed content:&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Keywords are essential; they help the search engine find you out. However, it doesn\\&#39;t mean that you would stuff your articles with keywords. All that you would need to do here is to make sure that the content is informative enough. If you have a website that is at the top of the search results only due to keyword stuffing, then it is high time that you get them corrected and make it informative.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Keyword stuffing can only get you to the top momentarily, but it is only about time that you would again lose your spot. So, it would be much better to take the more hard-earned way to provide the most relevant information on your portal, which would help you have a concrete base to build on.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<h2>2. Breaking the Code:&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Many times, some bloggers and website owners crack the Google algorithm. That is something appreciable. But then, if you have understood the algorithm, try to build on a website that would sustain the algorithm by taking on the pointers in the most positive way possible.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>If you go on to challenge the algorithm and tweak it in such a way that you reach the top using black hat techniques, then rest assured that in the very next algorithm, you would lose the spot that you are in right now. So, make sure that you do not challenge Google, it is not easy to win, and more often than not, you would end up on the losing side, and you would lose a lot.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<h2>3. Random Backlinks:&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Backlinks are vital. These help you grow your business and help you have a better ranking on Google. However, this does not mean that you would go on to backlink yourself anywhere and everywhere that you can. Make sure that the backlinks come from the most reasonable and trustworthy sites. Also, they should be worth it.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>By that we mean, that the backlinks should not be random. Make sure that you are not promoting women\\&#39;s apparel in a men\\&#39;s grooming portal. This would only ruin your chances to ever reach the top. It is most likely that you would end up being at one of the worst rankings possible. If you are doing great practicing this method, wait for Google to update its algorithm, and your website would take a hit on the ranking font.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<h2>4. Do Not Duplicate:&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>This DND is important to remember for the website and blog owners. Make sure that you do not duplicate. What exactly do we mean by that? Well, simple, do not write the same thing again and again. This can be in the same post or over several posts.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>This is simply one of those that you should keep in mind. The duplicate posts are a big turn-off for the viewers. There is just no way that Google would support something that the viewers don\\&#39;t like. So, you should make sure that any content on your website is not duplicated.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<h2>5. Ill-Functional Website:&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>If a website or part of the website is not functional, there is just no way that you can top the charts. Even if you do, it is most probable that your competitors with the <a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/website-designing/\">most effective websites</a> are doing that with half the effort. Make sure that there are no broken links on your website. Ensure that each and every functionality on the website is perfectly well maintained and is working as per the expectation. Ill-functional websites are a big no-no for search engines.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nNow that you are aware of some of the reasons that can substantially negatively impact the ranking, you should also understand that an algorithm update is not the only way to get your website removed from the rankings. Google is one of those search engines which inflicts manual penalty.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>This means that if any of the search algorithms in Google trigger a red flag, it is most probable that a real person would then be assigned to check if your website had something that needs to take any action against. There are 6 stated pointers under which Google can penalize you. We would talk about each one of them in details in some other article.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>For now, you need to understand that just in case if you fall in any of these six pointers that Google has listed, your website would then be penalized. These penalties last for a few weeks, and you are expected to amend your mistakes, after which Google would again check on your website. You might just lose your ranking even for the articles that were perfect. So, make sure that you stay away from any of these practices.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nSo, these are some of the most important things that you should stay away from while working on your website. Let us now help clear some of the doubts that most frequently come through to us and try to answer them.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\\\"level\\\":3} -->\r\n\r\n<h3>1. Why does Google update their search algorithm?&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Google upgrades their search algorithm to make sure that nobody takes undue advantage of the search engine. This means that having one algorithm would also mean that many of the users would better understand some and then many would exploit. However, having a constant metamorphosis would not let one settle. That would also mean that they would always be on their toes to provide the best content every time.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\\\"level\\\":3} -->\r\n\r\n<h3>2. What are the best ways to understand that your website has been penalized?&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>The easiest way to understand if you have been penalized is to check the number of organic views your website has. If you see that there is a sudden drop after a particular day on the chart, then it is most probable that your website was penalized on that particular day. That is just what has led to the decrease in the number of searches. Also, if you are aware of the keywords for which your websites appear in the search results, check on them. If they have lost their position by quite a margin, then it is most probable that your website is penalized.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nSo, with that, we do hope that you have a clear understanding of Google Algorithm Update all that you should never indulge in to make sure that you keep growing year on year and you never get a penalty from Google. In case you have anything else that you want us to help you with, please let us know in the comment section. We would try to answer as many questions as we can! Do let us know if this article helped!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'In this article, we would try to understand some practices that almost always get penalized by Google Algorithm Update', 'negative-impact-of-google-algorithm-update', 'Google Algorithm Update,Google Algorithm Update Negative Impact', 'Jewel', '2021-07-24 08:48:51', '2021-08-04 12:35:29'),
(30, 'Most Important Ranking Factors After Google Algorithm Update', 'Ranking Factors', 'ranking-factors-after-google-algorithm-update-1-1024x576.png', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>Most Important Ranking Factors</strong> On average, Google changes its algorithm at least 500-600 times every year. That might be shocking to you. But that is a fact, and that happens to be something that every blog and website owner has to go through. Many of the changes that the company brings along affect websites and their ranking. Yet, there are some of the most essential and fundamental features.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>If you take care of these, you would have the most negligible impact because of the changes in the algorithm. In fact, in some of the cases, you might not have any impact at all. So, in this article, we would try to understand the important key points. You would have to keep these in mind if you want your website to be resistant to any updates.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Content Is King:&nbsp;</strong></h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Remember that no matter what happens, content is always the king for Google. In every update that the company does, if there is one thing that almost always gets more important than the last time, it is the content that you have on your website. It is imperative to have the best content. Make sure that your content is crisp, engaging, and to the point.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Remember, when it comes to your SEO, the amount of time that the readers spend on every post of your website is something that Google will look into. This means that your website should be enticing to the clients.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>At the same time, your keywords are important, but make sure that you do not stuff them. Let the keywords flow in the content. Ensure that you provide every information related to the keyword you choose. This would further help in your ranking in whatsoever way possible. The third thing that you should keep in mind while writing your content is, make sure that you are as detailed as possible. This would help you portray yourself as the complete guide. One might need you in any particular thing possible. Trust us, this would help us grow in the best way possible!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Functional Website:&nbsp;</strong></h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>When you create your website, there are a few things that you need to keep in mind. Google tries to make sure that each user who visits the website has the best experience. Thus, you should make sure that your website is one of those that is exciting and, at the same time, easy to use.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>So, there are a few important things that you would have to keep in mind when you get into this particular phase. So, let us help you with some of them. First, make sure that every functionality you have on your website is working in the best way possible.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Make sure that the users are getting the expected outcome on every click or action on your website. This would make your website more accessible to the users and a favorite to your search engine. The next one would be to keep your website light. This is of utmost importance. It is seen that the websites that take a lot of time to load lose out on a very large chunk of the visitors that they receive. This means that you would also take a toll on your search engine rankings.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Thus, make sure that the website is light. You can do the same by using images and videos which are lower in size. The third thing that you should keep in mind is making sure that your website\\&#39;s different sections or elements do not move during the website\\&#39;s loading. So, you might have seen that the elements change their places before and after the website is loaded in various websites. This takes a huge toll on the customer experience.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>This happens especially when it is for some websites where you have to log in or click on a specific button as soon as you reach the website. These are some of the essential pointers that you should keep in mind while getting your website ready if you are looking to stay at the top of the business.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Mobile-Friendly Website:&nbsp;</strong></h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>In today\\&#39;s world, more than half the number of searches occurs on mobile devices. This means that mobile devices are growing more popular than traditional desktops or laptops. As a result of the same, the websites and blogs need to be completely mobile friendly. This means that your website must be completely functional on a mobile device and must not be distorted</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>If you do not take care of this, you would be losing out on a large chunk of the traffic that you could have otherwise looked at. However, that is not all. Google has also started honouring websites with a functional mobile website. This means that if you do not have a mobile-friendly website, it is most probable that you would not do well even on desktop and laptop devices.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>So, making your websites mobile-friendly is of utmost importance. So, if you have a website that is not so, make sure that you get your priorities right. You should get them working on the mobiles at the earliest that you can. This would boost your rankings and thus your revenues by quite a margin.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Well, these were some of the most fundamental pointers that you should keep in mind. This would help you fight over most of the Google algorithm updates. Your rankings on Google would not be much affected by these. So, let us now try to answer some of the most consistent questions that we do receive on this particular field by most of the readers and try to address them in the most simple way possible.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\\\"level\\\":3} -->\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>When are the algorithm updates released every year?&nbsp;</strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Well, there is no definite answer or pattern to this. The release dates can be any, and the updates are always the ones that help improve the customer experience on the website. But then there is no timeline to this.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\\\"level\\\":3} -->\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>How does a mobile-friendly website help in Google search results?&nbsp;</strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>The answer is pretty simple. Since the larger number of people on the search engine these days are on mobile devices, the number of people visiting your website and spending time on mobile devices is also higher. If these websites are not available on mobile, you will lose a large chunk of the viewers, which would hurt your website ranking. Remember that the number of views and the time spent by each viewer on the website is something that Google takes very seriously into account.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\\\"level\\\":3} -->\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Does having good content on my website mean that I would not be affected by the algorithm updates?&nbsp;</strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Definitely not! Having the best content is not all that Google looks at. Although it should be said that contents play a major role, but it is not the only thing that is important when it comes to Google. There are tons of other things that are taken into consideration, and you would have to make sure that you have all your ends secured.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>We hope that we have answered most of the questions and doubts that you might have had related to some of the essential pointers that you should tick off to make sure that your website is completely ready for the next algorithm update. If you need assistance to make your website ready for the next update, you can take the help of <a href=\"https://idotcommers.com\">iDotcommers</a>.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>We hope that you would be able to build a website that is resistant to almost all the updates that we might have in the years to come and would help you have a stable ranking!</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Google changes its algorithm at least 500-600 times every year, there are some most important ranking factors after Google Algorithm Update', 'ranking-factors-after-google-algorithm-update', 'Ranking Factors,Google Algorithm Update,Important Ranking Factors', 'Jewel', '2021-07-24 08:48:51', '2021-08-04 11:38:40'),
(31, 'How To Stay At Top In SERP | How Google Algorithm Affects Revenue', 'Google Algorithm', 'stay-at-top-in-serp-1024x576.jpg', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>Stay At Top In SERP</strong> The world is shifting to the online mode and there is, most probably, no business left that has not yet marked its online presence. <strong>The internet is getting cheaper by the day</strong> and finding an online audience has become a much easier thing. The biggest and most significant role played in all of it is of a search engine. Google is used by everyone and the algorithms that are used by it are highly complex.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/what-is-the-google-algorithm/\">These algorithms</a> must thoroughly be understood by the businesses so that they can keep their websites in good ranking.&nbsp;It is impossible for you to believe that you can save yourself from these algorithms and ranking scores. To get started, these algorithms will also have the potential of affecting your revenues and that is what we are going to discuss here. These updates are not a new thing in any way for the people who are working in the SEO domain and are aware of the process and mindset of Google behind these updates.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>The professionals are always ready to tackle such updates and if someone has hired a firm for their <a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/what-is-seo/\">SEO needs and requirements,</a> they will never get to know a thing about how these algorithms work.&nbsp;The guidelines that are issued with these algorithm updates must be met by the websites, if not; the ranking will go down instantly. It could only be understood by an SEO professional how hard it can get to fetch the website on the first page of the search result.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Now, that too is the case with ever-changing algorithms. Its continuous work and you will not get to keep the first spot forever. To stay at the first page with good rankings, you will have to keep continuously working towards it. It&rsquo;s necessary for you to stay updated on these updates and in case you are not paying attention to it, your business will suffer.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>How does it affect my business/website?</strong></h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Having your website on the search engine&rsquo;s first page is stuff you can boast about. There are various factors that will play their respective roles in the website ranking and you must also know that all the algorithm updates released by Google will not necessarily affect your website. However, you must not leave it up to that and not work towards it. The update might be the one that will affect certain criteria that you might have already fulfilled.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>The content that you have posted should be regularly updated and the quality must not deteriorate. As it&rsquo;s all based on how the algorithm understands it, it would be quite difficult for you to get back to a better ranking.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>If you are worried about not being able to find the correct vitals of your website, we would recommend going for the Page Speed Insights. It&rsquo;s a completely free service that you can use to know the ranking score of your desktop and mobile versions of the website.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>It will also provide you a detailed guide on the tips that you can implement to make your website better for your audience. The tool will provide three categories, red, yellow, and green. The areas that are completely ok and match the requirements will be marked under green, yellow will include the areas/elements that need to be worked upon, and lastly, red will represent the aspects you need to fix immediately to improve the rankings.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>As we discussed that not all the updates will affect your website the same way, it can be said that a few might also impact in a positive or a negative way.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>You might see a sudden spike or a downfall in the revenues, it might be due to some low-key update that you have missed. There are certain techniques that will help you in calculating the changes and we would also recommend monitoring your revenues so that you can make a correct judgment about the revenue after a particular update.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>The pages that are in Google&rsquo;s better ranking and are on the first SERP, will definitely fetch heavy clicks and you might also see enhancement engagement and time spent by a visitor on your page. All the factors that you have taken care of will show you good results once you have the desired traffic on your website.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>No doubt, Google algorithms are quite complex, but there is also no denying the fact that these are intended to provide more revenue to your business and an overall better experience to your targeted audience.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>3 Tips to Remain in the Good books of Google SERPs</strong></h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Once you have gained a good ranking and your hard work has finally paid off, now you need to stay at the top. In order to effectively do that, you will need to follow a few tips and make sure you are making yourself well-versed with the updates released by Google in its search engine algorithm.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>To get better results, you can also hire an SEO firm like ReachLocal for the best professional help. A marketing company will provide you with the best practices that are suitable for your business and are in sync with the latest algorithm updates.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\\\"level\\\":3} -->\r\n\r\n<h3>1. <strong>Add Voice Search</strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Having the option of voice search is one of the best things you can ask for while surfing through the internet. It is an element that is recently added by Google into its algorithm as a step taken towards making the user experience better. If your page hasn&rsquo;t been optimized for voice, it will not show in the results.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\\\"level\\\":3} -->\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>2. Rich Content</strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>The content that you are posting on the website should be accurate and grammatically correct. It should and must not be copied from any other source. If the algorithm finds the content to be a copied one, it will deduct multiple points from your website ranking score.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\\\"level\\\":3} -->\r\n\r\n<h3>3. <strong>Add Snippets</strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>The latest Google algorithm update offers a much higher ranking to the websites that are using snippets to provide precise information to visitors. The search engine might also include your snippet as the instant answer to a user&rsquo;s query.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\\\"level\\\":4} -->\r\n\r\n<p><strong>FAQ</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:yoast/faq-block {\\\"questions\\\":[{\\\"id\\\":\\\"faq-question-1626753275049\\\",\\\"question\\\":[{\\\"type\\\":\\\"strong\\\",\\\"props\\\":{\\\"children\\\":[\\\"Whats the most common factor in the low ranking?\\\"]}}],\\\"answer\\\":[\\\"If the website is taking a long time to load, it will definitely be the reason behind the low ranking. You must upgrade the servers to find a better speed.\\\"],\\\"jsonQuestion\\\":\\\"\\\\u003cstrong\\\\u003eWhats the most common factor in the low ranking?\\\\u003c/strong\\\\u003e\\\",\\\"jsonAnswer\\\":\\\"If the website is taking a long time to load, it will definitely be the reason behind the low ranking. You must upgrade the servers to find a better speed.\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"faq-question-1626753295409\\\",\\\"question\\\":[{\\\"type\\\":\\\"strong\\\",\\\"props\\\":{\\\"children\\\":[\\\"Are backlinks helpful?\\\"]}}],\\\"answer\\\":[\\\"It is an SEO technique that is highly used by professionals. Creating backlinks will enhance the ranking significantly.\\\"],\\\"jsonQuestion\\\":\\\"\\\\u003cstrong\\\\u003eAre backlinks helpful?\\\\u003c/strong\\\\u003e\\\",\\\"jsonAnswer\\\":\\\"It is an SEO technique that is highly used by professionals. Creating backlinks will enhance the ranking significantly.\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"faq-question-1626753323850\\\",\\\"question\\\":[{\\\"type\\\":\\\"strong\\\",\\\"props\\\":{\\\"children\\\":[\\\"Will it help to rank better if a voice search is added?\\\"]}}],\\\"answer\\\":[\\\"Yes, the voice search feature is taken highly by the latest Google algorithms. If your web page has a voice search, it will come up in the SERP.\\\"],\\\"jsonQuestion\\\":\\\"\\\\u003cstrong\\\\u003eWill it help to rank better if a voice search is added?\\\\u003c/strong\\\\u003e\\\",\\\"jsonAnswer\\\":\\\"Yes, the voice search feature is taken highly by the latest Google algorithms. If your web page has a voice search, it will come up in the SERP.\\\"}]} -->\r\n\r\n<p><strong><strong>What&rsquo;s the most common factor in the low ranking?</strong></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>If the website is taking a long time to load, it will definitely be the reason behind the low ranking. You must upgrade the servers to find a better speed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><strong>Are backlinks helpful?</strong></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>It is an SEO technique that is highly used by professionals. Creating backlinks will enhance the ranking significantly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><strong>Will it help to rank better if a voice search is added?</strong></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Yes, the voice search feature is taken highly by the latest Google algorithms. If your web page has a voice search, it will come up in the SERP.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:yoast/faq-block --><!-- wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Conclusion</strong></h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Google is continuously working towards making these algorithms a better functioning tool. The user experience is everything for a search engine and it&rsquo;s crucial for a website or a business to be head-to-head with it and keep tweaking the changes that the update requires.&nbsp;For more updates, and to keep your website updated with all the Google Algorithm updates, you can refer to<a href=\"https://idotcommers.com/\"> iDotcommers.</a></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'How To Stay At Top In SERP, How does Google Algorithm Update affect my business/website, 3 tips to remain at top in google serp', 'stay-at-top-in-serp', 'Google Algorithm,Stay At Top In SERP', 'Jewel', '2021-07-24 08:48:51', '2021-08-04 12:37:59');
INSERT INTO `blog` (`id`, `blog_title`, `blog_category`, `image1`, `image2`, `description`, `description1`, `blog_url`, `tags`, `author_name`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(32, 'Crucial Updates By Google In Its Algorithm | Google Algorithm Updates', 'Google Updates', 'crucial-updates-by-google-in-its-algorithm-1024x576.jpg', NULL, '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<p><strong>Crucial Updates by Google</strong> If you are dealing with <a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/digital-marketing-trends-2021-trends-to-watch-in-2021/\">digital marketing</a> in any form, it&rsquo;s extremely crucial for you to understand the Google algorithms and how it keeps making tweaks in them<strong> to offer better search engine optimization.</strong> As per the search engine mogul, it keeps changing the algorithm no less than a thousand times a year.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>The Google updates will be responsible for enhancing the search results and will constantly work towards the precise results. <strong>These algorithms are highly based on logic and mathematics</strong>.<strong> </strong>and if you are running a website or any SEO-related tasks, you must know the key details of these updates.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>For even an advanced user, the changes that these updates will bring are quite small for the majority of the time. An average user can understand it in the way that these algorithms are highly perplexing codes. That are written to fetch data from its search catalog. <strong>Google uses a numerous </strong><a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/ranking-factors-after-google-algorithm-update/\"><strong>number of factors that are basically used to rank the web pages.</strong>&nbsp;</a></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Here, we are going to discuss a few top updates that Google has done recently. In the latter part of the blog, we will also briefly discuss the impact that it had on the search engine over the past few years.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>FS Deduplication</strong> - The Crucial Updates By Google</h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>You must have seen the result that is in the featured snippet to occur twice on the search engine result page. Through this update, Google has now restricted double-dipping completely. Earlier, the pages with FS used to get another listing on the first page of the results, as well.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>The update was introduced in January last year and it was implemented globally. Apart from being selected as the featured snippet, the organic listing will move to the first spot on the next page.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>January 2020 Core Update</strong></h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Google describes all of the updates that it releases in detail and it offers users and marketers to analyze their content and improve accordingly. The January 2020 Core Update was a very discreet one where it played with the rankings of the web pages.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>For example, if you have created a list of films based on their rankings, after a few years, a few of these movies will go down and new ones will come up. The same is done with this core update in the search results. To cope up with this updated algorithm, you will need to keep updating the content on the webpage.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Page Experience Update</strong></h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>The update has now been rolled out on June 15 and will be completely rolled out incrementally. There will be no drastic change that you will witness on the website after this update. The algorithm will further precise the browsing experience for a wide number of users. The signals will be accessed by the algorithm and it will provide the score on the experience report on the search console that can be accessed by the owner.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>A good score can be achieved by a few determining factors such as mobile usability, security issues, and it must be surfed over HTTP. the webpage must also offer a better ad experience.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Google Passage Rankings</strong> - Crucial Updates By Google</h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>There are certain users who find themselves confused about Passage Rankings with the Featured Snippets. The snippets will provide you with a safe and simple result that will also be called instant results. It will provide you a simple and easy answer to the search that you have made.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>However, the Passage results will contain much more information rather than being a precise answer. It might also contain multiple blue links that can be clicked to reach another page/source. The update was released on Feb 10 this year and now, passages will also be a determining factor in the website ranking.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading -->\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Product Review Update</strong> - Crucial Updates By Google</h2>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Google has released the update on April 8 and it will be focused on enhancing the websites that include in-depth research for the product reviews that are listed there. The sites and the content that is posted on the review page should not be just the content that summarizes the product.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>The search engine tycoon has also added that it is not a core update. Well, there is a twist that you should know. In the announcement, Google stated that the advisory that is implemented for the core update will also be applied here.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\\\"level\\\":3} -->\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Impact of Google Algorithm Updates on SERPs</strong></h3>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>When it comes to optimizing your website according to the search engine, there are various factors that one needs to keep in mind. The process can&rsquo;t be done overnight and it&rsquo;s also not the one-time job that you can just get done with. The updates released by Google in its algorithms will impact a number of SEO factors.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>Once an update is released, you should go through the whole release and announcement to understand it completely. Next, you should tweak your website with those adjustments and updates.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>The updates are generally released by Google every month, once or twice. It can be a core update or a feature update based on the tweaks that it is going to offer. It can also happen that the update might not affect your website. While you are on SEO, there are a few things that you should know. There are various people who are into illegal practices of SEO and Google keeps monitoring these things to improve efficiency.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>There will also be a few updates that will significantly impact the website. Well, it might not happen that all the updates impact your ranking equally. Each algorithm update will affect different parts of SEO and the determining factors will be keyword stuffing, quality of the content, duplicacy, and non-optimized content.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>There are still various other factors that will be affected by Google algorithms. These factors will constantly be checked on your website and based on the score, it will go up and if there are any discrepancies, the ranking will go down.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\\\"level\\\":4} -->\r\n\r\n<p><strong>FAQ</strong></p>\r\n<!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:yoast/faq-block {\\\"questions\\\":[{\\\"id\\\":\\\"faq-question-1627033205784\\\",\\\"question\\\":[{\\\"type\\\":\\\"strong\\\",\\\"props\\\":{\\\"children\\\":[\\\"As far as the Google algorithms go, whats the latest update?\\\"]}}],\\\"answer\\\":[\\\"The latest updates that are released recently include passage indexing and FS drop. Both the updates needed to be dealt with precisely so that your website can remain on the top.\\\"],\\\"jsonQuestion\\\":\\\"\\\\u003cstrong\\\\u003eAs far as the Google algorithms go, whats the latest update?\\\\u003c/strong\\\\u003e\\\",\\\"jsonAnswer\\\":\\\"The latest updates that are released recently include passage indexing and FS drop. Both the updates needed to be dealt with precisely so that your website can remain on the top.\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"faq-question-1627033217402\\\",\\\"question\\\":[{\\\"type\\\":\\\"strong\\\",\\\"props\\\":{\\\"children\\\":[\\\"Which was the most important algorithm update?\\\"]}}],\\\"answer\\\":[\\\"It is said to be none other than BERT, the one released in Oct 2019. With this update, Google has managed to change its search engine capabilities significantly.\\\"],\\\"jsonQuestion\\\":\\\"\\\\u003cstrong\\\\u003eWhich was the most important algorithm update?\\\\u003c/strong\\\\u003e\\\",\\\"jsonAnswer\\\":\\\"It is said to be none other than BERT, the one released in Oct 2019. With this update, Google has managed to change its search engine capabilities significantly.\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"faq-question-1627033242034\\\",\\\"question\\\":[{\\\"type\\\":\\\"strong\\\",\\\"props\\\":{\\\"children\\\":[\\\"How often are these updates released by Google?\\\"]}}],\\\"answer\\\":[\\\"The algorithm updates are released quite frequently as Google keeps continuously working to improve the overall search engine experience for its users.\\\"],\\\"jsonQuestion\\\":\\\"\\\\u003cstrong\\\\u003eHow often are these updates released by Google?\\\\u003c/strong\\\\u003e\\\",\\\"jsonAnswer\\\":\\\"The algorithm updates are released quite frequently as Google keeps continuously working to improve the overall search engine experience for its users.\\\"}]} -->\r\n\r\n<p><strong><strong>As far as the Google algorithms go, what&rsquo;s the latest update?</strong></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The latest updates that are released recently include passage indexing and FS drop. Both the updates needed to be dealt with precisely so that your website can remain on the top.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><strong>Which was the most important algorithm update?</strong></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>It is said to be none other than BERT, the one released in Oct 2019. With this update, Google has managed to change its search engine capabilities significantly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><strong>How often are these updates released by Google?</strong></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The algorithm updates are released quite frequently as Google keeps continuously working to improve the overall search engine experience for its users.</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:yoast/faq-block --><!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'If you are dealing with digital marketing in any form, its extremely crucial for you to understand the Updates by Google In Its Algorithm.', 'crucial-updates-by-google', 'Crucial Updates By Google,Google Algorithm Update,Google Crucial Updates', 'Jewel', '2021-07-24 08:48:51', '2021-08-04 12:42:35'),
(33, 'How to Monitor Google Algorithm Updates?', 'Google Algorithm', 'how-to-monitor-google-algorithm-updates.webp', NULL, '<p><strong>Monitor Google Algorithm Updates</strong> If you are a website or blog owner, then it is almost certain that if there is one thing that you keep working on all day, it is your website. And there is no doubt that once it has a great ranking, it&#39;s a matter of joy! But then, one fine morning, you end up finding that your website, which used to top the searches in one of the keywords, does not show up on the first page of the search results itself! It&#39;s heartbreaking.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\r\n\r\n<p>But then, having said that, do not worry! You are not the only one facing that. It is most likely because Google has come up with a new update. <strong>Every time Google comes up with a new update, </strong>a major section of the websites, lose out on the ranking. A few others emerge as the winners as they take on the positions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>So, in this article, we would try to understand how exactly we can monitor the <a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/crucial-updates-by-google/\">Google Algorithm updates. </a>One needs to understand the updates to work on the changes and get themselves prepared to be back at the top of the results. So, let us see how exactly we can do that!&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Set up A Google Alert:&nbsp;</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<h2><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>You can visit the website:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.google.com/alerts/\">www.google.com/alerts/</a>. Here, you can set up the perfect alerts for your website on Google. On this website, you can also set up alerts based on the following field, Phrase, Topic, Frequency, Source and Quality. Now you can set an update on something like &quot;Latest Google Algorithm Update&quot;. This means that you would get an alert right when an algorithm update comes through. You would be one of the first ones to get an alert, and this would give you the time to act!&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Follow The Industry:&nbsp;</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<h3><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>This is another tip that would help you better understand the industry. Follow the industry leaders, they are the best in business, and they are always on the lookout. Thus follow them as much as you can to make sure that you get all the updates from them. So, start following those who you think would have the knowledge and join the other blogger communities where you can have the best idea-sharing.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Google Webmaster Central Blog:&nbsp;</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<h3><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Although this is a blog that has not been used in the most recent years, now and then, Google uses this blog to inform the users of any big changes or updates that they were looking forward to implementing. So, keep a frequent eye on it. Or, if you can smell anything fishy, then this is one of those blogs or resources that you can always fall back on to check if there is something that you must have the knowledge about.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>MozCast:&nbsp;</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<h3><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>One of the most refreshing tools that you would find online. They are simple to use and understand. When it comes to search engine updates, they are one of those who have been trustworthy and consistent.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\r\n\r\n<p>MozCast shows the algorithms in the style of a weather report. So, you can check the turbulence, that is, the changes that the algorithm has gone through in the past 24 hours or even 30 days! Also, there are various other pointers that you can check on this website, like domain diversity, average result count and others.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>SEMrush Sensor:&nbsp;</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<h3><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>SEMrush is possibly one of those tools available for bloggers and website owners, each and every time they need one. If you want to track the algorithm yet again, you can take help from one of your constant companion, SEMrush. SEMrush Sensor shows the algorithm&#39;s volatility over the last 24 hours and up to 30 days.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This helps you to track if there has been a significant change in the algorithm. You can check on the range, which is out of 10, where anything below 5 means stable. Anything close to 10 means that the algorithm is heating up, and there might be an update on the cards!&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Rank Ranger:&nbsp;</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<h3><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>This is another tool that can be a real lifesaver when it comes to algorithm updates. The website keeps a constant eye on the SERP fluctuations in over 10,000 websites and keywords that they daily monitor. This means they have a decent sample file to test and understand if there is any change in the process daily.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Apart from informing you about the update, there is one thing that the website stands out for. It also tries to analyse how exactly the changes might impact us. This means that not only would you get the knowledge of a possible update, but you would also get a first-hand idea about how to deal with it.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Join Twitter:&nbsp;</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<h3><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>This is something that we would strongly suggest. Even if you fail to use any of the above, join Twitter and be in touch with some of the most influential bloggers. This would help you have the information at the earliest. These days, almost always, the first news of an algorithm update, apart from these tools, breaks out on Twitter itself. Also, evidently, the solution or the best turnaround to have the best ranking back is also shared on Twitter. Thus, joining Twitter and following the best in the business would help you in your efforts.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\r\n\r\n<p>So, these were some of the major pointers that you should keep an eye on to get an idea about any change in the algorithm at the earliest. So, before we move forward, let us try to check in some of the most frequently asked questions. This would help you have a clearer idea, and these are some of the questions that we most commonly receive about this particular topic.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} --></p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>1. How many times does Google update its algorithm in a year?&nbsp;</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<h4><!-- /wp:list --><!-- wp:paragraph --></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Google updates its algorithm by as many as 500-600 times every year. This means that almost every day, there is an update that Google is implementing in its platform to make it more user friendly.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, do you have to worry about all the algorithms? Well, in most cases, you would not have to worry about them. If you are one of the hard-working bloggers, then you already have yourself covered with the best resources. But, every once in a while, there would be a major change in the algorithm, which might impact your website. So, these are the updates that you need to be aware of.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true,\"start\":2} --></p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>2. How do I keep up with algorithm changes?&nbsp;</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<h4><!-- /wp:list --><!-- wp:paragraph --></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>You would have to keep in mind a few things to keep up with the algorithm changes. Keep track of the search rankings and the number of visitors to your website. Also, keep a close look at the various tools that you have in place. Following your favourite blogger will also help you understand if there is an update.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\r\n\r\n<p>These were some of the most important and easy ways to help you understand whenever Google undergoes some change in its algorithm. We have tried to help you with the most options possible to help you have the best idea about it. If you have any more questions about this particular topic, please feel free to contact us. Also, do let us know if this article could help you with the doubts that you might be having!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>', 'In this article, we would try to understand how exactly we can monitor Google Algorithm updates.', 'how-to-monitor-google-algorithm-updates', 'Google Algorithm Updates,Monitor Google Algorithm Updates,Monitor Google Algorithm', 'Jewel', '2021-08-06 16:10:37', '2021-08-06 16:33:44'),
(34, 'Does Google Have An Index Limit | What Is Indexing', 'SEO', 'google-index-limit.webp', NULL, '<p><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Index limit in Google</strong> Today almost everything related to the digital world is managed by computers. In such an advanced world, search engines such as Google plays a key role in the design of information infrastructure. These not only constitute the foundation for the internet and web but also impacts our general life in adverse ways.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\r\n\r\n<p>In this article, we are going to discuss the index property of search engines and specifically for Google, and its limitations if there exist any. But before jumping directly to the context of Google, we first have to learn the important basics about index limits.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading --></p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>What&#39;s Indexing?</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Everything on the web has its specific property and contribution to the overall infrastructure. And indexing is the main contributor to such a digital system. <a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/seo-tips-to-index-and-rank-new-content-faster/\" target=\"_blank\">Search engine indexing is one of the key aspects</a> upon which the World Wide Web is built.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The process of collecting, processing, and then storing any data to avail fast as well as exact information is called indexing in web search. This term may look simple; however, it consists of different disciplines in its design such as mathematics, language, computer science, and psychology.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Since it is generally used in search engines, it is often called web indexing. The search engines available on the internet have facilities that can index various formats of information such as text, audio, videos, and images too. Large services from different popular search engines such as Google use predetermined timing as well as different indexing systems to minimize the cost of running the whole network. Now one must be wondering, what&#39;s the purpose of such web indexing?</p>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Well, the sole purpose of indexing the data is to enhance the speed that occurred while searching anything on the engine. This ultimately optimizes the document required with the search query and increases the relevance with the web search.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\r\n\r\n<p>So, in simple words, if there is no index in the search engine, then it would have to go through all the data scanning for every document which will take an immense about of computational power as well as a huge processing time. This results in the availability of an answered query on the search engine in milliseconds rather than a sequential search which would take hours of the user time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} --></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Index limits</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Everyone wants their query to be answered as quickly as possible. And this is where the indexing of data comes into the picture. As discussed in the previous section, the different types, and properties of web indexing influence search engine optimization. And one of such aspects is the number of indexes involved in the system. Now the question arises, is there a limit for an index across different search engines?</p>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The answer to this question is yes, there exists a limit of the number of indexes depending upon the search engine. Various forms of indexing are used around the world by different search engines. The affectability of an index lies in its data structure which decides the overall performance of the web search.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Also, the index storage affects the design and architecture of search engines which potentially can change the index limit. So basically, when the data structure of the index changes, then the limits of the index changes with different search engines. In the next section, we shall be discussing the index limit of Google if there is any present in its architecture.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} --></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Index limit in Google</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\r\n\r\n<p>It&#39;s a common notion among everyone that there exists an indexed limit for every search engine. Well, not necessarily all of the search engines have such limits. And Google is a great example of that.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Before diving into the limits of the index in Google, we need to first shed some light on the difference between static HTML pages and dynamic ones. In simple words, static HTML pages can be described as those web pages, which don&#39;t change their content unless one admin changes them manually.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\r\n\r\n<p>On the contrary, dynamic pages have a different set of properties and here the contents can be changed by different visitors to the website. The changes made in static webpages in HTML format are rare whereas the dynamic pages cover changes regularly. So, to the question that whether there exists any index limit for Google, the answer will be no as long as you are considering static HTML pages. When the content is made available to Google, the whole process is automated and is controlled by search engine algorithms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\r\n\r\n<p>So, Google isn&#39;t able to differentiate between static pages and dynamic ones since there is no way to find out whether it was created or changed in any server. In simple terms, it never matters to the search engine whether you are uploading static pages or dynamic ones.&nbsp;Sometimes some websites try to add an extension of HTML in static pages to make them look dynamic which is completely unnecessary.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Google doesn&#39;t have any limit regarding the indexing process. And more importantly, Google bot doesn&#39;t differentiate between a million-page website freshly made or an old one with more visitors. So, there is a practically infinite number of indexes with static HTML pages which are included in Google as a search engine.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As of now we have explained everything very well about google index limit, but still you have any kind of doubt regarding google index limit, then you can watch this video <strong><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uG1VnZlwHgs&amp;ab_channel=GoogleSearchCentral\" target=\"_blank\">Google Index Limit&nbsp;by john muller</a>&nbsp; A Senior Webmaster Trends Analyst at Google.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} --></p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>Conclusion</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\r\n\r\n<p>One must consider the fact that Google always focuses most of its resources on areas that make more sense. Google doesn&#39;t have any specific preferences or reservations regarding the indexing of any website. The key lies in the static and dynamic type of HTML pages that constitute the website. From the above discussion, it can be seen that Google doesn&#39;t have such index limits.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Now, this means it can possess an infinite number of static pages with HTML type and that too in a single site. So, there is no such boundary condition for the number of such HTML pages ultimately leading to unlimited index. And the index is just an important part of the Google search engine which helps the algorithms to find the query answer more easily with greater search engine optimization thus making the whole process easier and faster.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>', 'In this article, we are going to discuss the index limit in google, does google have an index limit, and what is indexing', 'does-google-have-an-index-limit', 'Index Limit,Google Index Limit,SEO', 'Jewel', '2021-08-09 15:16:03', '2021-08-26 18:37:49'),
(35, '5 Trustworthy SEO Tools to Evaluate your Backlink Profile in 2021', 'SEO', 'trustworthy-seo-tools-in-2021.webp', NULL, '<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><strong>Trustworthy SEO Tools</strong> The website that you are handling will not remain on the top all by itself; there will be hours and days of hard work that you will need to put on it to keep in the good eyes of SERP. There are certain strategies and techniques that you must be following to maintain your website. The techniques and strategies fall under a broad term Search Engine Optimization. No matter what you are trying to achieve, the very core of your strategy should be to produce content that is original and rich in terms of quality.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The website that you have created must be kept updated, and you should also keep yourself updated with Google&rsquo;s and other<a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/increase-your-google-search-ranking/\" target=\"_blank\"> search engines&rsquo; algorithm updates </a>that will help you in knowing about the updated factors that will impact the SERP rankings. Among various factors, the one that generally remains on the top is to load your website with a number of backlinks.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The web pages that have the precise keyword selection will be given priority by these algorithms, and another factor that adds to the good SEO practice is creating backlinks.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --></p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>What is a Backlink?</strong><!-- wp:paragraph --></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>For someone who is not very familiar with the concept,<a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/purpose-of-backlinks/\" target=\"_blank\"> backlinks are basically the links that are created when a site takes you to another site.</a> These links are considered a significant SEO strategy because having a link created to another website will basically boost confidence. The search engine will send the indication that other websites are supporting the content that you have posted.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Well, it doesn&rsquo;t mean that all you need to do is create a link to your page and use it on other pages that are owned by you. Sorry to intrude on your thoughts, but that&rsquo;s not how it&rsquo;s done. The links that you are creating should be rich in quality so that they can impact the SERP score in a better way. If the link that you have created isn&rsquo;t a good one or is one the links that are called toxic, it will deteriorate all the efforts that you have made in getting a <a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/increase-your-google-search-ranking/\" target=\"_blank\">good search engine ranking.</a>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>\r\n\r\n<p>You might ask what a bad/toxic backlink is; though it&rsquo;s quite a broad topic, a simple answer is that the link will be considered a poor one if it&rsquo;s not authentic. The link that you are putting, if it&rsquo;s on the page that has no related content, it will trigger the search engine. Generally, this is the technique used by black-hat SEO, and it will not help you in finding a better SERP score.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Building the Backlinks: 5 Best Trustworthy SEO tools to put to use</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<h3><!-- /wp:paragraph --></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Once a detailed influx is done on the backlinks, you should also go through a few tools that will help you with a better implementation of these SEO strategies.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>1. Google Search Console</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>It&rsquo;s a completely free service that you can use to monitor the website that you own, and it will include troubleshooting and maintaining the key aspects. The Search Console will be a very helpful tool in enhancing the search result rankings.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The console will offer a set of handy tools that you will find drastically helpful in keeping the site up and running.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>It will help in better indexing the updated content along with fixing all the indexing issues that might be there on the posted content.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Search Console will also give you compiled data on all the search traffic. It will also provide you the details related to how often the site is appearing in the search result.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>In case of any spam or any other undocumented or non-recorded issue, the Search Console will send you the appropriate alerts. The tool will help you with all the data compiled in one place related to the present backlinks on your website.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>2. Screaming Frog</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>The tool is significantly helpful in the techniques that are used for onsite SEO. It&rsquo;s basically a crawler that will keep extracting the buried data and will audit all of it to find and troubleshoot any and all the SEO issues.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There is a free as well as a paid version where the free one will give you a limited run of 500 URLs, and by unlocking the paid version, you will find yourself a tool with a wide range of features and advanced tools.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Screaming Frog will help you find out the website links that are broken and are giving you the 404 errors. It will also find out the potential server errors.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The tool will also help in assessing the page tiles along with its metadata. It will provide you with a report that will include the excessively long/short content, duplicate content, or/and if something&rsquo;s missing.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The crawler will also analyze the progress and changes that are registered between two crawls. It will help in making sure where the strategy that is being used is effective or not.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>3. Ahrefs</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>The tool is widely used by a number of businesses and online marketers; the primary reason behind this is its versatility and easy-to-use interface. If you are going to compare the tools that are available in the market, especially for backlink building, Ahrefs is definitely the top one that one should go for.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A feature that makes this tool a more comprehensive one is the Keyword Explorer 2.0. It will research the most popular one for you, along with SERP details and related keywords.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The tool will give you a detailed site structure report with all the subfolders and subdomains. It will also help in fetching a major part of backlinks. Along with it, the report will also include the links that are not up to the mark in terms of organic traffic.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Ahrefs will also show you the changes that your website has witnessed in between two crawls or more. To get these details, you must have executed more than one crawl for your project.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The keyword research can be done on more than 10 search engines, and it will help you in getting the best SEO strategy implementation.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>4. Serpstat</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>The tool is also widely used for content marketing, and there are various professionals who are using this tool to boost their SEO rankings. The tool will compile all your marketing campaigns in one place.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the background, it will keep searching for the keywords that it believes will be good for your website. Before you make any decision, you must know that it&rsquo;s a paid tool, and the most affordable plan will include tracking up to 15,000 keywords.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The backlink analysis that is a core demand of SEO can easily be fulfilled by this advanced tool. You should know that there is no free version, and to start using the tool, you will need to subscribe for a minimum of $69/month.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The tool will also keep checking the relevance of your webpage and the content that it has to offer to the masses.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The basic plan will also include keyword research, where you will find the tool to work for you and find the relevant trends. It will also track the keyword ranking giving you a more detailed compilation of your website.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>5. Moz</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>It&rsquo;s a full package that you will find help with all the SEO tools that is focused on increasing the overall website rankings. The interface that you will get here is also very intuitive and rich in features. It will provide you with a long list of tracking features that will help in better implementation of the ranking techniques.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Moz Pro is just the perfect tool for all the time when you will need to track your previous position or in case you want to compare the stats at point A and point B.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>It will crawl around your website and will provide you with a detailed report after a full audit. Along with it, Moz will also keep sending you the alerts to keep you updated.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>There will also be many customized suggestions that you will get here to improve the SERP scores.&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Conclusion</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>We hope that this blog and handpicked tools for your SEO requirements must have been a little help to you. Website owners must realize the importance of good SEO practices. Though you will need to implement the strategies all by yourself, the tools that we have discussed here will only help you with better understanding on what&rsquo;s going on with all the stats of your website.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'You should go through a few trustworthy seo tools that will help you with a better implementation of these SEO strategies.', 'trustworthy-seo-tools', 'SEO Tools,Trustworthy SEO Tools,SEO', 'Jewel', '2021-08-13 12:42:04', '2021-08-25 13:02:12');
INSERT INTO `blog` (`id`, `blog_title`, `blog_category`, `image1`, `image2`, `description`, `description1`, `blog_url`, `tags`, `author_name`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(36, 'How Is Guest Blogging Worthy To Be On The Content Marketing checklist?', 'Blogging', 'how-is-guest-blogging-worthy.webp', NULL, '<p>One of the effective and significant marketing tools through content is Guest blogging. Guest blogging is nothing but writing blogs or content on another website in such a way that more traffic is generated to the website of the guest from the website where guest post or content or the blog is published.&nbsp;When people read the post of the guest on another website, they become conscious of the brand&#39;s existence, and thus the brand of the guest writer gets a boost.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Again, adding hyperlinks to the blog post allows readers to visit your website. As more and more search people click the hyperlink on your guest post, the search engine notices the increased activity in your website and uplifts the ranking of your website to the top of the search list. However, one should master the tips and tricks of guest blogging so that the fundamental objective of getting the leads in your website and the brand recognition is enhanced.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>The things to follow</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>To make guest blogging worthy through content marketing, one should follow certain tenets. They can be Google search operators, Backlinks of the competitors, prolific guest bloggers, social searches, and many more. All of these, somehow or other, influence the traffic on your website as you guest blog on other&#39;s pages. Let us discuss them a bit.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After deciding on the goal of guest blogging, like positioning oneself as an expert blogger, the required traffic to your website, and casually creating backlinks, it is time to search for the most popular blogs that attract the attention of a considerable segment and then write quality guest columns in them. Again, defining the goals in advance helps to select the proper blog post where guest blogging is allowed.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Finding the opportunities to Guest Post</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>One prime focus in the <a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/content-writing/\" target=\"_blank\">content marketing</a> checklist is finding the right blog where one can place guest posts. The primary blog should be niche and relevant to the subject that one is trying to promote. Make sure that the audience of the primary blog is also interested in your guest columns and has an interest in the industry in which the one is involved.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Next, find a blog that is making rounds in other social media and is one of the talking issues for many. As a content marketer, one should ensure that the blogger is also active in social media so that the guest posts also get shared, promoting the client&#39;s objective through their website.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Getting the right opportunities</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Finding the best blog and writing in them is not that easy. Not all bloggers allow guests to write on their page. So, again, many blog posts are not popular, and the fundamental objective of content marketing through guest blogging is lost.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Therefore, one needs to search extensively for the blogs related to some particular industry common with the client&#39;s industry, hugely popular so that the traffic on the client&#39;s website is increased by reading the guest posts and the primary blogger allows guests to write on their wall.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>1. Doing Google searches&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>One of the&nbsp;best&nbsp;methods&nbsp;of finding a suitable blogging site to write as a guest blogger is doing a Google search. It is best to type your &quot;niche and blogs&quot; on the Google search engine. A list of top blogging links will appear on the screen on your subject. The content marketing writer needs to check the blogging sites about the acceptance of guest writing and then proceed if allowed.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>One should look at the rating and the authority of the domain to find out the popularity of the blogging site so that your content can add value to your or the clients&#39; website. Keep in mind that your niche blog is only suitable for a particular geographical market area or segment. Therefore, the selection of the guest blogging site should be made judiciously.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Going for advance search in Google operators with specific commands like &quot;your keyword + write for me,&quot; &quot;your keyword + submit an article,&quot; &quot;keyword + guest post,&quot; &#39;keyword + now accepting the guest post,&quot; etc., can open up the opportunities for guest blogging in many of the best websites. The target of the content marketing professional is to find out the best guest blogging site with a similar niche and post the blog to get the leads to the website through the hyperlink.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>2. Communities for guest posting&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>One can look for various online communities helping guest writers to be in touch with niche bloggers. These processes may often not connect the content marketer with the best and the biggest blogs with their niche in these platforms. Still, they are an excellent place to hone up writing and marketing skills, including mastering the keywords to generate maximum traffic to a particular website.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sometimes, going through the blogger&#39;s directory can help guest bloggers find some of the best similar niches that match theirs. One can even look at the traffic in these websites over a period that allows a content marketer to select the most popular guest blogging site to take advantage of the site&#39;s traffic.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>3. Searching Social media networks</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/social-media-marketing/\" target=\"_blank\">Social media</a> has opened up considerable opportunities to many people, particularly for the guest bloggers involved in content marketing. With people spending more time on various social media platforms like Facebook, Twitter, LinkedIn, and many others, posting guest columns has become easy.&nbsp;One can set alarms for similar niches of theirs or can look at the competitors&#39; feed of promoting any guest blog and act accordingly.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Searching with similar keywords and niches as Google search in a particular social media platform can reflect the best results. One can even join various groups to be in touch with the admin, other bloggers, or web admins to get their blogs approved and posted. They open up the doors where competitor&#39;s backlinks never open up with relevant results.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>4. Finding and analyzing the backlinks of competitors&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>As a content marketer, one always tries to make the guest blogging topics worthy. One of the best methods is to analyze the backlinks of the competitor using tools like SEMRush or Ahrefs. Using these tools can help you to understand the source of the backlinks of the competitors. Once you get the backlinks, chances are there that your guest post will also be accepted and posted on the most popular blog page with similar niches.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It also reflects that the blogging site is quite popular and can give good leads; else your competitors won&rsquo;t have used the site. Posting and requesting the admin to publish your blog can help to gain more traffic to your website.&nbsp;Again one can personally in touch with some blogger friends, who in turn introduce you as a guest blogger to others in the blogger community so that your article is published.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Interacting with the blog commentators after your guest blog is approved and posted draws the attention of others. Once a blog is posted, it receives comments, and interacting with the commentators helps keep your blog on the top list, giving some good leads and opportunities. One can get more backlinks and make a database of them for the requirement in the future. One should look at all the opportunities and explore them to fulfill the content marketing objective through guest blogging.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>FAQs</h4>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>How to make the guest blog-worthy?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>One should never forget that SEO gains success on strategy. As a guest blogger, one should never over-promote the brand or ever try to be too hard to sell a product. One should have reasonable control over the language and avoid using hyperlinks as far as possible.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The blog itself should be attractive so that the reader should automatically fall into the trap and visit your designated website. One should use keywords and place them strategically to lead the reader to the desired link.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>How fast the guest blog gets published?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>One should keep some patience and follow up with the web owner after submitting the guest blog. With Google, one has to follow certain norms and guidelines so that low-quality blogs are not promoted, or the blog only aims at creating the link.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Therefore, the admins have to go through the guest blog before publishing it else they might get penalized by Google for quality issues.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Do I need to pay to publish guest blogs?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Unless your worth is proven as a guest blogger, many popular blogging sites ask for money to publish them. However, once your worth is established and generate more traffic on your guest post, the owners will publish your guest blog for free. The more SEO- friendly your blog will be, the more your demand will be.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Why do guest blogs get rejected?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The websites that publish content from guests have made years of effort to be on the top of the list. They always want to publish quality contents that are not repetitive but SEO- friendly. Therefore, the best sites often reject guest blogs that do not fit their site&#39;s ethics and culture.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>To make content marketing worthy by writing guest blogs, one should follow the process mentioned herein. One has to have a good command of the language and find out the best site to generate more leads and traffics, maintaining SEO and other writing features.</p>', 'One of the effective and significant marketing tools through content is Guest blogging. To make guest blogging worthy through content marketing, one should follow certain tenets.', 'how-is-guest-blogging-worthy', 'Guest Blogging,Guest Blog,Content Marketing Checklist', 'Jewel', '2021-08-17 16:44:53', '2021-08-17 17:00:03'),
(37, 'How To Boost Ranking In Google Search Engine With Strategic Internal Linking?', 'SEO', 'boost-ranking-in-google-search-engine.webp', NULL, '<p>The discussion of enhancing the website ranking on the SERP through the internal linking strategy is seen to be a very complicated topic, and simultaneously, the discussion also revolves around the importance of such strategies.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The core concept of the strategy is quite simple and straightforward. All website owners should find themselves implementing such strategies to improve the overall performance of their website. It&rsquo;s quite advanced, as well as simple at the same time. Well, if you are finding it hard for you to implement it, we would always recommend going for some professional help.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This<a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/what-is-seo/\" target=\"_blank\"> search engine optimization</a> strategy is widely used by content marketers. These links are the clickable content that will take a user from one page to another on the same website. On the contrary, the external links will take the visitor to some other domain. The internal links will provide the search engine a better and more detailed understanding of the structure of the website. Along with it, having a good amount of internal links will also help the search engine and the users to understand the relevance of the content on your website.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Now, when it comes to implementing the internal links, there are various points to consider. These factors will be significantly helpful in enhancing the overall fitness of the website. Without any further delay, we are going to jump right into the tips that you will find helpful in the easy implementation of internal linking.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Regulating the structure</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>What we will recommend right away is to consider your website in the structure of a pyramid. The primary section or the top of the pyramid is generally the homepage of the website, moving down there will be some categories or sections that will be compiled under the Menu section. Further down the pyramid, there will be the pages/posts or basically any content that you post.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Relevance of content</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The next step will be the one where you will find the relevance of the content. The content that we are discussing here is the one that is related to the core of the business. It should be about the products and services that you are offering. Having such content will help you teach the search engine about the core purpose. There are various spots where you will get to insert the link and make the Google algorithm learn about your content.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Contextual link</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>On the website, you must have posted multiple contents related to a certain topic. These topics should be interlinked with each other, and you will see substantial growth in the performance ranking of the website. The stats related to the website will be shown on the Google Search Console. The interlinking can either be linked using any relevant sentence or just post a link on the bottom of the post. Also, never forget to add the backlinks from such cornerstone posts.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Create taxonomies</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>In today&rsquo;s world, taxonomies are a significant add-on to any website. The categories and proper tags will help in organizing the content on your website. It will also give the search engine a wide context about the nature of the content. The trick will help in linking the blog content. The visitor and readers will also find these links to be significantly helpful.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Why is strategic internal linking helpful?</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Now, after enough tips to efficiently implement the internal linking, we are also going to jot down the impact that it is going to have on your website. As a majority of you would know that Google has significantly taken up the game over the past years, it&rsquo;s next to impossible that anyone can tamper with the algorithm. Though it has become quite advanced, there are a few techniques that you will need to implement to boost the SERP rankings of the website.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>A better indexing</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The crawler will keep searching for the paths, and if the website has good internal linking, the crawler will find it much easier for it to get the website&rsquo;s right structure. Having a set path will help the bot to crawl faster.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Provides value to the visitors</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>While a visitor is searching for a topic, there are always a number of resources that they will go to. Having a better internal links set up, they will be able to find multiple resources on one topic, easily. It might be just another post, or the visitor will need to find another post by the same author. It will also significantly enhance the post quality by providing better links and relevant anchor texts.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>A better dashboard</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The links that are seen to be available on the website in the form of interlinks will not only offer a better and enhanced navigation, but will also provide a much better and more functional dashboard to your website. The visitors will also get to go through the website without any hassle.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>FAQs</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Q1. Are internal links and backlinks the same?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>No, the internal links are the links that will navigate you through the website internally. It will help you in making the search engine understand your website in a much easier way. However, the backlinks are the links created to link your website to a different domain or any other external post.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Q2. How internal links will help in better SEO?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Google algorithm will use its crawlers to identify the relevant content, and if it sees a number of links leading to the same content, it will find it to be a high-priority one. These internal links will help you implement better SEO, and we recommend doing it because, as a site owner, you will have better control of it.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Q3. Any extra tips to implement in this SEO strategy?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Well, if you are looking for a bonus tip, you should add a Related Post section at the last of every post. It will help visitors to find more relevant content without tirelessly searching your website for it.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>Conclusion</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>As a website owner, you must know the significance of good SEO. The topic that we discussed here is a part of a wide range of SEO techniques, and once implemented, you will find it significantly helpful in the website rankings. The internal links will not only help in better navigation, but it will also guide the search engine to understand the structure in a much better and easier way. Once you consider the website a pyramid, it will become quite efficient for you to add categories and tags.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'How To Boost Ranking In Google Search Engine With Strategic Internal Linking, Why is strategic internal linking helpful, and How internal links will help in better SEO.', 'boost-ranking-in-google-search-engine', 'Boost Ranking,Google Search Ranking,Boost Ranking In Google', 'Jewel', '2021-08-21 12:33:37', '2021-08-21 12:33:37'),
(38, 'Purpose Of Backlinks | What Makes Backlinks And Google Rankings Correlate', 'Backlink', 'purpose-of-backlinks.webp', NULL, '<p>A backlink may not be something that most of us are aware of, but it adds up immensely to the betterment of a website, resulting in better search results and more <a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/boost-ranking-in-google-search-engine/\" target=\"_blank\">optimized Google searches.</a>&nbsp;Also, backlinks&nbsp;still remain one of the most valuable off-page SEO aspects and ranking&nbsp;signals in search <a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/what-is-the-google-algorithm/\" target=\"_blank\">algorithms of Google.</a> And hence, you must care and know about how you can leverage this factor to generate leads.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>So, in this segment, you will come to know about the various aspects of backlinks and how you can ensure your website has effective backlink tracking.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What is the purpose of a backlink?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>It is crucial to understand the basic functionality of a backlink to ensure we truly understand its potential and the various opportunities it provides to a particular website. So, to put it simply, a backlink is a link that replicates the purpose of a hyperlink while pointing directly back to the specific webpage in consideration. This can be done with any webpage that is part of the website you ought to consider.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In other words, when someone clicks a link that is meant to relocate you to a particular website, that website also receives a backlink that reaches back to the original website. Thus, a backlink replicates a trail that connects two web pages from different websites. Moreover, the former can use the backlink to get back to the original website. However, this is just the basic understanding of how backlinks function, and there are numerous ways to be beneficial for your website.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>How do valuable link-backs affect SEO and then Google Ranking?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Backlinks have remained one of the top contenders to dominate the SEO industry for a long time now. Given the expansion in the internet-based businesses and firms right now, it would be safe to say that every website needs to focus on backlinks to ensure they are not trailing behind their competitors. Thus, having an essential sense of backlinks and how to use them with maximum efficiency is very important.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There are two primary reasons to use backlinks efficiently and effectively:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Backlinks help to increase the search engine rankings massively.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Backlinks provide extensive exposure to your website from other external sources, which generally accounts for the growth and reach of your website.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>In the next segment, you will be brought to light with some of the most helpful ways in which backlinks can achieve this feat.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>How do backlinks impact a website&rsquo;s search engine ranking?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Backlinks behave like votes that indicate the relevance of your web page&#39;s blog or content. Thus, if you can manage enough admins from other websites to have a look at your content, you will be able to achieve massive popularity in very little time through the usage of backlinks. So, it would engage active customers on your website and indicate a sense of positive growth to the respected search engine management protocols.&nbsp;Thus, using backlinks, you can effectively engage enough traffic to your website.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This is reflected in the popularity of your content. So, the greater the number of active and efficient backlinks you can achieve, the more will increase the number of people going to visit your website regularly. However, it is not easy to differentiate the backlinks that are significant to your cause from those that do not impact growth in any manner.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thus, it is necessary to pay close attention to your website&#39;s statistics and analytics. Nonetheless, it is crucial to understand the fundamental factors driving the backlinks and making them practical for a website.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What factors impact the effectiveness of backlinks?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>As mentioned earlier, backlinks can upgrade SEO quality and impact it heavily in reach and traffic. Thus, if you can use backlinks efficiently and more often, you can effectively flood your webpage with enough clients. Moreover, you can also make sure that your website<a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/rank-higher-on-google/\" target=\"_blank\"> ranks considerably higher in the search engine rankings</a> in a matter of a few months or so. Thus, it will lead to establishing the mark of your brand in the sights of web rankings and outreach.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, you must know what efficient backlinks work like and what differentiates them from those that do not add value and productivity to your website. For that, you should know about the various aspects that govern the effectiveness of backlinks. Here are some of the significant criteria that dictate the feasibility and efficiency of backlinks:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>1. Authority</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>This is the primary step to test the feasibility of any backlink. It would be best to target the authority websites with a seemingly higher audience and directly impact their customer&#39;s interests. These are shockingly much harder to summarize, mainly if your website is a new one and has a fresh start to its career. There are probably only a few reasons for an established website to work favorably with a new and freshly started organization.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To measure the authority of a website, Page Rank or PR is generally used very often. This is an online rank that has been assigned to a website by search engines. You are highly recommended to target the websites with a PR higher than your website and carry the steps accordingly to highlight your content. As long as you keep targeting the web pages that are superior to you and keep achieving decent results, you are on the right track.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Such backlinks are considered to be highly beneficial, given the circumstances your website is in. An active backlink from an established webpage will provide enough traffic and highlight your new journey.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>2. Theme</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The theme of a backlink in consideration is something you would need to pay great attention to. If your blog is based on agriculture and plantation, and it is very often visited and addressed by other blog admins that manage similar web pages, it would be highly beneficial for you.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It shows that your content is quite relevant, and your peers from a similar field are also interested in your views. Thus, this is kind of giving your website a greater chance of growth. In terms of SEO, your website will most probably be displayed in the Google search results when keywords related to this topic are looking for in the search engine.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You are also suggested to consider related specialties as these will likewise be of advantage. For example, you might need to target backlinks from sites that pay attention to home upgrades, bird watching, sheds, lakes, or other perhaps related subjects for a planting blog.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>3. Anchor Text</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The primary text or content in the backlink that you use is known as the Anchor Text, and it also plays a crucial role in the success you are looking for. So, if you are not yet sure about the syntax of your backlink, you must not come off as vague or unnecessary in this segment. Proper usage of keywords and a strong motive are necessary to attract your potential audience.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When people follow the backlink that you have provided, it peruses the anchor text. Therefore, if you can utilize related catchphrases inside your anchor text, it will imply the web search tools regarding the subject the connection is identified with. Consequently, it would be best if you utilized the keyword with rich anchor text that applies to the objective of the link or the catchphrase you are expecting to work on your rankings for.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Some Related FAQs</h4>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Q1. What is the purpose of a backlink?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ans. A backlink is a link that trails back to the previous website in consideration. Thus, it can be of great use when it comes to online visibility and client outreach. The best way to utilize backlinks is to target an already established website with a PR higher than your website.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Q2. How does a backlink function?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ans. When you click a link pointing towards a particular website, you leave a link that trails back to the former. This helps small web pages and blog sites attract and acquire potential audiences and clients from hubs filled with large groups of people.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Q3. Do backlinks work in 2021?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ans. Given the large number of people that use the internet today, it would be best to say that backlinks are more effective than ever. However, you must choose and implement these links very effectively to benefit from their function.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Q4. Are backlinks good for SEO?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ans. Yes, backlinks play a pillar role when it comes to SEO management for a particular website. Backlinks have the capability of enhancing the search engine rankings of your website very quickly so that your outreach is extended enormously.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Conclusion</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>This article focuses on the proper utilization and implementation of backlinks to create a stable and profound hub for new websites. As we all know, backlinks can engage heavy traffic and outreach for any website, and thus, it would be best to understand how to conduct this procedure. In this blog, you have been brought to light with some of the most effective ways of utilizing backlinks to generate a better overall search engine ranking. An improved search engine ranking will eventually lead to better search results and outreach. Thus, it is necessary to pay proper attention to this crucial aspect.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'the purpose of backlinks is simple, it replicates a trail that connects two web pages from different websites. Moreover, the former can use the backlink to get back to the original website.', 'purpose-of-backlinks', 'Purpose Of Backlinks,Backlink,What Is Backlink', 'Jewel', '2021-08-25 12:50:15', '2021-08-25 12:50:15'),
(39, 'Why Ignoring 404 Errors A Bad Off-Page SEO Practices', 'SEO', 'why-ignoring-404-erors-a-bad-off-page-seo-practices.webp', NULL, '<p>It becomes quite frustrating when you type in a URL and find an error message displaying&nbsp;404 not found. The error message may be due to an internal error where either the content has been deleted or moved, or the domain name does not exist any longer. In some websites, the error message is displayed in the initial stage as the URL is inappropriate from the initial stage.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>This often leads to visitors&rsquo; dissatisfaction. Here&rsquo;s how:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>In most cases, where you find the error&nbsp;404 not found,&nbsp;the website redirects you to the actual website that you were searching. It is mainly because the original webpage had some errors, but the developer forgot to remove it entirely from the functioning link. A proper functioning link is an advantage to the company. Thus, when there is an error message on the webpage, it affects the SEO as it mostly depends on the number of visitors visiting the site.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Often customers do not feel the need to try other keywords to search the webpage because of lack of time unless it is urgent. Hence the count of customers visiting the site starts melting down, and the ranking of the webpage is also affected badly. What should you do then?</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Keep a Constant Vigil</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>If you want to <a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/boost-ranking-in-google-search-engine/\" target=\"_blank\">improve the ranking of your website,</a> it should have a well-deserved design and technique. Hence, if the search engine results give an error message, especially&nbsp;404 not found,&nbsp;it&nbsp;will significantly impact the count of the visitors visiting the web page.&nbsp;It will be good practice to keep a check on the web pages occasionally.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Moreover, if there is an error message, you must try to resolve it as early as possible. It will help to maintain your ranking, and the visitors will not be disappointed. Here&rsquo;s a quick guide on how to locate and fix 404 errors:</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>3 Best Tools you can Use to Locate 404 Errors</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The first option to fix errors on your web page is to locate the exact errors obstructing it to open. You can avail yourself of numerous tools for free from the internet to locate&nbsp;404 not found&nbsp;error messages. The tools will help you find the broken links easily so that you will fix them as soon as possible for the smooth running of your web page. Some of the best-known tools that will be able to solve the problem in locating the errors are as follows:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>1. Google Search Console</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>If you have a Google account and have registered your website through that account, you will have the freedom to use the Google search console. It is a free tool that will help you find the errors in your website. If there are any&nbsp;404 not found&nbsp;error messages on any of the web pages, it will quickly locate them and display them in the web tool.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You will be able to monitor and resolve all server errors, including any site load that returns an error message. It is easy to use and does not require an expert to resolve your web page issues.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Click on the Google Search Console and log in with your username and password</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Click on &quot;Coverage&quot; and select the &quot;Excluded&quot; tab</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>You will see a list of all the&nbsp;404 not found&nbsp;error messages.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Click on each of the messages to see the complete list of the web pages.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>2. Dead Line Checker</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Dead Line Checker is the easiest and fastest way to find errors on your website.&nbsp;It is a free application that can check your website instantly by simply entering the URL. You will get the option to either check a single web page or the whole website.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You must use Dead Line Checker more than often to identify broken links quickly and prevent you from further embarrassment. Your website will run smoothly, thus, increasing its ranking.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>3. W3C Link Checker&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>W3C Link checker is a powerful and free online tool that can quickly inspect the broken line of your website and display the summary. Hence, you will be able to locate your web page&#39;s errors quickly and solve them as early as possible.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You can download and install it on your computer and use it frequently to monitor the functionality of your website. An ideal tool, the W3C line checker, will help you to keep away those sleepless nights.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>How to fix 404 Errors? Reasons for the Occurrence of 404 Error&nbsp;</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>- There are many reasons for a webpage that returns a&nbsp;404 not found&nbsp;error message. In some cases, the problem can be minute, but it can ruin your business if you do not take action instantly. Hence, it would be best if you came to a proper solution to fix the errors as soon as possible.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Some standard solutions will help you to fix the problem of your website:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>1. Redirect your error page</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>When a visitor gets a&nbsp;404 not found&nbsp;error message, most of the time, he will not search it again, and you will ultimately lose your customer. Hence if there is an error message on the webpage, solve it immediately by redirecting the page to the web page working on your website with the relevant information.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It will help get a positive response from your visitors as they did not have to wait long before arriving at the relevant web page.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>2. The Source Link must be corrected</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>If you find any broken links preventing your web page from opening, you must immediately try to fix it from its source. However, in some cases, when you find that you cannot fix the broken links, redirect the page to the actual page that the visitor wants to explore.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You must also make sure that the redirected page contains all the relevant information required; otherwise, they will become confused.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>3. You must check the External Links</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>A website may have some dead links because you have modified the website or deleted some pages. It is a common practice where most of the dead links are left untouched. It is a severe problem for the website as it may damage the ranking.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Many websites still appear in the search engine, and hence when you try to visit the site, you get a&nbsp;404 not found&nbsp;error message. You must regularly check the external links of your website and come to a solution whenever there is an error message.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Related FAQs</h4>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Q1. How 404 not found error message can damage your business</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Most of us use Google as the preferred search engine to find the web pages of our choice, but if a 404 not found error message pops out by visiting the site, it will create a negative impression. You will feel that the web page is not opening because of poor maintenance, and in the process, it will affect its ranking badly. The number of visitors visiting your website will ultimately ease off, and you will be responsible for ruining your business.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Q2. Why should you put links on a 404 error page?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>When you try to visit a website by entering the URL and find that the page is not being displayed and returning an error message, it can become quite frustrating. You will ultimately lose the total count of visitors as it will create a negative impact.&nbsp;If you can put a link on a 404 error page, it will redirect the visitor to the relevant page that is trying to find.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Moreover, you must ensure that the redirected page does not get him landed on an entirely irrelevant page. It will result in the downfall of your website.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Q3. How do 404 not found affect the ranking of a website?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>A 404 not found error message can seriously affect the ranking of a website, and hence you must resolve it as early as possible. If a page returns an error message, it means that the page does not exist; the search engines will not index it further.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Q4. What are the most common errors that visitors make will search a website?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sometimes you make some common mistakes that return an error message. Hence before jumping to a conclusion, check whether if you have entered the correct URL. Try to reload the page if it shows a 404 not found message or use a search engine to get the best results.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>Conclusion&nbsp;</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>When you are managing a website, you must have an eagle-eye as minor errors can disrupt the number of visitors. You must always check the functionality of your website and see that all the web pages are running correctly. If a visitor can easily access the website&#39;s landing page, he will be satisfied, and hence the outcome will always be positive.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>An error message on your website can ruin your business. It can significantly impact your website&#39;s SEO performance. You must fix the errors at the earliest and prevent them from downfall. A well made attractively designed website always creates the count of the visitors. Hence you must make sure that it works smoothly and efficiently.</p>', 'Lets See Why ignoring 404 Errors a Bad SEO Practices, How to fix 404 Errors, and reasons for the Occurrence of 404 Error.', 'bad-off-page-seo-practices', '404 error,Off Page SEO,Off Page SEO Practices', 'Jewel', '2021-08-30 12:50:09', '2021-08-31 12:32:25'),
(40, 'Which one is effective: Facebook ads or Google Adwords?', 'Digital Marketing', 'facebook-ads-or-google-adwords.png', NULL, '<div>In the world of marketing, there are various channels that you can choose from. If you are on the task of finding the top results, you will find only two names dominating the whole market. These are Facebook ads and Google Adwords. As a business owner myself, it was quite a difficult decision to settle on one according to the needs.&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<p>After investing a significant portion of my time in research, I found out that there is a false sense of competition established between the two. These are quite different services and we would recommend investing in both services for the best possible returns on getting the leads and enhancing their visibility.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Key differences between&nbsp;Facebook Ads and&nbsp;Google Adwords</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>You might want to just dive into the benefits and key strengths; however, we assume that you must know the key differences between Facebook Ads and Google Adwords<strong> </strong>before everything else. For starters, we would just say that these two marketing platforms work on completely different structures.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Having your business on these services will help you reach a precise audience, all thanks to a wide range of targeting options that are offered to you.&nbsp;Now, without any further due, let&rsquo;s dive into the key differences:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Google Adwords</h3>\r\n\r\n<div>This service offers you a paid search and Google has dominated the market in such a way that for a user, Google Adword is the only option when it comes to <a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/best-tips-to-run-google-ad-campaign/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>pay-per-click advertising</strong></a>. There are also other options, for example, Bing Ads is also based on the same structure and works similarly. Unlike Facebook Ads, Adword offers the advertising service based on the keywords and the campaign will primarily be based on written text.&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<p>The advertiser will try to bid on the specific keywords that the users will enter in the search bar. The campaigns created on Adword will appear right next to the queries made by the users.&nbsp;In this model, the advertiser will be charged by Google only when the user will click on that campaign. The topics of keyword bidding in PPC advertising and its optimization are quite extensive and there is no need for them to be discussed here.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>All you need to focus on is that Google Adword is the service used by a number of users to easily find their targeted audience.&nbsp;The key differences can be wrapped in one line; Facebook will help your customers spot you and on the contrary, the Adword will allow you to find potential customers.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>Google Adword: Key advantages</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>When it comes to wired marketing, Google has the widest presence and for a majority of advertisers, Adword is almost synonymous with PPC advertising. It is the world&rsquo;s most used search engine and registers a whopping 3.5 billion queries per day. The search engine offers the best tools to locate the audience that is trying to search for the products and services.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This advertising platform works on two patterns; display and search. The latter will comprise the whole search engine and the bidding will be done through millions of keywords and phrases based on the search queries of the users. However, the display channel will include ad banners that can be considered as a total of 98% of the WWW. Banner ads are highly effective and cost-effective for the specific purpose of brand awareness.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A boundless audience:&nbsp;Everyone already knows this. The primary advantage that you will get with Adword is the immense reach that it has to offer. The search queries registered by Google every single second go up to 40,000 per second. Moreover, it translates to 1.2 trillion per annum.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The platform is becoming drastically practical every day, all thanks to Google&rsquo;s own AI &amp; ML technology.&nbsp;No matter which strategy you are opting for, Google Adword should definitely be a part of it. Thanks to the search result accuracy, PPC advertising is dominated by Google.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Relevance of ads:&nbsp;A majority of users who are not very familiar with the concept of Google Adword believe that if they increase the budget, the campaign will reach a larger audience. It&rsquo;s a thought that can&rsquo;t get more wrong. Adword focuses solely on the relevance and the overall quality of the ad, and not how much budget you have.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The relevance of the content will directly impact Google&#39;s search engine. Moreover, that&rsquo;s why the platform focuses so heavily on this aspect. The price will vary based on the keyword. There are various poor-quality ads that will bid more in comparison to the ones that are better optimized and rich in terms of content quality.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Multiple ad formats:&nbsp;The platform was launched around 2000 and it has significantly improved since then. There is a wide range of available formats that you can choose from to get the best appeal for the targeted audience.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Though the core PPC advertising has yet stuck with text, Google offers multiple features such as ad extensions and social proofing to enhance ad visually.&nbsp;These ad formats will also offer you tailored experiences for the type of product/service that you are offering. These features will drastically help in reaching a new audience.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Facebook Ads</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Between the two, as it might suggest to you by the name, Facebook Ads is the service that you will use to <strong><a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/marketing-strategy/\">advertise your business </a></strong>on social media. It&rsquo;s known to everyone that no other platform can boast of higher monthly active users than Facebook. If you have any doubt, you can research a bit and find the difference between the MAUs with their competitors. With such a huge user presence, it has become one of the most cost-effective and fruitful mediums to market.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The only similarity that you can say between Facebook Ads and Google Adwords is that you are advertising over the internet. A paid social media campaign is highly dependent on the user&rsquo;s online behavior. The Facebook algorithm will show you the ads based on the interests of the particular user.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>Facebook Ads: Key advantages</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>If you compare it with Google&#39;s Adword, it will feel like an ardent tool that is quite complex. However, there are various changes that have been made by this social media giant to offer a much more refined service.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For paid <a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/social-media-marketing/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>social media marketing</strong></a>, Facebook has now come head-to-head compared to the presence of Google in paid search marketing. Let&rsquo;s go through a few key advantages.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Huge audience with precise details:&nbsp;In this aspect, Facebook Ads is quite similar to the search engine giant. This social media mogul boasts around 1.5 billion monthly active users. This number doesn&rsquo;t include the ones that open Facebook once in a while.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The best feature that Facebook offers is the audience with precise details related to their interests and online presence. This platform knows everything about you from which school you went to where you partied last night. The algorithm tailors the relevant content for the users.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Visual appeal:&nbsp;This is a key advantage in which Facebook has an upper hand and you can say it wins this aspect by a huge margin. Adwords is a platform primarily based on text campaigns whereas Facebook Ads is focused on visual details. The ads will appear in the user&rsquo;s feed. Moreover, if it&rsquo;s rich in media, there are high chances of it getting the engagement.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Good returns:&nbsp;The number of targeting options that you will get with Facebook has some serious impact and you will get a higher return on investments. There are also various tools that you will get here offering you an easy approach to create engaging ads.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There are various factors that will play their roles in the final pricing. However, you can rest assured that it&rsquo;s highly affordable when you put the budget side by side to the ROI.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>FAQs</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Which one should I use, Facebook Ads or Adwords?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Though it depends on your business and its market presence, we would still recommend following a strategy that includes both platforms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Are Facebook Ads cheaper?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>It&rsquo;s also not a straight yes or no. Google will charge you according to the number of clicks. However, Facebook Ads is a time-bound campaign that will expire after a specific time.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>How are these two different?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The answer is quite simple. Facebook will show users the ads based on their relevance to their interests and hobbies. On the contrary, Google Adwords will show your campaign with the query that the user has asked for.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Conclusion: Which one to settle upon?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>We hope we were able to bust your myth that both of these platforms are adverse to each other. If you are still confused, all we can say is to make such a marketing strategy in which you can include both platforms. Also, ensure you extract the full return on your investment. While doing this, don&rsquo;t forget the respective requirements of each platform. No matter what you end up using, the online marketing platforms have made reaching the targeted audience much easier than once can imagine.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you ask us, for all your marketing related needs, we highly suggest that you opt for the iDotcommers. Since they own a remarkable working portfolio, all your needs will be taken charge of.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', 'When it comes to the primary difference between Google and Facebook Ads you must know the key differences between Facebook Ads and Google Adwords before everything else', 'facebook-ads-or-google-adwords', 'facebook, google, adwords', 'Mona', '2021-12-23 14:55:41', '2021-12-27 19:33:13');
INSERT INTO `blog` (`id`, `blog_title`, `blog_category`, `image1`, `image2`, `description`, `description1`, `blog_url`, `tags`, `author_name`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(42, 'What are the Best Tips to Run a Google Ad Campaign?', 'Digital Marketing', 'google-ad-campaign1.png', NULL, '<p>We have come way past the era when online marketing techniques were only opted by the ingenious brands that were trying to do something creative and new. The world has gone virtual and so did the marketing strategies. The effectiveness and the impact that online marketing offers are quite significant over the more traditional marketing strategies. Among various effective strategies for online marketing, Google Ads is one of the important ones that you must include.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To address it efficiently and extract your money&rsquo;s full worth, there are a few tips that you need to keep in mind. No matter whether you are a big or small business, there is something for you at every step.&nbsp;Before diving into the tips to extract your campaign&rsquo;s full potential, we would like to jot down a few key benefits of including Adwords in your marketing strategy.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Benefits of a Google Ad campaign<br />\r\nIf you are a business owner and have landed here, there are high chances that you are finding yourself unable to convince yourself to invest the money here. We are going to take you through a few benefits that will help you in making a decision.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Leading-edge search engine<br />\r\nThe very basic rule of selling any product online is that the customer must be able to easily locate you online. Google has an upper hand where it has transformed into a verb when it comes to searching online for anything. The search engine giant offers Google Ads to introduce yourself in the market. The platform will also offer you the tools to get into the SERPs on the top as an ad based on the keyword selection. For an e-commerce site, it can go for Shopping Ad format.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Quick results<br />\r\nThe most significant and top-of-the-line advantage that you will get with the Google Ads campaign is that it will give you some instant results. It will be much faster than the more conventional strategy, i.e. SEO. The primary reason why it&rsquo;s quicker and more agile is that it will allow business owners to focus simultaneously on multiple keywords.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>On the contrary, SEO is a very long-term engagement where if you want to get in the top SERP, it will require various articles with precise proofreading along with a wide range of backlinks.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Use Gmail inbox for more engagement<br />\r\nWhen it comes to online marketing, the strategy that is opted for by a majority of businesses is email marketing. This is where Gmail Ads can turn out to be of big help. Google has offered full Gmail ads integration with its Adwords algorithm to everyone and it has opened a new channel for finding the potential audience. It&rsquo;s also highly effective as a majority of users are using Gmail as their primary email service and the ads will appear in the Promotions and Social section.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Continuous monitoring<br />\r\nThere are no tools that can provide you the exact outcome from the traditional marketing mechanisms such as newspapers, TV, pamphlets, billboards, etc. Not only will you be unable to monitor the investment, but these strategies are also much pricier than Google Ads. The only way to know whether the ad is working is to ask the customer from where they got to know about your brand. Whereas Google Adwords will provide you all the details comprising who clicked on it, the number of generated leads and the traffic that you are getting from Adwords, and also the cost per lead.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Remind the visitors<br />\r\nThere are various visitors who scroll through each and everything on the site, these are called window shoppers. These visitors will go through all the pages but will not take any sort of action. Google Ads offers you the required tools to remind such visitors about your brand. You can use remarketing through display networks along with the RLSA network to get the job done. The latter is based on Search and the user will, therefore, need to also use keywords so that it can remind the visitors who have used the same set or particular keywords.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Tips to efficiently use Google Ads<br />\r\nSmall-scale business owners will have a wide range of options when it comes to promotion. The best part about online marketing that is essential for these small businesses is that there is no fixed amount that they need to pay to create a campaign. It is highly flexible and you will get to start with it, no matter how low your budget is.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, to get the best out of this platform, just creating a campaign and forgetting about it will not work. You will have to keep a few tips in mind so that you are able to create an appealing and creative ad on this platform. Let&rsquo;s dive in right away.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Synced landing page<br />\r\nWhen it comes to paid search campaigns, the landing page is a crucial element. An ad can be considered worth it only if it&rsquo;s able to drive the visitor to the website. The CTA button that you have created on the campaign should be in sync with that of your landing page. If it&rsquo;s not the same, the visitor will get confused and will eventually leave the page. For example, if you are adding a CTA button for &ldquo;Register Now For Free&rdquo;, the landing page should make it clearly visible that it&rsquo;s the registration page.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Use negative keywords<br />\r\nThere will be a few keywords that you must find unsuitable for your product and services that might sound similar to yours. This tool offers you to drive away all the unwanted traffic that is not your potential audience. You can understand it better with an example; let&rsquo;s say you are posting an ad about a lodging set up for students. You can add terms like &lsquo;family&rsquo;, &lsquo;premium&rsquo;, etc. to the negative keywords allowing users to not show the ad to these visitors.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A set objective<br />\r\nThe ad campaign that you are creating should come with an objective behind it. Not only with Google Ads, but you must also set goals before working with any online marketing platform. These search ads work on the PPC model and the money that you are investing should not be wasted. The goals that we are talking about here will include enhancing the conversions, getting more leads, boosting the CTR figures, etc. Once the goal is set, you are a step closer to finding your money&rsquo;s full worth.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Proper keyword research<br />\r\nGoogle Ads are significantly based on keywords and the visitors who will search for the service using these keywords will get to see the ad on top of the SERP. To get it right, you will need to invest your time in proper keyword research and to make things easier for you, there are various tools that are available online to help you with research for the appropriate keywords.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Set the budget<br />\r\nIt&rsquo;s a very crucial aspect in the world of PPC ads, no matter whether you are planning to spend $100 or $1,000, the bids should be set accordingly. For example, if you are setting the overall budget for the campaign to be around $100, the highest bet that you should place is $1. It will allow you to get 100 clicks until the budget touches 0. Same with a higher budget, if you are planning to invest $1,000 you can set the highest bid to be $50 or $100. It will get you 20 or 10 clicks, respectively.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>FAQs<br />\r\nWhat is a PPC ad?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>PPC is the abbreviated form of pay-per-click ad. What it does here is that the platform, i.e. Google Ads, for instance, will charge you based on the clicks that you are getting.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Can I create a campaign with more than one keyword?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Yes, Google Ads allows you to choose multiple keywords for a single campaign and you will get to focus on them simultaneously for quicker results.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Can I turn on/off the campaign once it&rsquo;s posted?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The ads based on the PPC model can be turned on/off without any restriction. You can resume it once you feel the need.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Conclusion<br />\r\nWe hope that the blog can be a bit helpful in shaping your thought process and you are able to make a decision. There is one thing that you must keep in mind is that you should never copy a strategy from some other business. There are high chances that it will be a complete waste of funds. Find the requirements that your business demands and then plan a strategy around it to extract your money&rsquo;s full worth.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you wish to opt for professionals or a company that will take care of your marketing and campaigns, we highly suggest you get in touch with iDotcommers. Their years of expertise and portfolio are surely going to help you.</p>', 'No matter whether you are a big or small business, here are some best tips for you to address Google Ads efficiently and run successful google ad campaign', 'best-tips-to-run-google-ad-campaign', 'Googleads, PPC, Adwords', 'Jewel', '2022-01-07 14:08:23', '2022-01-07 14:08:23'),
(43, 'Technical SEO: Complete Guide 2022', 'SEO', 'Technical SEO Complete Guide 2022.png', NULL, '<p>Of course, generating excellent content after doing thorough keyword research greatly aids in search engine optimization and offers a fantastic user experience. But what if some technical SEO problems cause your optimized page to be hidden from search engines?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We&#39;ve heard from publishers who claim that Google&#39;s search engine results page doesn&#39;t display their published web pages (SERP). Some believe that a black hat SEO strategy they employ has resulted in Google penalties.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We&#39;ve prepared a technical SEO tutorial to make things simpler for you and explain how it makes sure Google crawls and indexes your web pages.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>indexing and Crawling</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>XML sitemaps</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>duplicated materials</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Detailed information</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Hreflang</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Start with some straightforward definitions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Table of Content</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Technical SEO: What is it?</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Why is technical SEO so crucial?</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>How do websites function?</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>How a website is transferred between a server and a browser</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>HTML: What a website says</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>CSS: How a webpage looks</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>How a website functions with JavaScript</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Client-side rendering as opposed to server-side rendering</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;5. Tips for Technical SEO:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Establish an orderly site organization.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Look for problems with indexing</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Consistently structure your URLs</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Add noindex tags to pages that are redundant or thin.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Use Google Search Console to inspect URLs</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Cut down on the size of web pages by deleting third-party scripts</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Verify your sitemap in XML</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Make breadcrumb navigation available</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>For overseas websites, use hreflang</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Check for broken links on your website.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Pages with noindex tags and categories</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Boost the speed of your website</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Advice on how to annotate your pages:</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Canonicalization</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Mobile Optimization</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Image optimization:</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>SRCSET</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Lazy&nbsp;loading</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Conclusion</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>1. Technical SEO: What is it?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Technical SEO is the process of making sure your website complies with the technical standards of contemporary search engines in order to raise its organic ranks. The most crucial elements of technical SEO are website construction, rendering, indexing, and crawling.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>2. Why&nbsp;is technical SEO so crucial?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>You can have the best website and the best content, as we just discussed. However, you won&#39;t rank if your technical SEO is ineffective. At the most fundamental level, search engines must be able to locate, crawl, render, and index the pages on your website.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, that only scratches the surface. Your website&#39;s web pages must be safe, suitable for mobile devices, devoid of duplicate material, and quick to load in order for your site to be properly technically optimized.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>3. How do websites function?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>You must have a fundamental understanding of what you&#39;re optimizing before you can optimize your website for search!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The path taken by a typical website from getting a domain name to being completely rendered in a browser has been described. Perhaps you&#39;re asking why this is significant. Here are some of the causes:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Understanding how a website functions can help you speed up page loads, increase dwell time, and boost search engine rankings.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Therefore, it employs what is known as an Internet protocol (IP) address, a set of numbers (ex: 127.0.0.1). We&#39;ll need to employ a DNS to connect those machine-readable numbers to those human-readable website names.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>4. How is a website transferred between a server and a browser?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Requests are made by your browser. Your browser performs a DNS lookup request to translate our domain name to its IP address when it gets your request for a web page. The source code used to create our website is then requested from the server by the program.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The requested resources are sent by the server. The server sends the files for our website to your browser so it can put them together when it receives this request.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our website is put together by your browser. Although your browser has now gotten the necessary resources from the server, it still needs to assemble and render our website before you can see it. The browser builds a Document Object Model (DOM) as it organizes and decodes every resource on the online page.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Lastly, your browser sends requests. Only after all required code has been downloaded, parsed, and performed by the browser will a web page be visible. The browser will send a separate request to our servers if it needs any more code to display our website.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Let&#39;s now examine the elements of a website or the source code (programming languages) that creates our web pages.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Website components</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h3>HTML: What a website says</h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Every website is built on HTML, or hypertext markup language. It defines things like headings, sentences, lists, and content.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The relevancy of your document to a given query is determined by how search engines crawl HTML elements.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h3>CSS: How a webpage looks</h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Your web pages&#39; fonts, colours, and layouts are decided by CSS, or cascading style sheets. It was a game-changer when CSS was introduced because HTML was created to describe content rather than style it.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h3>How a website functions with JavaScript</h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>In the early days of the Internet, we utilized HTML to generate web pages. Then CSS came along, enabling us to design and layout web content in whatever we pleased. Websites can now have structure, appearance, and dynamic functionality, though, owing to JavaScript.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>JavaScript provided many new opportunities for developing dynamic web pages. Your browser will apply JavaScript to the static HTML that the server has returned when you access a website that has been augmented with this programming language, creating a webpage with some amount of interactivity. You probably saw JavaScript in action without even realizing it. JavaScript has the ability to produce pop-up windows and to ask for the display of external resources, such as advertisements, on your page. It&#39;s essentially the secret to using adverts to monetize your website.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h3>Client-side rendering as opposed to server-side rendering</h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Because JavaScript is not interpreted by browsers like HTML, there may be SEO problems. The distinction between client-side and server-side rendering is the cause of this problem. The client&#39;s browser is where JavaScript is primarily used. Server-side rendering, on the other hand, renders files on the server before providing them to the browser in a finished state.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As long as you don&#39;t prevent Googlebot from crawling your JavaScript files, they should be able to render and comprehend your web pages similarly to a browser, according to Google.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You can check to see if Google shares your visitors&#39; perceptions of the world. To see how Googlebot sees your page, use the &quot;URL Inspection&quot; feature in Google Search Console.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Then click Test Live URL after pasting the URL of your webpage into the search bar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After Googlebot has re-crawled your URL, click View Tested Page to check how your page is rendered.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the More Info tab, Google also displays a list of any sources they were unable to find for the URL you supplied.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Knowing how websites operate creates a strong foundation for the following section, which discusses technical adjustments to make it easier for Google to understand the pages of your website.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>5. Tips for Technical SEO</h2>\r\n\r\n<h4>1. Establish an orderly site organization.</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>How each page is arranged depends on the website&#39;s structure. You want your site to have a &quot;flat&quot; structure, which means that each page should only be a few links away from another.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A flat structure may be easily crawled by search engines. This isn&#39;t a major deal for a blog or a website for a neighborhood pizzeria. What about an eCommerce site with 100,000 product pages?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Additionally, you want your structure to be well-organized. &quot;Orphan pages&quot; are typically a result of an unorganized structure (pages without internal links pointing to them). It also makes it challenging to find and fix indexing issues.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Use Ahrefs&#39; &quot;Site Audit&quot; feature to get a bird&#39;s eye view of your website&#39;s structure. You can use Visual Site Mapper to see your pages&#39; connections more visually. You may view the architecture of your website in real-time using this free tool.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>2. Look for problems with indexing</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Finding pages on your website that are challenging for search engine spiders to explore is the first step.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Coverage analysis</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Your first port of call should be the &quot;Coverage Report&quot; in the Google Search Console. This report will inform you if Google cannot render or index the pages you want to be indexed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Screaming Frog</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The reason Screaming Frog is the most well-known crawler in the world is that it&#39;s amazing. After you&#39;ve rectified any problems in the Coverage Report, we advise performing a full crawl using Screaming Frog.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>3. Consistently structure your URLs</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>If you manage a tiny website, there&#39;s no need to overthink the format of your URLs (like a blog). You do need a sensible, consistent structure for your URLs. This truly aids visitors in locating themselves on your website.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>By classifying your pages into several categories, you can give Google more details about each page inside each category.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>4. Add no index tags to pages that are redundant or thin.</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Pages with duplicate content will be present on the majority of websites. It&#39;s alright. However, this becomes a problem when those duplicate content pages are indexed. The &quot;noindex&quot; tag should be added as a fix in this case. Search engines are told not to index the page with the noindex tag.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Verify that your noindex tag is configured properly by using Google Search Console&#39;s Inspect URL tool. Click Test Live URL after entering your URL in the text box.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The noindex tag is wrongly configured if you get the notice &quot;URL is available to Google.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The noindex tag is active if you get a notice that reads, &quot;Excluded by &quot;noindex&quot; tag.&quot; Google may need to re-crawl the pages you don&#39;t wish to be indexed for a few days or weeks.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>5. Use Google Search Console to inspect URLs</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Does your website contain any URLs that are not indexed?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You can determine what&#39;s happening by using the Inspect function of the Google Search Console. It will explain the reason a page is not being indexed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, you can observe how Google displays indexed pages. By doing so, you can confirm that Google can access and index each and every piece of content on that website.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>6. Cut down on the size of web pages by deleting third-party scripts</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Every third-party script on a page adds 34 milliseconds to its load time. However, some of these scripts are necessary (such as Google Analytics). It never hurts to take a look at the scripts on your website and see if there are any that you can get rid of.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>7. Verify your sitemap in XML.</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Even in the era of mobile-first indexing and AMP, Google still needs an XML sitemap to locate the URLs on your website. XML sitemaps are the &quot;second most significant source,&quot; according to a Google representative, for finding URLs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To confirm that your sitemap is functioning properly, visit the &quot;Sitemaps&quot; section of the Search Console.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>8. Make breadcrumb navigation available</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>The advantages of breadcrumb navigation for SEO are well established. This is due to the fact that breadcrumbs automatically provide internal links to your website&#39;s categories and subpages, strengthening the structure of your website.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Not to mention the way Google transformed URLs into breadcrumb-style navigation in the SERPs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>9. For overseas websites, use hreflang</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Does your website have distinct versions of the same page for various locales and languages? The hreflang tag can be very helpful in that situation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Hreflang tags are challenging to set properly, though. Additionally, Google&#39;s usage instructions aren&#39;t precisely clear. Use Aleyda Solis&#39; Hreflang generating tool. To create hreflang tags for numerous nations, languages, and areas, use Aleyda Solis&#39; Hreflang generator.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>10.&nbsp;Check your website for dead links.</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>If your website has a lot of dead links, it won&#39;t make or break your SEO. Google claims that broken links are &quot;not an SEO concern.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>What if, though, some of your internal links are broken? It may be more challenging for Googlebot to identify and crawl the pages on your website if there are broken internal links. Therefore, we advise performing a quarterly SEO assessment that involves fixing broken links.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Almost every SEO audit tool, such as SEMrush, Ahrefs, or Screaming Frog, may help you detect broken links.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>11. Pages with noindex tags and categories</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>If WordPress powers your site, we strongly advise not indexing category and tag pages. (Except, of course, if a lot of people visit those pages.)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>These pages typically don&#39;t offer users much in the way of value. They might also lead to problems with duplicate material. If you utilize Yoast, you can quickly noindex these pages with just one click.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>12. Boost the speed of your website</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>There are various techniques to make your website faster:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Utilize rapid hosting.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Use a fast DNS service.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>By limiting the use of plugins and scripts, you can lower the number of &quot;HTTP requests.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Use a single CSS stylesheet rather than several CSS stylesheets or inline CSS.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Your website&#39;s pages should be smaller (using a GZIP tool ).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Your HTML, CSS, and Javascript code should be free of any extra spaces, line breaks, or indentation; for help, check Google&#39;s Minify Resources page.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Further technical SEO advice&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Think of yourself as a search engine spider reading a 1000-word page on a cycling product. How can you locate the seller, the cost, the details of the goods, or the customer reviews?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Here, schema markup is relevant. By spoon-feeding search engines, you can provide them with more precise categories for the data on your page.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Schema is a system for categorizing or arranging material that helps search engines comprehend the meaning of the various parts on your web pages. There is no connection between Schema and first-page ranks, according to a study into search engine ranking parameters.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, schema adds structure to your data, which is why it is often referred to as &quot;structured data.&quot; Because you are using organized code to mark up your content, structuring your data is referred to as markup.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>JSON-LD is Google&#39;s preferred schema markup, which Bing also supports (announced in May 2016). For a comprehensive list of the tens of thousands of schema markups available, visit Schema.org, and for further information on using structured data, see Google Developers&#39; Introduction to Structured Data.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After implementing the structured data that best matches your web pages, you may use Google&#39;s Rich Test Results tool to test your markup.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Schema markup can enable unique characteristics (Rich snippets) to distinguish your pages in the SERPs while assisting search bots in comprehending the nature of your content. They are probably what you saw while you were looking at your preferred coffee makers or your ideal vehicle.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Rich snippets can show up as site link search boxes, review stars, Carousels of Top Stories, and more.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Keep in mind that getting a rich snippet isn&#39;t always assured even when you use structured data. Google will eventually offer more categories of rich snippets as schema markup expands.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Advice on how to annotate your pages:</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>On a single page, use a variety of schema markups. But you must also mark up the other products on the website if you mark up one element, like a product, and it also contains other products.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Be sure to abide by Google&#39;s quality guidelines and avoid marking up information that is hidden from visitors. Make sure the reviews are shown on the page if you utilize review-structured markup.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Google advises using structured markup on other versions of a page in addition to the canonical one.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Your page&#39;s structured markup should appropriately reflect its content.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Use just the most specialized kind of schema markup.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Canonicalization</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>You can tell search engines which pages you like by using canonicalization. It can be challenging to choose which page to index in search results when Google crawls identical material on several web pages. The rel=&quot;canonical&quot; element is useful in this situation. By indexing the chosen version of the information rather than all of its duplicates, it aids search engines.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This property instructs search engines where to go for a piece of content&#39;s original, master version. In essence, you&#39;re asking Google to index this original page rather than its duplicates. Therefore, the canonical tag can be useful if you want to republish a web page but don&#39;t want to take the chance of producing duplicate material.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Duplicate content should be avoided for a good reason. Instead of rewarding websites with copied content, Google wants to reward those that give original, worthwhile information. Google seldom ever displays multiple versions of the same material to provide users with the best experience possible. It would rather only display the canonicalized version. If there isn&#39;t a canonical tag, it displays the version they think is most likely the original.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Mobile Optimization</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Given that well over half of all web traffic nowadays comes from mobile devices, it is reasonable to assume that your website should be mobile-friendly and easy to use. In April 2015, Google updated its algorithm to give mobile-friendly pages the upper hand over those that weren&#39;t. So how can you ensure that your website is compatible with mobile devices?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Although there are three major ways to do it, Google suggests responsive web design for making your website mobile-friendly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Google Search Console&#39;s Mobile Usability report should be used. Google will let you know if one of your website&#39;s pages isn&#39;t mobile-friendly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Google will inform you if your site is not optimized. Even more, they&#39;ll go into great depth about the page&#39;s flaws for you. That will assist you in determining what needs to be corrected.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Image optimization</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>One of the main causes of slow-loading websites is the use of large graphics. There are more technical approaches to increase the speed at which photos are shown on your website for users, in addition to image compression and selecting the appropriate image format.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Let&#39;s go over some of the most crucial methods for enhancing image delivery:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. <strong>SRCSET</strong>:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You can have many versions of your image and then indicate which version should be utilized under what conditions using the srcset attribute. The img&gt; tag (found in HTML) has this code appended to it to generate distinctive images for particular devices.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Offering various and appropriate images to various device kinds is a special technique to enhance your on-page user experience while shortening your image load time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>2. Lazy&nbsp;loading</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>When visiting a webpage, you may occasionally see a blurry, low-quality version of the image or a coloured box in lieu of the image while the surrounding content loads; the image gets loaded after a few seconds in full resolution.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The full-resolution version loads after the low-resolution version have finished loading. This assists with the critical rendering route optimization as well. In order to explain the situation to users, you show a low-resolution teaser image while the remainder of your page&#39;s resources is downloading. For additional details on lazily loading your photos, see Google&#39;s Lazy Loading Guidance.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Conclusion</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Many experts think that Google will one day be able to fully understand websites thanks to the tremendous improvements in AI, particularly machine learning. Making technical SEO obsolete in the process.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The intricacy of Google seems to be rising annually, but this has just made technical SEO more crucial. Technical SEO, which includes crawl optimization, mobile technical SEO, and classic technical SEO, won&#39;t vanish, in our opinion. For the typical publisher, each of these disciplines is growing independently and becoming more complicated.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Looking out for the<a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/\"> best digital marketing agency in Navi Mumbai</a>, reach out to us in order to grow your business.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To get more insights on how SEO works, visit here <a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com\" target=\"_blank\">iDotcommers</a>.</p>', 'Technical SEO is the process of making sure your website complies with the technical standards of contemporary search engines in order to raise its organic ranks. The most crucial elements of technical SEO are website construction, rendering, indexing, and crawling.', 'technical-seo-complete-guide', 'Technical SEO, technical seo for beginners, technical seo checklist, Advanced Technical SEO', 'Ayushi', '2022-11-08 17:47:35', '2022-11-15 22:15:28');
INSERT INTO `blog` (`id`, `blog_title`, `blog_category`, `image1`, `image2`, `description`, `description1`, `blog_url`, `tags`, `author_name`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(44, 'Top 16 Digital Marketing Company in Navi Mumbai', 'Digital Marketing', 'Top 16 digital marketing companies in Navi Mumbai.png', NULL, '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">You may develop the ideal online perception of your company or brand with the aid of a digital marketing firm. We now have a wide variety of digital marketing organizations to choose from due to the proliferation of social media platforms and other digital platforms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">To provide business organizations with a fresh viewpoint on the topic of online marketing and promotions and to point them in the proper direction, it is necessary for a digital agency to be present. But one must pick an agency wisely, one that lives up to the demands of the company. Some of the characteristics you must have in a <a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com\" target=\"_blank\">digital marketing agency</a> before hiring them for your company are expertise, creativity, confidence, execution, analysis, transparency, and having a good website of their own with responsive design, clear icons, and great content, ideal for you to choose from.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Today, we&#39;ll talk about the best 16&nbsp;digital marketing companies in Navi Mumbai that can help you succeed in the cutthroat business world by understanding your needs and utilizing the world wide web.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align:justify\">1. iDotcommers Digital LLP</h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/ckfinder/userfiles/files/iDotcommers-logo.png\" style=\"height:400px; width:400px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">IDotcommers was founded by a group of web development and digital marketing experts. One of Navi Mumbai&#39;s <a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com\" target=\"_blank\">top digital marketing firms</a> is iDotcommers. As this digital sector grows in size and complexity, so does how it operates. It can be difficult to communicate the proper message to the general public. With the development of the world wide web, competition is only growing. Businesses need to stand out by emphasizing themselves in order to dominate this online. IDotcommers merely seeks to accomplish the same by assisting you in making your company visible to your audience online.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Digital marketing, SEO, SEM, SMM, Email, SMS, and Whatsapp marketing, brand development, brand loyalty, online reputation management, social media optimization SMO, Google Ads, pay-per-click advertising, search engine optimization, search engine marketing, content marketing, content writing, website development, website maintenance, user experience design, and user interface design are a few of their key services.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Website:- </strong><a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com\">Digital Marketing Company in Navi Mumbai</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align:justify\">2. Digital Yolks</h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/ckfinder/userfiles/files/Digital-yolks-logo.png\" style=\"height:129px; width:390px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The best digital marketing company in Navi Mumbai is Digital Yolks, which offers services that include developing your brand identity through digital platforms and concentrating on reaching the expanding market. They are passionate to craft your brand&rsquo;s digital journey. They have years of experience boosting brand awareness and conversions in organizations in Noida, Delhi, Gurgaon, and Faridabad. <a href=\"https://digitalyolks.com/\">VIEW MORE</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align:justify\">3.&nbsp;Anuvaa<br />\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"/ckfinder/userfiles/files/annuva%20digital%20marketing%20agency%20logo.png\" style=\"height:235px; width:214px\" /></h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Being one of the fine digital marketing agencies in Navi Mumbai, Anuvaa works to provide complete client pleasure via the provision of services with the aid of top authorities in the area. Anuvaa is a one-stop shop that can meet all of your needs for digital media and has six years of experience in the field of digital marketing. They take care of all of your demands and wants, starting with the research and ending with implementation. Once you begin working with Them, all of your burdens are immediately transferred to Them. They kept this in mind when creating their service portfolio. <a href=\"https://www.anuvaa.com/\">VIEW MORE</a><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align:justify\">4. Olio Solutions</h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/ckfinder/userfiles/files/Olio%20Solutions%20agency%20logo.png\" style=\"height:156px; width:156px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">They desired it to be distinctive. similar to their creatives and designs. They also desired that people have pleasure in uttering the word. We are a varied assortment of individuals from different backgrounds. They include engineers. Some are MBAs, while others are... artists. However, they all shared the same passion. enthusiasm for creating lovely things Being noticed is a typical objective. We&#39;re not kidding when we claim that after three years and 500+ completed projects, they&#39;re only getting started. <a href=\"https://www.oliosolutions.com/\">VIEW MORE</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align:justify\">5. Socio Mark</h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/ckfinder/userfiles/files/sociomark-squareLogo.png\" style=\"height:180px; width:180px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">They have designed a special setup to satisfy all of your needs under one roof. Here are a few stand-out qualities that set them different from rivals, whether it be technical, online assistance, or consulting. They provide SMM, email marketing, content marketing, and SEO among other things. <a href=\"https://www.sociomark.in/\">VIEW MORE</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align:justify\">6. Idigitalise</h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/ckfinder/userfiles/files/Idigitalise%20agency%20logo.png\" style=\"height:100px; width:504px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">It is an&nbsp;honorable Digital Marketing Agency from Navi Mumbai, India. Digital marketing, branding, SEO, social media marketing, e-commerce development, digital campaigning, software &amp; application development, mobile app development, and other 360 marketing solutions are our primary specialties. <a href=\"https://idigitalise.net/\">VIEW MORE</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align:justify\">7. TG Connect Media Services</h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/ckfinder/userfiles/files/tg-connect-media-services-.png\" style=\"height:200px; width:199px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">TG Connect provides a comprehensive range of digital solutions that produce high-quality, result-driven production and healthy returns on your investment by fusing the best of innovation and unconventional thinking. When you work with them, you will be collaborating with the top digital marketing agency in Mumbai&#39;s Vashi neighborhood and a group of intelligent, enthusiastic, results-driven, and certified professionals who are driven to build your brand&#39;s online presence and establish your presence across various digital channels. <a href=\"https://www.tgconnectmediaservices.com/\">VIEW MORE</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align:justify\">8. Brain Candy</h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/ckfinder/userfiles/files/braincandy.png\" style=\"height:280px; width:280px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The esteemed digital marketing agency in Navi Mumbai, Brain Candy, assists in establishing connections with the networks of prospective clients. The intended audience would be difficult to reach with conventional marketing strategies. The group members merely share and promote the merchandise.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Without investing any money, the business and its brand are effectively marketed. New goods and services can be introduced here. <a href=\"https://www.braincandy.in/\">VIEW MORE</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align:justify\">9. Matrix Bricks</h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/ckfinder/userfiles/files/Matrix%20Bricks.png\" style=\"height:225px; width:225px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Best Digital Marketing Agency in Mumbai, India: Matrix Bricks The top digital marketing firm in Mumbai, India is called Matrix Bricks, and it offers services to all different kinds of companies. Optimizing customer performance in the worldwide market is the aim of Matrix Bricks. The greatest way to achieve this is to effectively market businesses online. To do that, Matrix Bricks offers the ideal fusion of cutting-edge technology and unconventional creativity. <a href=\"https://www.matrixbricks.com/\">VIEW MORE</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align:justify\">10. Digital Marketing &amp; Branding by BinduRa</h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/ckfinder/userfiles/files/BinduRa.png\" style=\"height:225px; width:225px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Bindura Digital, one of the top digital marketing agencies in Navi Mumbai, offers incredible strategies and plans to expand a business&#39;s clientele and draw in new customers who may later turn into brand ambassadors.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">They offer a fusion of branding, digital marketing tools, and creative services that successfully build clients&#39; online brand presences.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Their cooperative professional behavior demonstrates that they have inherent qualities of transparency, clarity, and honesty. BinduRa often consults with the client to ascertain whether there are any inconsistencies and values of collaboration, examining the goals, aspirations, or client requirements that clash.<a href=\"https://binduradigital.com/\"> VIEW MORE</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align:justify\">11. BigTrunk</h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/ckfinder/userfiles/files/BT-LOGO-black.png\" style=\"height:45px; width:154px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">BigTrunk Communications Pvt Ltd, a digital marketing firm with its main office in Mumbai, was established in 2013. Their 45+ member team has numerous offices in India and has expertise in digital strategy, social media marketing, SEO, content marketing, and other areas. They are one of the top agencies in Navi Mumbai for digital marketing, offering services like digital strategy, mobile marketing, digital media planning &amp; buying, social media marketing, etc. In this fiercely competitive digital age, they have differentiated themselves as market leaders with a quick and efficient work culture. <a href=\"https://www.bigtrunk.co.in/\">VIEW MORE</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align:justify\">12. WebyAppy Digital</h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/ckfinder/userfiles/files/webyappy.png\" style=\"height:75px; width:373px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">WebyAppy Digital is aware of the significance of effective websites in luring customers and inspiring trust in them to make the correct impact.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">They put a lot of effort into giving you some of the most intriguing, appealing, and website designs possible, making this company one of the best digital marketing firms in Navi Mumbai for everything to do with websites and web development.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">They work for a variety of companies in various industries. Webyappy has the appropriate solutions for your digital difficulties, regardless of whether you are a startup, a new medium firm, or a major corporate organization.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">One of its key components&mdash;the use of digital marketing tools and the execution of strategies&mdash;is digital transformation.<a href=\"https://webyappy.com/\"> VIEW MORE</a><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align:justify\">13. Digital Hangover</h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/ckfinder/userfiles/files/digital-hangover-logo-04.png\" style=\"height:205px; width:400px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">One of the most well-liked digital marketing companies in Navi Mumbai, Digital Hangover manages all of your online projects and assists you in realizing your aspirations, goals, and objectives by continuously expanding and improving.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Their strategy is quite novel, and it&#39;s ideal that they give their customers top priority. They are quite knowledgeable about internet trends, behaviors, and how the web works.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">They provide services to help individuals, small and medium-sized businesses, and startups establish their brands through the effective use of online marketing strategies. <a href=\"https://www.digitalhangover.in/\">VIEW MORE</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align:justify\">14. Ogilvy Public Relations</h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/ckfinder/userfiles/files/Ogilvy_Logo_new_2.jpg\" style=\"height:226px; width:400px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">A full-service SEO company, IT info Digital helps clients expand their businesses online. Today&#39;s startups, small, and existing businesses are all making every effort to maintain their market presence as a result of the changing and evolving audience brought about by current technologies. Services for digital marketing increase leads and sales, distinguish your brand and keep your marketing costs to a bare minimum.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Consumers now have higher standards for brands. People have higher expectations of brands. We establish and develop at the places of intersection to give our clients the best growth choices. Ogilvy inspires organizations and people to make a difference in the world. <a href=\"https://www.ogilvyindia.com/\">VIEW MORE</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align:justify\">15. Growth Hackers Digital</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/ckfinder/userfiles/files/Growth%20Hackers%20Digital.png\" style=\"height:300px; width:300px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">People not only make great firms non-existent but also make good companies great. So, when you hire a digital firm to assist you in growth and hacking your way up, you are looking for a larger team that shares your passion and discomfort for creating something amazing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">To help us all relax, refocus, and rekindle our relationships with one another, we take excursions to lovely locales every six months. You&#39;ll notice that we know how to have a good time if you join us! A work-only schedule? Oh no. Every month (at least), games and laughter break out in our happy place, replete with pompoms and whistles. Every year, the Summer Olympics feature competitions that raise the bar on fun. <a href=\"https://growth-hackers.digital/\">VIEW MORE</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align:justify\">16. Amura</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/ckfinder/userfiles/files/Amura-logo.png\" style=\"height:225px; width:225px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Amura SEO Services is a top-tier, leading international small- and medium-sized business (SMB), large- and enterprise-level business (SMB), and digital marketing services company/agency in Mumbai, Vijayawada, Visakhapatnam, Andhra Pradesh, and Telangana from India. We are a top-tier website SEO services provider with a highly skilled team of SEO and digital marketing professionals.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Our growth-focused tactics and data-driven insights are made to extend your client&#39;s lifetime value and boost revenue over time. Our growth marketing plan describes your consumer&#39;s behavior and path to purchase using in-depth research, user segmentation, and online behavior analysis. This study aids in the marketing funnel nurturing of your clients.<a href=\"https://www.amuratech.com/\"> VIEW MORE</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\">Conclusion</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Your selection criteria for <a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com\">digital marketing agencies in Navi Mumbai</a> must be quite specific. Some agencies are great for Google Ads Marketing, while others are experts in SEO and social media.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Others were then worried about building, sustaining, and ensuring that your brand recognition and awareness remain at the top. You should be able to articulate why hiring a digital marketing agency will benefit your company. You won&#39;t ever second guess choosing a digital marketing firm for your company if it is in line with your goals.</p>', 'Today, we\'ll talk about the best 16 digital marketing companies in Navi Mumbai that can help you succeed in the cutthroat business world by understanding your needs and utilizing the world wide web', 'top-16-digital-marketing-company-in-navi-mumbai', 'digital marketing company in Navi Mumbai, digital marketing agency, Digital marketing company, Top 16 Digital Marketing Company in Navi Mumbai, idotcommers,', 'Ayushi', '2022-11-10 18:49:08', '2022-11-15 22:10:40'),
(45, 'Technical SEO vs On-page SEO', 'SEO', 'Technical SEO vs On-page SEO.png', NULL, '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Nearly every digital marketing plan heavily relies on search engine optimization or SEO. It is the method that enables websites to get high rankings in search engine results pages (SERPs), hence enhancing their online presence.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">In the past, SEO just required website owners to incorporate keywords into every page of their website to achieve a significant rating on SERPs. But year after year, the rating procedure gets more intricate and exacting. Now, the phrase &quot;SEO&quot; actually refers to a number of marketing tactics and techniques that are intertwined. On-page SEO and technical SEO are part of this intricate web of tactics.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">There are times when a marketing firm will concentrate primarily on particular SEO strategies. For instance, if a company primarily focuses on <a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/technical-seo-complete-guide/\" target=\"_blank\">technical SEO</a>, it may refer to itself as a technical SEO agency. This enables companies to concentrate on and enhance a crucial component of their SEO. You might be unsure if this is the best course of action for your company.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Does concentrating on just one aspect of SEO impact how well your website performs overall? Do some tactics have a higher priority than others? Are we not forgoing alternative SEO tactics (like on-page SEO) that can likewise aid in the accomplishment of our marketing objectives?</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">We need to comprehend the nature of these SEO tactics and their objectives in order to respond to these queries.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align:justify\">Technical SEO: What is it?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">This Technical SEO section deals with all the technical issues in the back end of your website, as implied by the name. It&#39;s where you include the appropriate HTML codes to improve your website&#39;s user-friendliness and search engine ranking.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Once you&#39;ve made the decision to optimize your website for search engines, technical SEO is the best place to start.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>What an effective technical SEO plan may do for your website is as follows:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Design a Great Site Structure</strong></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Many people believe that a decent website needs to be fully equipped with bells and whistles. However, cramming too many elements into one page may make it difficult for users and search engines to navigate your site.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Having a straightforward website architecture is therefore preferable. Make enhancing its usability and informational value your top priorities. Removing broken links will improve your chances of ranking higher, so do it now.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Particularly if you want to start accumulating links from other websites, this will help search engines identify the key pages on your website.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Additionally, your users will have no trouble finding all the information they require about you and your company. With only a quick peek at your homepage, they will be able to browse with ease. Additionally, you won&#39;t have the dreaded dead links that make visitors stop using your website.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Improve the security of websites</strong></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Your site&#39;s structure and content are merely two factors in your search engine rankings. Furthermore, it is based on how secure your website is. This is because search engines place a high value on internet security.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Secure Sockets Layer (SSL) is used by <a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/technical-seo-complete-guide/\" target=\"_blank\">technical SEO</a> to increase the security of your website. It&#39;s not that difficult to obtain this certificate. Some suppliers even provide free installation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Your ranking and credibility both increase if your website is safe.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">People are far more likely to believe you once they see &quot;HTTPS://&quot; in your URL. Removing intrusive pop-up advertisements, it also enhances the user experience.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Quick Page Loading</strong></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">A high bounce rate, or visitors that leave your site too quickly, is one of the things you want to avoid when it comes to your website. When a page takes longer than three seconds to load, people typically do this.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">By maintaining the previously described minimal structure, technical SEO speeds up your website. Additionally, it purges the codes of all unnecessary components such as extra spaces and line breaks. Additionally, it reduces the size of the images.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Not only does having a quick-loading website attract more people, but search engines also give sites that load rapidly higher rankings.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Create Original and Useful Content</strong></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Technical SEO examines your material to make sure it is unique and not already present elsewhere. Duplicate material might hurt your rating since it makes it difficult for search engines to distinguish between different sources.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Having numerous URLs for a single piece of information or print copies is a common cause of duplicate content. Your content management system (CMS) settings can be changed to prevent it from generating these extra URLs. You may also use a canonical link element to indicate the &quot;preferred&quot; version of the page.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Technical SEO checks your material for uniqueness but also assesses whether it is too thin or doesn&#39;t benefit your audience. You can either fix them by adding more information or you may delete them. Even two related bits of thin content can be combined to save time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Adapt to Mobile Devices</strong></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Since many individuals now access the internet using their smartphones and tablets, search engines pay a lot of focus to mobile SEO. This means that websites should function efficiently on handheld devices in addition to a laptop or desktop computer. Not many websites work well on mobile devices, the truth is known. Others don&#39;t correctly display all of their elements, while some take a while to load. Users may become angry and leave your website as a result.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">There shouldn&#39;t be any implication on your website that users need to launch their computers in order to read it correctly. To move to the next result on their phones, they can simply hit the &quot;Back&quot; button.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align:justify\">What is On-Page SEO?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">On-page SEO is concerned with the kind of content you post, while <a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/technical-seo-complete-guide/\" target=\"_blank\">technical SEO</a> concentrates on the website&#39;s back end. You may build a top-notch website that is widely visible and easily navigable using its guiding ideas.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">It&#39;s also important to note that optimizing your content raises the domain authority of your website. This metric gives your website a more reliable appearance. Although it isn&#39;t a factor in determining your search engine position, it enables you to track its performance in comparison to that of your rivals.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\">Use these on-page SEO strategies for your website optimization:</h3>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">1. Develop the Right Keywords</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">One of the key components of on-page SEO is the use of keywords. They alert search engines to your website so that they can rank it appropriately. Nevertheless, you cannot just do this at random.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The usage of keywords for SEO has a logical justification. There is research that supports the effectiveness of your keyword strategy. Utilize keyword research tools and keep an eye on your rivals.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">In order to minimize competition, always seek uncommon keywords. Discover the search engine terms your audience uses by researching them. Long-tail keywords are typically the best option because they frequently lead to specific content.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">2. Using Targeted Keywords in Your Content</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Once there&rsquo;s a final list of keywords, it&rsquo;s time to use them on your website. Before, websites used to &ldquo;stuff&rdquo; their pages with keywords regardless of whether the content made sense or not. Even so, a lot has changed since then in the world of SEO.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Nowadays, websites with useful content are given a lot of weight by search engines.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">They have the tools to determine whether websites are abusing the algorithms to improve their ranks. These sites are penalized, which makes it more difficult for them to rank.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Throughout your text, naturally, incorporate your keywords. To make your material visible to search engines, you should use each keyword a certain number of times across each piece of content.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">3. Boost Your Titles</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Not just the main body of your article, but also the titles should contain keywords. This makes it easier for search engines to comprehend and learn about your topic. Use the keyword at the beginning of your titles, being careful to keep the whole length under 55 characters.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">But don&#39;t forget to come up with intriguing headings to draw in your viewers. In order to make your information easier to read, headers are also beneficial. To give search engines even more information, you may also add your keywords to the headers.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">4. Set up SEO-friendly URLs</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Despite their seeming shortness, URLs can still be used for SEO purposes. They don&#39;t simply have to be made up of symbols and random integers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Search engines and users can learn more about your content&#39;s subject matter via an SEO-friendly URL. But make sure to keep them succinct and include your essential keywords.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">A strong URL might also encourage visitors to visit and stay on your page. Additionally, it could be advantageous.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">5. Complete Your Meta Descriptions</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The summary of your page that visitors view when they find you in search results pages is known as a meta description. It could be simple to skip it first, especially if you are unaware of its significance and potential value.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">However, there are a number of reasons why you should put in the effort to write a strong meta description. Like any summary, it offers readers a chance to learn more about the subject of your material. It informs them of the value of viewing your page.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Not all meta descriptions benefit search engine rankings. Even so, search engines will highlight your keywords in this section if they exactly match the ones someone entered in the search bar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">6. Freshen up your content</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Once they press the &quot;publish&quot; button, many people commit the error of forgetting about the content they have created. SEO is a dynamic field. Therefore, as soon as search engines update their algorithm, you should immediately make SEO adjustments to your website.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">By going back to your earlier work, you may also fix any mistakes you may have overlooked the first time. Additionally, it gives you the opportunity to present fresh data on the subject to keep your content current and pertinent.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">7. Add images</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Visuals are essential to websites.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">In addition to improving the aesthetics of your sites, adding photos can assist users in better understanding the content of your pages by providing context. Additionally, graphics make your material easier to read by serving as paragraph separators.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">When adding photographs to your pages, though, take care. Huge visuals can make your website load more slowly, which can lower its rating. Your photos can be resized without losing quality.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Additionally, by including your primary keyword in the alt text for each image, you can optimize them. By doing this, your page will also appear higher in the search engine results for photos.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align:justify\">Which SEO strategy is more crucial?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The greatest place to start when overhauling and optimizing your entire website is with technical SEO. Your website will already be ready to rank on search engines thanks to this. Additionally, it will establish the foundation for your on-page SEO.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">All of your other SEO efforts could be for naught if you don&#39;t do <a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/technical-seo-complete-guide/\">technical SEO</a>. If you didn&#39;t optimize the back end of your website, on-page SEO won&#39;t produce the results you need.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Nevertheless, to have a top-notch website, you still need on-site SEO. To raise your search engine rating, it combines technical SEO. After all, if you don&#39;t have worthwhile information to offer, search engines won&#39;t recommend you to users.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">If you can&#39;t accomplish both rights immediately, that&#39;s okay. On-page SEO can be set aside while you focus on technical SEO initially. Although it may appear overly hard, it might help you identify all the things you need to focus on in order to accomplish your goals.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">To get more insights on the latest SEO techniques, <a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/blog/\" target=\"_blank\">stay updated here.</a> Find out more about our content marketing stories by visiting our campaigns page. Feel like collaborating with us? Don&rsquo;t shy away from <a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/contact/\">contacting us</a>.</p>', 'Technical SEO section deals with all the technical issues in the back end of your website, as implied by the name. It\'s where you include the appropriate HTML codes to improve your website\'s user-friendliness and search engine ranking.', 'technical-seo-vs-on-page-seo', 'technical seo, on-page seo, What is a technical SEO?, Technical SEO vs On-Page SEO, technical seo factors', 'Ayushi', '2022-11-15 22:51:43', '2022-11-15 23:02:34');
INSERT INTO `blog` (`id`, `blog_title`, `blog_category`, `image1`, `image2`, `description`, `description1`, `blog_url`, `tags`, `author_name`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(46, '20 Local Marketing Strategies in 2023', 'Digital Marketing', '20 Local Marketing Strategies in 2023.png', NULL, '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">A staggering 85% of business owners rely on word-of-mouth recommendations, demonstrating how important it is to target local clients. The strategies you&#39;ll use for local marketing are a little different from those you&#39;ll use for broad marketing because you&#39;ll be putting more effort into locating, contacting, involving, and appealing to locals. We have 20 tried-and-true local marketing concepts and strategies for small companies. Let&#39;s first clarify what we mean by &quot;local marketing&quot; in detail.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align:justify\">How does local marketing work?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Local marketing is described as marketing techniques and methods that aim to attract clients locally, often within a 50-mile radius of a business. It might include conventional physical marketing or online marketing that is regionally oriented. It is also known as neighbourhood marketing or location-based marketing. Nowadays, local marketing frequently combines the two methods.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Local search marketing, commonly referred to as local SEO, is a subset of local area marketing. Local search marketing relates especially to strategies to make sure a business is found by potential local customers in search results, location pages, and online maps.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Local businesses may receive all of their patrons from within a short distance. The term &quot;main street business&quot; (also known as &quot;high street business&quot; in certain other countries) may be familiar to you. This is a reference to how tiny businesses rely heavily on foot traffic and visibility on major thoroughfares. So, while small businesses can succeed online, it requires a specific geographic emphasis. Otherwise, you risk wasting time and money trying to draw nationwide online traffic who will never set foot in your store or make a purchase.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align:justify\">20 Local Marketing Techniques</h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Here are 20 of the most effective local marketing strategies to increase exposure, generate more leads, and draw in and retain local clients:</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>1. Participate in Community Life</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Although it may seem obvious, local marketing depends heavily on community involvement. Engagement in the community is also very affordable. This tactic is demonstrated, for instance, by taking part in local festivals, competitions, and seasonal events. Alternatively, your company may support neighbourhood sporting activities or high school musical and dramatic productions. Another illustration is local small company owners that donate their time to charities and causes. You&#39;ll network with a lot of people, develop goodwill through doing good, and increase brand recognition.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>2. Make the most of your local business listings.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">According to one study, more than half of small businesses still haven&#39;t claimed their Google My Business listing. They are passing on a valuable local marketing opportunity. Your company name, phone number, address, directions, operating hours, and a link to your website can all be found on your profile. Smart small businesses also include content, such as alluring images. It offers free visibility in the most effective search engine on the planet.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">You must first actively manage your Google My Business listing after claiming it. Additionally, this adds your position to Google Maps. Bing Places and yellow page directories are only two additional online locations where you can list yourself. Start with the top three:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Apple Maps</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Google My Business</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Bing Places</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>3. Emphasize local SEO</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Some of the most technologically sophisticated local marketing initiatives use the web to drive customers to your store or other physical site. You may order takeout or shop online using the internet. Customers are using the internet and mobile devices to search for products and services in your neighbourhood. People should have no trouble finding your company.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Although Google My Business is a great place to start, local search engine optimization (SEO) encompasses much more than that. Making the pages of your website more noticeable in search results is another step in the local search engine optimization process. Aim for the top spots on search engine results pages for a term or phrase that clients use to find businesses like yours. Local newspaper websites, blogs, and even social media sites like Twitter may link to your website and direct readers there if you generate great content.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Engage a local search professional if you don&#39;t know how to increase your visibility on search engines or don&#39;t have the time. A specialty area is local search. When interviewing SEO consultants and suppliers, make sure to probe about their success in local search and how it has benefited small local businesses.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>4. Contact local businesses</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Expanding your network through partnerships with companies in related but unrelated industries is a terrific local marketing tactic. To meet people and network with other businesspeople in your area, join the chamber of commerce or similar regional business organisation. Your goods or services can be required by other small businesses in your town or city. For instance, if you own a local web design business, you might find that you have new clients who require website assistance. Or, if you&#39;re opening a small bakery, perhaps nearby caf&eacute;s or eateries would be interested in carrying your delectable treats.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Additionally, you can collaborate on referrals to get more clients than you could on your own. Maybe you could pool your marketing resources with those of other small local firms for media ad purchases. Or organize community gatherings with food provided by nearby bakeries, restaurants, and wineries, where each participant advertises the event.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>5. Establish a Loyalty Program</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Customers enjoy feeling appreciated! A customer loyalty program offers rewards to those who make purchases or take other actions. It has long been standard to print out customer loyalty cards and distribute them to customers. After that, use a hole punch with a recognizable shape to indicate the number of purchases. The eleventh coffee, for instance, is free if a customer buys 10 from your caf&eacute;. As an alternative, you may provide free trims after a certain number of appointments.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">For your retail marketing, you can also go high-tech and implement a mobile loyalty program. Through the app, users receive prizes for their behavior.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>6. Boost Client Referrals</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Why not entice your consumers to help you out with word-of-mouth marketing by offering them an alluring referral programme? Starting is easy. All you have to do is provide the original consumer and the person they suggest with an alluring freebie or exclusive discount. Because they are a force multiplier, referral programs can prove to be a very successful local marketing strategy. It enlists people to assist you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>7. Engage your employees as your emissaries</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">By including them in your referral programme, you may turn your staff into the focal point of your neighborhood marketing. As a reward for bringing in new customers, provide non-sales staff members with a bonus.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">You can get employees to participate in your content marketing initiatives by creating a lighthearted behind-the-scenes video of a typical workday to upload to the corporate YouTube account or embed in blog posts. To find out if employees are open to appearing in TV commercials, ask them.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>8. Display Marketing Collateral&nbsp;in Public</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Use public spaces to spread marketing messages to members of your neighborhood. Reaching out to other companies and groups in the city or town where you operate might be helpful in this situation as well. Can you post fliers or business cards on a community bulletin board or place them on the door of nearby eateries, coffee shops, and supermarkets? This works best if your company is a good fit for the other business. If you own a graphic design or photography studio, for instance, you might be able to post marketing materials in a neighboring gallery or non-profit arts organization. Affirmative consent must be secured.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>9. Engage local audiences using social media.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Social media marketing can improve local businesses&#39; visibility if done properly. The trick is to concentrate on your local market. Thanks to its hundreds of millions of active monthly users, Instagram provides a variety of alternatives for brand recognition.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">In your social media profiles, mention your location. To increase engagement from users in your area, be sure to tag your location in postings. Focus on the social media platform that appeals to your target market.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">LinkedIn, for instance, draws business users, which may be advantageous if you sell to other firms. Additionally, working with influencers on influencer marketing could expand your audience on social media.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>10. Use Targeting Tools When Marketing Online</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Facebook and other social media platforms provide a variety of options for locating local customers. You can &quot;boost&quot; postings using social media advertising capabilities, establishing settings to target buyers within a specific radius. Employ Facebook&#39;s &quot;Create the Location&quot; function as well. When creating a new post, click &quot;Check In&quot; and add location-related information. Additionally, you can use location hashtags and stickers in Instagram posts and stories. You can also target your local market using Google Ads. Start a Google Ads campaign so that advertisements display on content websites all over the internet and in search engines. To encourage previous consumers to come back, use a targeted local marketing landing page and remarketing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>11. Share a Story</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Describe the background of your business or your own life as an entrepreneur. By telling a tale, you may pique people&#39;s curiosity and help them remember your company. Prospects are more likely to make a purchase from you if you can make them relate to your company through storytelling.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">A compelling origin narrative for your company strengthens the bonds with current clients, preventing them from defecting to the glitzy new chain down the street.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Share your story in your TV ads, online videos, blog posts, and your About Us website. Another illustration is a neighborhood family restaurant that displays framed, hand-signed pictures of notable customers throughout its existence. To recall for founder stories:</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">If you are a native of the area, mention it. Discuss your local upbringing, your favorite aspects of the community, and your feelings for the locals.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Entrepreneurs who recently relocated to a location can discuss their reasons for doing so.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>12. Organize an Event</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">At least two strategies can be used to promote local businesses at community events. The first is to put on the event by yourself. Invite residents of the neighborhood to a party or product launch event to check it out. Offer free entertainment, libations, and food. Joining together with other companies to organize a larger event that promotes all of your goods or services is another local marketing strategy. For instance, perhaps local eateries, bakeries, and wineries could organize a neighborhood fair to promote local fare. It&#39;s excellent marketing for promoting local businesses.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>13. Obtain testimonials and reviews</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Local clients want to work with a company they believe they can trust, which you may show through favorable testimonials and feedback. Never pay for reviews; it will just lead to difficulties. When explicitly requesting customer feedback, exercise caution. Communities opposed to this include Yelp and others. Instead, you may suggest that customers generally tell others what they think of your products or services. This encourages users to post reviews without explicitly requesting them on a certain website. Learn the guidelines so you don&#39;t cross the line.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">To find out what people are saying about your company, keep an eye on social media and review websites. Ask customers who have experienced subpar service how you can make it right by speaking with them.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">People will appreciate your effort and notice it. Additionally, you might be able to salvage a bad review if your client feels that you are genuinely interested in helping them.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>14. Distribute individualized email campaigns</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">One of the easiest and most affordable local marketing strategies may turn out to email. It entices social media followers to visit your door and prompts returning customers to visit your shop. Targeted personalization boosts consumer engagement, according to 75% of marketers. Therefore, be sure to localize campaigns as part of your local marketing efforts. Start a local email list by asking everyone coming to your store for their email address, and request permission to send them communications. Instead of a general email newsletter, send discounts designed to lure people into your store to buy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>15. Launch a Coupon Campaign</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Choose a site like Groupon or a local coupon paper mailer like ValPak for local marketing with coupons. Coupons bring in a host of new customers and help with brand awareness. But be careful! The customers these campaigns bring in are sometimes just looking for a bargain and won&rsquo;t ever become regulars. Set up offers that encourage repeat buying or bulk buying, if you can.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>16. Provide Free Advice or Consultation</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">This is a fantastic method to show off your industry knowledge and pique the curiosity of possible new clients. They might visit today to receive free advice, but they&#39;ll probably return later to make a purchase. A free consultation or piece of advice, like that found on a blog or YouTube channel, gives potential customers a free preview of your offering. For instance, if you run an accounting firm, see if the library can host a free tax workshop one evening.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>17. Submit a News Article</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The local newspaper is a fantastic resource for local marketing. Of course, you can spend money on advertising and contact editors with press releases. However, be more original. Offering oneself as a source and subject matter expert to neighbourhood journalists by phone call or email. If you run a local gym or practice physical therapy, for instance, you would be a fantastic candidate to speak with about appropriate forms of exercise.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Keep up with significant trends in your industry so you can suggest stories to the neighbourhood press. Give them a local perspective to help them localize huge stories. For instance, the proprietor of a nearby garden center could be a reliable source for information on a drought or an invading pest. For reporters on deadline who require a prompt response within a few hours, make sure to include your phone number.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Alternatively, register with Help a Reporter Out (HARO)&nbsp;to serve as a source for reporters. To begin, visit the HARO source. Another area where you can mention yourself as a source is Qwoted.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>18. Gain the favour of local bloggers and online journalists</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Local news websites and blogs can be found in every municipality. Make contact with the authors of these websites. Why? First off, the articles they write about your company may encourage visitors to your website or store. Readers in the area will see a mention of your company. Additionally, having a presence on regional blogs and websites benefits your local SEO. Recall that local websites and blogs are frequently indexed by search engines. By appearing on regional websites and blogs, you make sure that your company will appear in additional online searches with a pertinent local link.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>19. Participate in Local TV</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">TV appearances for local marketing may be simpler than you think. The key? Offer your knowledge. Offer to participate in a news piece explaining the most recent changes to the tax code if you are the owner of a nearby accounting business. Offer to demonstrate a special recipe on a local cooking segment if you own a restaurant. Present the plan to your local station as a means for their viewers to gain from it. Don&#39;t use the pitch to advertise your company.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Local media may, however, be more accommodating to businesses that already run advertisements.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Consider purchasing local airtime or internet advertising space, depending on your marketing budget, to get on the station&#39;s radar. You&#39;ll at the very least benefit from the advertising.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>20. Collaborate with Other Businesses</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Try forming a partnership or a collaborative local marketing plan with other companies. In order to increase sales, this goes beyond passing along informal recommendations and entails forging stronger, continuing ties with other nearby companies. When local farmers and other food producers get together to establish a farmer&#39;s market, they accomplish this. You may invite a nail technician to share your space if you own a hair salon to increase the number of customers both establishments attract. Alternatively, local healthcare professionals including chiropractors, nutritionists, occupational therapists, and physical therapists may work together under one roof, increasing referral chances (subject to professional and ethical rules, of course).</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Start now</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Local company marketing is a crucial component of marketing as a whole. But resist feeling intimidated and refrain from over-analyzing. It is preferable to experiment and test fresh local marketing strategies as opposed to waiting for the ideal approach. Get moving and do something.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">To get more insights on local marketing and marketing ideas for small businesses, <strong><a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/\">stay updated.</a></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Looking out for the<a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com\" target=\"_blank\"> <strong>best digital marketing agency in Navi Mumbai</strong></a>, reach out to us in order to grow your business.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', 'Local marketing is described as marketing techniques and methods that aim to attract clients locally, often within a 50-mile radius of a business. It might include conventional physical marketing or online marketing that is regionally oriented.', '20-local-marketing-strategies-in-2023', '20 Local Marketing Strategies. local marketing strategies, Local Marketing, 2023, Ultimate Guide to Local Marketing,', 'Ayushi', '2022-11-15 23:28:47', '2022-11-15 23:35:04'),
(47, 'Taxonomy SEO : Ultimate Guide To Optimize Your Categories And Tags', 'SEO', 'Taxonomy SEO Ultimate Guide To Optimize Your Categories And Tags.png', NULL, '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">We frequently come across websites with entirely mismanaged category and tag structures. Overusing tags and categories can have negative effects on even major news websites. A taxonomy system includes things like tags and categories. An effective taxonomy system can improve the <a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/technical-seo-complete-guide/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>SEO</strong></a> of your website when applied properly. The inverse is also true: if utilized improperly, it will cause damage. The importance of those pages and how to use them are covered in detail in this article. Category archives will serve as our main example. Read up on taxonomy SEO here!</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Landing pages are archives by category and tags</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">We organize information on our website using category and tag archives, and SEO relies heavily on them. Despite the fact that WordPress employs both of these taxonomies to classify information together, their use calls for different approaches. In contrast to tags, which let you classify information by topic, categories help you give your pages a structure. But you should be cautious when using tags, and you shouldn&#39;t just keep adding new ones to every page you make. Learn more about using tags correctly or the distinctions between tags and categories by reading up on these topics.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The importance of categories and tags might sometimes outweigh that of your individual pages and posts, especially for eCommerce sites. Consider that your internet shop sells shoes. Sneakers, loafers, and other shoe categories could exist on your website. You should undoubtedly attempt to rank for terms like &quot;sneakers&quot; or &quot;loafers&quot; rather than only for the individual pairs of shoes you offer. Naturally, you may sell a pair of shoes that is particularly popular and for which you want to be found, but most people search for more general phrases, so you want to make sure that they can locate you. If so, those category archives, which serve as landing pages, need to appear as the first result in the search engines. Therefore, they ought to offer the best user experience possible.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">This is true to a greater extent the more likely it is for your individual pages to expire. Your categories are particularly crucial if your website doubles as an online store with changing merchandise. Your categories are especially crucial if your website is a job listing site where jobs expire. Otherwise, you&#39;ll be optimizing sites that will be obsolete in a few weeks or months.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Individual pages are unable to compete due to taxonomy SEO</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The likelihood of your individual pages expiring increases the likelihood that this is true. If your website doubles as an online store with constantly-changing inventory, your categories are very important. If your website is a job listing site with expiring jobs, the categories you use are very important. Aside from that, you&#39;ll be optimizing websites that will be out of date in a few weeks or months. Consider how much text you include on your product pages and whether doing so is still in the best interests of your customers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">No matter what kind of website you have, this is true. When you optimize this page, your tag or category for that topic may rank #1 in the search results if your site is a blog and you produce multiple posts on a particular subject. Don&#39;t overoptimize your individual product pages; instead, start with that one.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Archives for categories and breadcrumbs</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">In this kind of setup, breadcrumbs are crucial. Every item should have a link back to the closest category. This not only demonstrates to Google the layout of your website but also reinforces the authority of the category page on the main subject.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">If the category&#39;s subject enhances the value of the product or post, having the URL structure mirror the category may be helpful. But be careful: if your site already exists, don&#39;t change the URL structure. The advantages of modifying the structure outweigh the &quot;cost&quot; of redirecting all those URLs. It would be much better to simply use the breadcrumbs feature that our Yoast SEO plugin provides.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\">How to design outstanding taxonomy pages?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Describe the category</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Having some code snippets to examine and use as examples can be useful. In-depth and filled with useful code samples, our tutorial on WordPress archive pages is available here.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Despite being extremely valuable, taxonomy archives frequently go unappreciated. Although adding information to the page can be useful, you want the attention to be on the goods or items that are being showcased there. Nevertheless, you ought to be selective about the material you include. Prior to this, it was advised to place the remaining information at the bottom of the page and just add a little amount of introductory material to the top. However, it is now obvious that doing so will just confuse search engines and lower your page&#39;s results.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\">What sort of content should you include on your taxonomy page?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Consider truly delving into the queries that consumers have regarding your products when it comes to your category pages. Then use the answers to those queries to produce content that helps your category pages. Content that explains why customers are in the optimal location to buy these products and dispels any lingering questions about the goods or their application. Your sales will increase as a result of this user-centered approach, and search engines will understand the purpose of these sites. which is beneficial to your rankings.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Being strategic with your content addition is important when discussing tag pages. A good rule of thumb is to constantly keep the website visitor in mind. What would they want to read here, and how can your page be tailored to meet their needs? Making ensuring a person doesn&#39;t bounce when they arrive at one of your taxonomy pages depends greatly on having the appropriate material there. In addition to serving as a centre, a strong archive page should entice users to explore more of your website rather than less of it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Tag and category duplication</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Duplicate tags and categories on websites are a related problem that we frequently see. You shouldn&#39;t have a tag for &quot;bathing suits&quot; when you have a category for them. How will Google determine which one to rank first if you do?</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The same rule applies to singular and plural forms; an article shouldn&#39;t fall within the &quot;shirt&quot; and &quot;shirts&quot; categories. The tags &quot;WordPress plugin&quot; and &quot;WordPress plugins&quot; shouldn&#39;t be used on a post. There shouldn&#39;t be one of those. For all of your category and tag terms, choose single or plural and stick with it.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\">Tools with which Taxonomy SEO can be implemented</h3>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">1. The Grid</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">We&#39;re really excited about the possibilities offered by The Grid plugin, which is included with the X/Pro Theme as mentioned below. It encourages us to have a totally fresh perspective on taxonomy SEO.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">We may apply a range of advanced filters to The Grid to collect any kind of content. Here is an easy illustration from a Product Page on our website: Content Plan for Bathroom Renovation. The Grid was used to fetch these Related Products with a lovely layout once we developed a Product Category for Home Improvement. The only thing that could be done to make this better is to remove &quot;Bathroom Remodel&quot; from these Related Products as that is the Product Page we&#39;re looking at.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">2. X/Pro Theme Framework</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">You may get most of the way there by utilizing Themeco&#39;s X and Pro Themes. The Meta title, Meta description, page title, and page subtitle can all be changed for each taxonomy page. The Description, which is distinct from the Meta Description, is not displayed by default, thus it could need some specific coding to render and appear correctly. An illustration of how X/Pro offers a nearly comprehensive solution to taxonomy SEO is our tag on &quot;community&quot;. What&#39;s lacking is a 200-word description that appears above the posts with the keyword &quot;community&quot; and below the page title and subtitle.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">For further ideas on how to use X/Pro as a workaround, including constructing custom pages with widgets that bring in content based on Category/Tag, see the comments section below.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">3. Thesis Theme Framework</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Some themes and theme frameworks, like Thesis by DIY Themes, come with built-in Category and Tag optimization. The introductory fields are referred to in the Thesis as &quot;Archive Title&quot; and &quot;Archive Content&quot; correspondingly. The thesis also excels at another task: it makes it simple to add rich text, photos, and other elements by turning on HTML in these fields (which is not enabled by default). Nevertheless, the Thesis does not seem to be updated or maintained in any way, thus we advise against using it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">4. Plugin to allow HTML in category descriptions</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">You might need to allow HTML if you can set up the introductory fields but they won&#39;t format properly. At least for Categories, there is a plugin that solves this nicely.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Try out the WordPress repository&#39;s Allow HTML in Category Descriptions plugin by downloading it. The plugin hasn&#39;t been updated in a while, so keep that in mind. If we locate a plugin that supports this feature, we&#39;ll update this article.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">5. WordPress SEO Plugin by Yoast</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">If you use anything for search engine optimization, it&#39;s very possible that you&#39;re utilizing the Yoast WordPress SEO plugin, which has thirty billion downloads and instals on six million planets throughout the Milky Way. This simply takes you a little step toward effectively applying taxonomy SEO.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Yoast WordPress SEO provides you with the following very crucial fields when updating a Category or Tag:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">SEO Heading (or Meta Title)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Description for SEO (or Meta Description)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Canonical (for setting the correct URL for indexing)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Noindex This Class (changed to index when properly optimized)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Embedding in Sitemap (should be set to Always Include when properly optimized)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The introductory title and content, which are so important for producing a high-quality informational page, are not provided by this plugin. As a result, we are not quite where we want to be.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">6. Plugin for Showing Archive Descriptions</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The Show Archive Descriptions plugin had a lot of potentials, but it was still in the very early stages of development. In fact, it hasn&#39;t been updated since 2008 as of 2022! However, it demonstrates the capabilities we need.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The Sidebar widget has to be eliminated, the Category and Tag title setup need to be separated out, and the CSS needs to be pared down but changeable. Having said that, one piece of the puzzle we&#39;re trying to solve is having the Description appear on Archive sites.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;<br />\r\nDo you need help with optimizing the layout of your website? Connect with us <strong><a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com\" target=\"_blank\">iDotcommers Digital Marketing Company</a>. </strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">To get more insights on the latest SEO techniques, <strong><a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/\">stay updated here.</a></strong> Find out more about our content marketing stories by visiting our campaigns page. Feel like collaborating with us? Don&rsquo;t shy away from <strong><a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/\">contacting us</a></strong> at any of our branches!</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>', 'A taxonomy system includes things like tags and categories. An effective taxonomy system can improve the SEO of your website when applied properly.', 'taxonomy-seo-ultimate-guide-to-optimize-your-categories-and-tags', 'taxonomy seo, What is a taxonomy?, Does taxonomy affect SEO?, keyword taxonomy, website taxonomy,', 'Ayushi', '2022-11-16 21:04:29', '2022-11-16 22:05:11');
INSERT INTO `blog` (`id`, `blog_title`, `blog_category`, `image1`, `image2`, `description`, `description1`, `blog_url`, `tags`, `author_name`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(48, 'Ecommerce SEO Guide: That Actually Work in 2023', 'SEO', 'Ecommerce SEO Guide That Actually Work in 2023.png', NULL, '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">You have started selling online and are figuring out how to expand your e-commerce business; it&rsquo;s pertinent to say that <a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/technical-seo-vs-on-page-seo/\" target=\"_blank\">on-page SEO</a> is the primary step. Your product is flawless, it has a clear business model, and it is selling. However, the volume of visits to your e-commerce website has begun to level out without an increase in organic traffic. Increasing your e-commerce traffic will increase clicks that turn into conversions and product purchases. In order to increase sales, our all-inclusive guide on <strong>e-commerce SEO</strong> will help to promote organic clicks to your product website.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\">1. Knowing the fundamentals of e-commerce</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">A website for purchasing and selling products online is known as e-commerce. As new technologies advance, e-commerce enterprises are growing quickly. You probably know that increasing revenue and visitors to your website is your main objective. Simply put, you don&#39;t yet know how to increase your sales precisely. A ticket to boosting your e-commerce sales and raising profits is SEO tools and practices. Your sales will increase if you have a detailed plan for e-commerce SEO.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\">2. Concentrate on the target consumer.</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Consider your customer as if they were virtually entering your store when you develop the framework for your e-commerce website. Start imagining what your clients are thinking while you compose your website copy and product descriptions with your virtual customer in mind. A sale will be facilitated if you develop your e-commerce platform with an emphasis on the feelings behind why your buyer needs your product.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">SEO fundamentals: Recognize your clients&#39; issues and use your services and goods to address them.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Your e-commerce platform will function more easily as you visualize your ideal consumer, giving you more control over the sales and product pitches you make to them.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">You can relate to the thoughts, desires, and issues of the people visiting your e-commerce site if you can visualize who they are. Understanding their requirements and emotions will help you make a sale more effectively. Your customer will spend more time on your site since they will feel a connection between it and your products. Search engine sites track traffic duration and will give you a higher rating on searches if your customers spend more time on your e-commerce platform looking for your products.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\">3. Use keyword phrases</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Knowing how to create SEO keywords will help your e-commerce website receive more traffic. Utilize pertinent terms with high search volume and keyword tools.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Using SEO keyword tools will make it simpler to find keywords to use in your content. Investing in keywords might be costly. You can check into the keywords needed to increase traffic to your website if you have the time and effort. Here are a few totally free tools to help you find keywords.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Google Keyword Planner</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Keyword Generator</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">AnswerThePublic</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">These are the fundamental word-generation tools. There are many high-quality SEO tools available for purchase if you require more help.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\">4. Examine the products of your competitors.</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Modern technology allows new enterprises to research the market of their biggest rivals. It will benefit your company if you take the time to browse your competitors&#39; pages and observe the strategies they employ to boost sales.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Observe the following while examining the website of the rival:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Does each product on their website naturally lead to another?</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">recognizing how people are being sold on their items. How are they describing their products in their writing?</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">What kinds of pictures are they including on their e-commerce platform?</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">These are only basic questions to consider while you evaluate their website. You can determine what features you need to add to your platform by researching the market of your competitors.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\">5. Make use of your meta headers.</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Search engines can better grasp your webpage&#39;s content with the aid of meta headers, which also summarise your subject. Using your meta header to summarise the content of your website in 50&ndash;60 characters is an additional SEO opportunity to include targeted keywords. Use target keywords that can be searched for in your titles.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">They are more likely to click on your website if you provide useful information and help your customers use meta headers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\">6. Use ALT-text and include images.</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Create a visually appealing website for your audience. Start including images of your products&#39; potential uses if your e-commerce site sells goods. Customers can better comprehend your product by adding illustrations of how you utilize it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Alt-text nicely compliments your images. Use the alt-text SEO tool to provide your photographs with brief, meaningful captions. It is a piece of technology that provides descriptions of images to visually impaired people. A larger audience can be attracted by making your website simple to use for everyone. Additionally, search engines will reward your platform by elevating its position on search results pages.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Your product&#39;s objective should be measurable for everyone, and you will be helped by providing a variety of tools to assist everyone.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\">7. Speed up the loading of your website</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Keep your website&#39;s rate low. If it takes too long for your website to load, potential clients will leave because of the slow, lagging rates.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">How to shorten delay periods:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Optimize pictures by reducing file sizes</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Reduce HTTP request volume</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Cut back on style sheets</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\">8. Fostering connections with pertinent content</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Gaining humanizing connections with other creators and companies increases consumer confidence in your goods. Creating connections will lead to additional social media mentions or links to the content of your website. Customers will have more faith in your product as a result of the increased mentions your eCommerce site obtains. Creating a genuine connection with your audience can increase your confidence in your offering and raise the click-to-sale conversion rate.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Developing high-quality material for backlinks High-quality backlinks assist in providing more details about the goods and services offered by your company. It takes effort and skill to rank on a search engine with a full page of products.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">By creating educational content for your items, you can encourage other websites to link to them by mentioning them. Longer, more worthwhile, and more insightful content encourages readers to learn more beneficial information. In order to increase traffic and authority from other websites, consider how to integrate high-quality informational content into your e-commerce page.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\">9. Your website&#39;s flow should be organized.</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Check that the information about your services and items on the front of your e-commerce page is accurate. Don&#39;t mislead prospective customers about the quality of your services. On your product page, use your target keyword.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">As a general guideline, your website&#39;s merchandise should always be three clicks or less from your main page. The idea is to make it simpler for customers to access your home page. The user experience on the website will be improved and made simpler.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Understanding the foundations of website architecture will help your platform have a natural flow.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\">10. Examine your online store.</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Consider yourself a customer visiting your website. Start by examining how your website is structured. Are the buttons leading customers in the right direction? Is the website&#39;s aesthetic appealing?</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The objective is to increase e-commerce site traffic so that more people visit your online store.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align:justify\">SOME IDEAL TOOLS FOR E-COMMERCE SEO</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\">1. ScreamingFrog</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Finding issues with your website, such as broken links, missing meta descriptions, and duplicate content is really easy using ScreamingFrog. Create redirects or add missing information when you find those issues to prevent being punished by search engines. Although the free version has many helpful features, you may want to upgrade to the premium version if you have more than 500 URL extensions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\">2. MOZ</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The best tool for tracking and locating keywords, identifying link-building opportunities, and examining competitor page data is MOZ. You can choose how much strength you need to power your e-commerce SEO campaign because there are free and paid versions available.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\">3. Ubersuggest</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">This tool is quite helpful for determining the ideal keywords to target for your e-commerce site and for identifying related keywords to raise your rankings. Just enter a word or phrase that describes your product. The application will scrape numerous websites to get data on relevant keywords, CPC, search volume, and other factors.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\">4. Ahrefs</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">For eCommerce SEO strategy optimization and tracking, use Ahrefs. It&#39;s excellent for locating backlinks to both your website and the websites of your rivals. If someone has linked to your competition, you might be able to gain their trust by emailing them and asking them to link to your website. Offer to link to their website and then recommend one of your excellent posts that their audience might find interesting.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\">E-commerce SEO Stats</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;More than 43.0% of all e-commerce traffic originates from Google&#39;s organic traffic, according to Audit My SEO&#39;s guide to e-commerce SEO.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">According to Google, at least 51% of internet users have learned about a new product or company online. Most consumers use the internet to research products and services.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Most search engines use location to provide consumers with results.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">According to Google statistics, conversion rates are projected to rise for keywords associated with &quot;Near Me&quot; search queries.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">According to Ahrefs, 25% of the pages with the highest rankings lack meta descriptions.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">A search engine is where at least 68 percent of all online searches begin. Search engines are crucial to the development of any e-commerce business.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Only 48% of people use voice search to access general information on the internet, according to Search Engine Land research.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">67.60% of Google clicks come from the top 5 organic results.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">The CTR for ranking first on Google is 34.36%.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Search engines are where 46% of individuals begin their internet purchasing.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">More than 56% of shoppers start their shopping journey on Amazon.com.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Start by carefully reviewing your site with the help of a heatmap, scroll map, and confetti reports. Watch how visitors interact with your website to improve each page&#39;s conversion potential. You can consistently create traffic and increase the conversion rate of that traffic as long as you&#39;ve also optimized for SEO.<br />\r\n	&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Summary</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Your ecommerce goods and services are of the highest caliber. Occasionally consumers need more than a perfect product to be sold. Customers are seeking for reputable businesses to produce informative information that might assist in solving their difficulties.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Increasing consumer views of your product page are the ultimate objective. Our comprehensive e-commerce SEO tutorial explains how to create an online business that attracts customers naturally. Your online store will benefit from knowing how to interact with search engines like Google by getting more clicks and converts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Find out more about our content marketing stories by visiting <a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/\">our campaigns page.</a>&nbsp;Feel like collaborating with us? Don&rsquo;t shy away from <a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/\">contacting us</a> at any of our branches!</p>', 'In order to increase sales, our all-inclusive guide on e-commerce SEO will help to promote organic clicks to your product website.', 'ecommerce-seo-guide', 'ecommerce seo, ecommerce seo guide, ecommerce seo checklist, e-commerce seo services, ecommerce seo tools, ecommerce seo company in navi mumbai', 'Ayushi', '2022-11-16 23:35:06', '2022-11-16 23:36:45');
INSERT INTO `blog` (`id`, `blog_title`, `blog_category`, `image1`, `image2`, `description`, `description1`, `blog_url`, `tags`, `author_name`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(49, 'Google Tag Manager : Step By Step Guide', 'Google Tag Manager', 'Google Tag Manager  Step By Step Guide.png', NULL, '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Any webmaster or site owner should have access to <strong>Google Tag Manager</strong>. In order to manage the tags on any website, the system is essential. For those of us who aren&#39;t professional coders, it makes tag management quick, effective, and simpler to understand.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Any website&#39;s pages can have tags inserted as short pieces of code. They do a variety of various tasks. The JavaScript code tag, which is essential to the operation of Google Analytics, serves as a prime example.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The information needed by Analytics to produce its many reports and insights is collected by that tag. Other tags have the ability to gather and transmit various pieces of data to platforms like Google Ads and many others.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">In order to do website analytics, your site&#39;s tags must be managed effectively. Because of this, it is crucial for enhancing the functionality of the website. You should continue reading to find out how much easier Tag Manager makes it to create and use all the tags your site requires.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/ckfinder/userfiles/files/gtm-id-in-the-google-tag-manager-dashboard.png\" style=\"height:306px; width:500px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Image Reference :-&nbsp;<a href=\"https://bit.ly/3V6AJ7u\">https://bit.ly/3V6AJ7u</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Google Tag Management System</strong> is how Google refers to their Tag Manager tool (TMS). It serves the same purpose for a website&#39;s tags that a content management system (CMS) serves for the latter&#39;s content. The service offers an interface via which you can generate and manage each tag that your website requires.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">You no longer need to manually code each tag. As an alternative, you can create all of your tags using the UI. Then Tag Manager will put them into action for your website. That is, if each page of the website has a simple Tag Manager code snippet placed in it.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\">Using tags in this fashion has three key advantages</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Reduced Demand on Developers &mdash; You don&#39;t have to bother about manually coding tags, and neither do the web developers at your business. As a result, you&#39;ll have more time to work on things like managing the content for your website.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Greater Accuracy &ndash; Tags that have been manually coded are more prone to mistakes. A tag may become meaningless due to a simple typo or copy/paste error. Such errors won&#39;t be made with Tag Manager.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Control and oversight of your marketing campaigns are made considerably simpler by the Tag Manager interface. As a result, you can produce and employ additional tags that are specifically related to your marketing aims. The creation and use of tags to gather data for your marketing initiatives is simpler.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">You can control and master tags for many analytics systems using Tag Manager. It&#39;s lovely and simple, not to mention free, to get started with Tag Manager. Setting up your Tag Manager account is the first thing you must do.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong><em>Drive in here.</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">For your business to grow online, convert leads into consumers, and optimize a digital marketing plan to forge closer connections with your audience, data collection utilising tools like Google Analytics is essential.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">However, gathering data is more difficult than it sounds. The process is aided by Google Analytics and other similar analytics systems, but they function best when tags are used.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Make your website better with technical SEO that works. Conduct this audit first. To start, tags are often small pieces of code that you insert into the HTML or javascript of your website in order to retrieve specific information.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The length of a user&#39;s visit to a page on your website, form submissions, how a user came at your website, the links that user clicked, or even the items that user withdrew from their shopping cart, are all examples of necessary tag information for marketers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Each tag keeps track of a separate object. You might, for instance, make a tag only to count the number of individuals who submit the form on your &quot;Contact Us&quot; page. Then, the tag may give Google Analytics, AdWords, or another third party more detailed information.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Unfortunately, marketers without much programming or coding experience may find manually coding tags to be a long and challenging task. Additionally, creating tickets for the IT department takes time. Your entire tagging procedure will be considerably simpler using Google Tag Manager. Simply insert a code once into the pages of your website, and Google Tag Manager will code and embed it for you each time you wish to create a tag. Variables, Tags, and Triggers</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">There is a vocabulary for each analytics platform. If you haven&#39;t used the tool before, you might not have encountered any of the unusual words and expressions they all employ. No exemption applies to Google Tag Manager.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">You must comprehend three labels used by the TMS in particular. Starting to use the tool will be simpler if you are aware of what they are all about. Tags, triggers, and variables are the three labels mentioned. Each comprises a crucial component of Tag Manager and has its own area in the user interface. The links to those areas are marked in the image above so you can see them.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><a href=\"https://in.video.search.yahoo.com/search/video;_ylt=AwrPpRx2tBljuIwQCT27HAx.;_ylu=Y29sbwNzZzMEcG9zAzEEdnRpZAMEc2VjA3Nj?p=google+tag+manager+tutorial+video+links&amp;type=E211IN826G91603&amp;ei=UTF-8&amp;fr=mcafee&amp;turl=https%3A%2F%2Ftse4.mm.bing.net%2Fth%3Fid%3DOVP.gSn6srIoCpwEnkBghGcmzAEsDh%26pid%3DApi%26w%3D296%26h%3D156%26c%3D7%26p%3D0&amp;rurl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3D_D5nd5SZ4s8&amp;tit=Google+Tag+Manager+Tutorial+2022+%E2%80%93+The+Complete+%28and+Practical%29+Google+Tag+Manager+%28GTM%29+Tutorial&amp;pos=5&amp;vid=0257c9f5ee91eed970422d265fe3cc64&amp;sigr=1FlrpTpUTnxD&amp;sigt=kGKpbFXumt1U&amp;sigi=55nvLT0QPqsY\">//GTM: just an hour away</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\">What are a tag, a trigger, and a variable, though?</h3>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Tags</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Tag Manager depends on tags. Code snippets are called tags. Platforms for analytics and marketing use them to integrate with websites and mobile applications.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">For instance, Google Analytics uses tags to assist in gathering information about users of various websites. You may create and use these tags more easily because of Tag Manager. The device functions as an interface. Through it, you may produce and distribute tags without having to manually code them. These tags are all uniquely used by web developers, especially the standard HTML tags.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">There are numerous tag settings that Tag Manager naturally supports. In addition to several tags from third-party platforms, they also contain tags from Google products. If the tag configuration you want to utilize isn&#39;t supported by GTM, you can also build custom tags.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The use of custom tags is not advised by Google. They advise that it would be preferable if you asked a tag supplier to sign up for their Tag Vendor Program. However, you can construct either HTML, image, or function tags if you do wish to employ custom versions. Complete instructions on how to make these are available here.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Triggers</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">When a specific event occurs, tags in a website&#39;s code will activate. That event is recognised by a trigger. Triggers keep an eye on your website or app and watch for certain events to happen. Such occurrences include things like form submissions, link clicks, and page views. Triggers direct tags to fire when they find the event they&#39;re looking for.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Configuring the trigger for a new tag is one of the steps you must take in GTM. You can pick from a variety of trigger types. Each one is related to the specific type of event you want the tag to fire for.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">A trigger you build by default makes a tag fire each time the pertinent event takes place. However, you may add filters to a trigger to more precisely define when you require tags to fire and when you do not.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">For example, you could include a filter such that a tag only fires when the URL on which an event happens has a particular suffix. That may be &quot;/products,&quot; &quot;/blog,&quot; or another phrase similar to that. You can then pay closer attention to what&#39;s happening in specific regions of your website.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Variables</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">In Tag Manager, variables are related to both tags and triggers. They serve as values to more specifically define what the tag or trigger should accomplish. The best approach to understand variables is to first examine how they operate for tags and triggers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Variables in the case of triggers define the timing at which the trigger should instruct its associated tag to fire. For instance, you could set up a trigger so that its tag is activated whenever the URL variable contains the phrase &quot;website.com/products.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The precise data that tags should gather is determined by their variables. You could set up a tag, for instance, to extract a product ID and the transaction&#39;s monetary value. There are many Built-In Variables in Tag Manager. They take care of the majority of your fundamental trigger and tag configuration requirements.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Additionally, you can define your own variables. To take into account any particular requirements you may have, you might construct those variables. That is presuming that those needs aren&#39;t met by the Built-In Variables. Later on, we&#39;ll go into greater detail about the two categories of variables.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">Steps for Making a Tag</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">You can use GTM for a wide range of activities. Making tags is the primary one. These are the bits of code that the service will apply for you throughout your selected website or app. Once you&#39;ve made a few of these tags, you&#39;ll discover that it comes naturally to you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">To help you with your first, let&#39;s take each step in turn. You can create a Google Analytics tag for pageview hits by using the steps below. Such a tag will activate and send information about each pageview hit to your Analytics account.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">If you use this kind of tag, you must delete the existing Analytics Container from the source code of your website. Both of them being incorporated in the code of a page will result in duplicate page view hits. Your data are ruined by this duplication.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Selecting the &quot;Add a New Tag&quot; link from the GTM workspace is the first step in generating a tag.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">You may&nbsp;configure your tag on the page that follows the one you just saw. Its naming is your first task. Your tags can have any name you choose. But each site will eventually have quite a few tags, therefore you need to be able to distinguish between them. You can name tags more effectively by using the following naming convention:</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Tag Type &mdash; Specific Tag &mdash; Identifier Unique</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">A Google Analytics pageview tag might be called &quot;UA (Universal Analytics) &mdash; Pageview &mdash; All Site Pages,&quot; for instance. After entering a name, you can click the box asking you to select a tag type.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">A list of available tag kinds will then appear. These are the tag configurations that GTM can support out of the box, as we previously said. Select the settings for any other platforms or analytics tools that you want to integrate with your website. This sample uses Google Analytics as the data source.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">We want the Analytics platform to track the tag since we are developing one. You must first select a &quot;Track Type&quot; before entering your web property ID from Analytics. The precise kind of tag you want to create is called &quot;Track Type.&quot; You should select the &#39;pageview&#39; Track Type since we are constructing a pageview tag in this example.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">You have two options for providing your Analytics web property ID. The manual entry of the IP for the tag is your first choice. It&#39;s simple to do, but you&#39;ll need to go through it again for any additional Analytics tag you add.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">You need to go to your Google Analytics account first in order to manually add the web property ID. Once there, select &quot;Property Settings&quot; from the Admin panel. Your tracking ID can be found in the box below:</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Be careful to choose the &quot;Enable overriding settings in this tag&quot; checkbox before returning to GTM. There will be a space where you can type your tracking ID. There is a different way to enter the web property ID.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">You can make a custom variable so that you don&#39;t have to type in each tag&#39;s ID individually. The ID will always be present in that variable. With only one click, you may add it to a tag. As we already mentioned, GTM has two different kinds of variables. You should be aware of the purpose of each variable alternative if you plan to construct a custom tag.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Built-in Variables</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The variables that GTM can automatically define for you are known as built-in variables. The tool can identify elements in a tag&#39;s code, and it uses these elements to determine the variable.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">GTM contains the vast majority of the most popular variable types. These include any that have to do with pages or clicks. These variables can be added by using the GTM workspace&#39;s &quot;Built-in Variables&quot; section of the &quot;Variables&quot; section.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">User-Defined Variables</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Custom or user-defined variables will store any value you specify for them. This could be a number, a single name string, or a list of URLs. It is the tracking ID connected to your Google Analytics account in the instance of our example. In that case, let&#39;s return to making that special variable for your initial tag.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Go to the &quot;Variables&quot; section of GTM to create the variable for your tracking ID. A list of the built-in variables that were added for the relevant property will be displayed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">You can find the section of the page marked &quot;User Defined Variables&quot; by scrolling down. When prompted to configure the variable, choose &quot;New&quot; and then select &quot;Constant.&quot; Next, provide your tracking ID as the value of the variable. Then, all you have to do is click &quot;Save,&quot; and your new variable will be ready.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Return to the tag you are producing at this point. Don&#39;t select the &quot;Enable overriding settings in this tag&quot; checkbox this time. Instead, select the newly created custom variable from the drop-down menu labelled &quot;Google Analytics Setting.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Your initial tag has been created and configured. Configuring the trigger is the final step.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Click on the &quot;Triggering&quot; box to set the trigger for your initial tag. The following is a screenshot:</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The next page you see will ask you to &quot;Choose a trigger.&quot; To add a new trigger, click the tiny &quot;+&quot; icon towards the top right corner of the page. The trigger must first be given a name, much like your tag. Give it a name that reflects how it works. For instance, we can call the trigger &quot;All Pages&quot; since we&#39;re making a pageview tag that will fire for every page on our site.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The trigger type is then a choice that is presented to you. The trigger type specifies the category of event that the trigger instructs your tag to fire for. You should choose &quot;pageview&quot; as the trigger type in the event of a pageview trigger.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Decide when the trigger instructs your tag to fire in the final stage. You may either set it to fire on all pages or just a select few pages. All pages on our website will be covered by our first, general tag.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Hence select the &quot;All Page Views&quot; option.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">That describes how to set up your first tag&#39;s trigger. Click &quot;Save&quot; now. The tag, along with any others you make, will be visible in the &#39;Tags&#39; section of your GTM workspace:</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Your tag has been generated, but it is not yet active on your website. To begin gathering data and sending it to Google Analytics, you must publish your new tag. It makes sense to test the tag through GTM and troubleshoot any issues you encounter before publishing it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">//<a href=\"https://in.video.search.yahoo.com/search/video;_ylt=AwrPpRx2tBljuIwQBT27HAx.;_ylu=Y29sbwNzZzMEcG9zAzEEdnRpZAMEc2VjA3Nj?p=google+tag+manager+tutorial+video+links&amp;type=E211IN826G91603&amp;ei=UTF-8&amp;fr=mcafee&amp;turl=https%3A%2F%2Ftse1.mm.bing.net%2Fth%3Fid%3DOVP.6ehA6J0UYuTu-zvMExrNqwHgFo%26pid%3DApi%26w%3D296%26h%3D156%26c%3D7%26p%3D0&amp;rurl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3D1dwk_erXAko&amp;tit=Google+Tag+Manager+Tutorial+2021+for+Beginners+%28with+Google+Analytics+4+examples%29&amp;pos=1&amp;vid=b7734e42b0814e03b1bef4cf65319d2e&amp;sigr=EUdplUlNy0Nx&amp;sigt=keFaxdjQYYbB&amp;sigi=HvY8ZWEJ1pdr\">Google tag manager tutorial 2021 for beginners</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\">Using GTM for Testing and Tag Debugging</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">GTM is completely user-friendly, much like the top Google Analytics tools are. The process of testing your tags is simple. All you have to do is click the &quot;Preview&quot; button in the workspace&#39;s upper right corner. The workspace will then display a banner notifying you that preview mode is currently in effect across the top.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Now, if you open your website in a new tab, a GTM terminal window for debugging tags will appear. Your browser&#39;s footer has it. The pane shows details about the tags associated with the website you&#39;re browsing. It most critically informs you of whether the tags fired or not as well as the information that was sent to each platform by the tags (Analytics, etc.).</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">When you visit a page on your website, the first pageview tag you created should start to fire. You&#39;re ready to publish the tag if you can see that it did so in the console window. You must ascertain why it didn&#39;t fire and address any problems if you can. The tag in that console window must be clicked in order to accomplish this.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The &quot;firing triggers&quot; for each tag are displayed when you click one of the tags in the preview window. These elements determine whether the trigger instructs the tag to fire. A red &quot;X&quot; will appear next to the firing trigger filter when a tag hasn&#39;t fired. That red &quot;X&quot; is essential if you believe that the tag should have been fired. It highlights the trigger configuration component that has to be changed again.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">You can publish your tag&nbsp;on your website, once you&#39;re confident about its working. Click the &quot;Submit&quot; button in the top right corner of the main GTM workspace:</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">You publish a new version of your container, complete with the tag you&#39;ve inserted, by clicking &quot;Submit.&quot; Both a name and a description must be given for the container version. These two components might be used to describe the changes you&#39;ve made. You can then review your actions and their timing or demonstrate them to other GTM container users.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The last step is to hit &quot;Publish.&quot; According to the parameters you specified, the tag ought to immediately activate and start sending data to your Analytics account. Now that it is functioning properly, it is worthwhile to check.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\">Best GTM Extensions</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">This tutorial attempts to introduce you to Google Tag Manager. You need to have grasped the fundamentals of setting up GTM and producing tags after reading the aforementioned material. But when you become more accustomed to it, you might want to utilize GTM a bit more.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">You may get your hands on a variety of tools and extensions that assist you in doing just that. Tag Assistant and GTM Debug are two of the top extensions currently available. Both of these Chrome browser add-ons were created to support your use of GTM.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Google&#39;s addon for tagging issues is called Tag Assistant. The extension will identify the tags that are present when you visit any page on your site after installing Tag Assistant.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">It will notify you of any errors involving those tags and provide advice on how to fix them.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">A comparable tool is GTM Debug. You may quickly check event information and Analytics hits pertaining to any of your pages. It may also be used to inspect and debug the tags on your website in a manner similar to how we explained using GTM&#39;s preview feature. However, with GTM Debug, you can only evaluate tags that are currently in use.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\">How does Google Tag Manager work?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">With the help of Google Tag Manager, you can create and manage tags through an interface rather than having to write new code for each tag you want to create. The Google Tag Manager code is simply inserted into each page of your website. Your marketing approach will become more effective and precise as a result of eliminating the manual procedure of establishing tags.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The first thing Google Tag Manager does is relieve your engineers and IT staff of the work of writing each individual marketing tag, allowing them to concentrate on other important projects.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Second, by automatically coding the tags, Google Tag Manager greatly lowers the chance of human error.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Third, Google Tag Manager gives your marketing division total control over the tags they develop and keep track of. Giving your marketers complete control over their tags improves productivity. Additionally, adding tags increases the precision of your analytics programme, ensuring higher-quality data and a more accurate understanding of your genuine online audience.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Despite this, you should still give the tool a shot before deciding if it&#39;s a good fit for you. Maybe you already have a tagging system established or don&#39;t think you need that much organisation since your website doesn&#39;t frequently require new tags.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Due to the fact that Google Tag Manager is free, you can test it out almost risk-free. Here, we&#39;ll walk you through how to register an account, add a new tag, integrate Google Tag Manager with Google Analytics, and embed the plugin in WordPress.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">After that, it will be up to you to decide whether or not it is the ideal system for your company.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align:justify\">Steps for Setting up&nbsp;Google Tag Manager</h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><em>Create an account</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">A free account may be created in two simple steps, but it is distinct from any other Google Analytics or Gmail accounts you may have. We&#39;ve documented our account setup procedure to make sure it&#39;s easy for you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">What you should do is:</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">1. Create an Account for Google Tag Manager&nbsp;</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Click the green &quot;Sign Up for Free&quot; button while you are on the Google Tag Manager website. The country, website URL, account name (business), and the location where you want to use Google Tag will all be requested (web, iOS, android, AMP). Click the blue &quot;Create&quot; button when you are finished.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"Sign up for Google Tag Manager\" src=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/Rd0-ei1JqPSgqHxJHNqPTON7_UTKVJ38gkK1rLAyZyVDigHkU2CI12DRRedxZazdlanjNmrtYDf9P2x4MLF1kHhD5wUf-ffrvz8UMVy1r4TIpP8LRBlNgjvgiHGt2tgoxPHisuP8-boRnd9beM6C_8hfyXF7d-MSKXx0d7OTvyefik4HRWlzx0LfqCY3PzcrmhLTYHfp_Q\" style=\"height:248px; width:602px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">//reference image taken from <a href=\"https://blog.hubspot.com/hubfs/The%20Beginners%20Guide%20to%20Google%20Tag%20Manager-8.png\">blog.hubspot.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">2. Activate Google Tag Manager</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Comply with the coding guidelines. Next, you&#39;ll be given two codes and told to add one after the first body&gt; tag and one high in the head&gt; of your page. Apply the codes to your website now or at a later time (they are accessible in your dashboard). Click &quot;Ok&quot; once you&#39;re done.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"Google Tag code instructions and codes\" src=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/VnPOwOJ0GWJln5oYvWVaM7kmfujgKkGASut2-d3FS8SVd7eOUpbiYKYiVjbb743_ugB_76a7d6kNghZFqzPdq4JtsxFM1yu6mMiwz3YQV7TrIq_b9qRwK74ujIE4HKrlG80cYinT8rq8-0UNLkUxL5jQd0_OBdFcjyCKAoRUGx4h--9zZnVK2S3_YXmu9b4KZ6W6oC-9jA\" style=\"height:381px; width:561px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">//Reference image taken from <a href=\"https://blog.hubspot.com/hubfs/The%20Beginners%20Guide%20to%20Google%20Tag%20Manager-10.png\">blog.hubspot.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">3. Codes and guidelines for Google Tags</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>1. Create a tag</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"Google Tag Manager dashboard\" src=\"https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/6DrwUOKWeFccZtP0kTPcLhe98_SimXxOseN_ZJLROa1GgOWlRVmo9yqZNuoz6Np7Qq-7ymowancjKqXnsCvOignH3nB4E3FLGyYyYE5NW3DA5QNdeCeA6_jpEq88SLp80voI5UCrTmvL-B2g_2G8ui160A7cX-RabC22lzRTYcXwcM2VMIBZzA23MOpijs5RimoRg07bNA\" style=\"height:238px; width:520px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;//Reference image taken from <a href=\"https://blog.hubspot.com/hubfs/The%20Beginners%20Guide%20to%20Google%20Tag%20Manager.jpeg\">blog.hubspot.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The first thing you&#39;ll want to learn after you have a Google Tag Manager account is how to set up a tag.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">In Google Tag Manager, you may arrange tags in any number of ways.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">This is useful for compiling in-depth reports on the actions of your audience, but if you don&#39;t structure your tags properly, it could become ineffective.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Tag type, app name, and detail are the suggested naming conventions by Google.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">You may give the first tagging configuration the names &quot;AdWords conversions - iOS - 2018-02 campaign&quot; and &quot;Google Analytics - CTA - About Us page,&quot; respectively.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">By doing this, you may appropriately identify and gather information on particular campaigns or pages.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">For instance, the second tag, &quot;Google Analytics - CTA - About Us page,&quot; provides you with information on the effectiveness of your About Us call-to-action button. If your tags were called more broadly, like &quot;CTA button,&quot; you might lose that crucial information.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>2. Integrate Google Analytics tracking with your tag.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The next step is to provide your Web Property ID, which can be located in your Google Analytics account, if you want your tag to be tracked in Google Analytics. Next, choose a &quot;Track Type.&quot; Although there are other other alternatives, I went with &quot;Page View.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>3. Select a trigger to specify how and when the tag will be recorded.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Next, select a trigger, such as &quot;every time someone visits the page,&quot; to indicate when you want the tag to be recorded. I selected &quot;All Pages&quot; to gather information whenever someone views one of my web pages, but your needs may differ.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Configure a tag trigger in Tag Manager</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">configure a tag trigger Maintain your tag.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"Tag configuration screen in Google Tag Manager\" src=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/eEqcbRpvxxboKVI75w1J2ZTm66rHLcAJg5q3BJAOVFfY1L9fBSVJqq5imOHqx9NyeroFMuOMpheFgEsY-Kony6osK4dU2UmAitXtHU37AtAID2X22EGng-vdsL9hNtcykJ8NDSmWXTbN0HSqwS6HADsPfiv6vWB7RfIlJcZ5ffap08hgcwfmobe4JXVe-huriaHoEStsgA\" style=\"height:296px; width:538px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">//Reference image taken from <a href=\"https://blog.hubspot.com/hubfs/The%20Beginners%20Guide%20to%20Google%20Tag%20Manager.png\">blog.hubspot.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Click the blue &quot;Save&quot; button once you are satisfied with the data in the &quot;Tag Configuration&quot; and &quot;Triggering&quot; boxes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Using Google Tag Manager, save your tag.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">4. Click &quot;Submit&quot; to activate your tag.</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Click the &quot;Submit&quot; button in blue to continue. Until you do that, your tag won&#39;t function.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">You will be directed to this &quot;Submission Configuration&quot; page after clicking &quot;Submit.&quot; &quot;Publish and Create Version&quot; and &quot;Create Version&quot; are the two choices. I chose &quot;Publish and Create Version&quot; and then clicked the blue &quot;Publish&quot; button in the upper right to force the tag onto all of my website&#39;s pages.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">publish your tag</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">5. Your tags will be more organized if you give them a name and a description.</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">You&#39;ll see this &quot;Container Version Description&quot; before the end. Add a name and explanation to your tags to keep them organized and make it clear what you&#39;re attempting to capture.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">You should give your Google Tag Manager tags a name and a description.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">6. Make sure your tag appears in the report for the current version.</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">You&#39;ve just finished making your first tag successfully.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\">Google Analytics and Google Tag Manager</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">There are a few procedures you must follow if you wish to use Google Tag Manager in conjunction with Google Analytics. The accuracy of your Analytics results will be improved by embedding tags in your website, therefore it&#39;s a worthy investment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">You must first remove the GA code from the pages of your website. Only your Google Tag Manager tag code needs to be inserted; if you use both, your data will be messed up because everything will be reported twice.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">A variable is a Google Tag Manager tool designed to boost productivity by storing extra (optional) data you offer. You&#39;ll probably want to create one for your Google Analytics Tracking ID.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">You won&#39;t need to seek up your GA Tracking ID each time you create a new Google Analytics tag if you preserve it as a variable (which makes the lazy-person in me very happy).</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">whichever page you&rsquo;ve selected.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', 'Any webmaster or site owner should have access to Google Tag Manager. In order to manage the tags on any website, the system is essential. For those of us who aren\'t professional coders, it makes tag management quick, effective, and simpler to understand.', 'google-tag-manager-step-by-step-guide', 'google tag manager, google tag manager guide, How do I use Google Tag Manager?, google tag manager beginners guide, digital marketing services in navi mumbai, how to setup google tag manager account', 'Ayushi', '2022-11-21 20:12:52', '2022-11-21 20:16:51');
INSERT INTO `blog` (`id`, `blog_title`, `blog_category`, `image1`, `image2`, `description`, `description1`, `blog_url`, `tags`, `author_name`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(50, '30 Top YouTube SEO Tools to Boost Your Reach and Rankings', 'Youtube', '30 Top YouTube SEO Tools to Boost Your Reach and Rankings.png', NULL, '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">It takes more than just producing video after video to increase your YouTube audience and video rankings. Focusing on quality rather than quantity will help you get better results. This will help you rank higher, take the top spot, and dramatically increase your video views and subscribers. You can also stop making subpar films only to reach arbitrary quotas.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">However, as anyone who has attempted to broaden their audience and increase video views on YouTube will attest, it isn&#39;t simple. Fortunately, we&#39;ve discovered 30 amazing <strong>YouTube SEO tools</strong> that help speed up your journey to a substantial and active YouTube audience.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align:justify\">30 Best YouTube SEO Tools to Improve Your Rankings and Reach:</h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">1. TubeBuddy</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">2. YouTube Analytics</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">3. vidIQ</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">4. YouTube Autosuggest</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">5. Google Keyword Planner</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">6. Keyword Tool (Keywordtool.io)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">7. Rank Tracker</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">8. Ahrefs Keywords Explorer</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">9. Kparser</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">10. YTRank</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">11. RapidTags</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">12. TagsYouTube</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">13. Rival IQ</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">14. SE Ranking</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">15. SerpStat</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">16. TagsForYouTube</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">17. YouTube&#39;s Comment Moderation</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">18. Smart Moderation</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">19. Google Trends</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">20. Camtasia</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">21. Canva</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">22. FotoJet</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">23. Snappa</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">24. iMovie</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">25. Blender</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">26. Corel VideoStudio</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">27. Morningfame</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">28. Tubics</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">29. NoxInfluencer: For Competitor Research</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">30. AnswerThePublic</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\">What Justifies YouTube Optimization?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Powerful search engine, YouTube. It actually comes in second place to Google in terms of popularity worldwide. Google also enjoys YouTube content. Video material stands out from the rest of the search results when you conduct a Google search:</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Your chances of ranking higher on Google and YouTube&#39;s internal search are greatly improved when you concentrate on producing the appropriate YouTube content utilizing the appropriate keywords and tags. This is the reason we&#39;ve compiled this list of 30&nbsp;YouTube optimization tools so you may increase your position and attract more YouTube subscribers without having to invest numerous hours in making videos only for the sake of making videos.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align:justify\">30 Top Tools for YouTube SEO</h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">It only makes sense to concentrate on producing the greatest, most optimized YouTube videos when you take into account that video is the top-performing content across all social media platforms. Following that, you can distribute them over your social networks to broaden your audience and gain more fans. Nevertheless, it might be challenging to get your films found on the network given its more than 2 billion subscribers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\">Your YouTube Channel Management</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">There is a little more to running a profitable YouTube channel than merely uploading videos. Additionally, you must monitor the effectiveness of your films to avoid spending time and resources on subpar material. You&#39;ll find YouTube optimization tools in this part that can help you learn how your channel is doing so that you can take action to change its direction or promote the material that is working well on your other social networks.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">1. TubeBuddy</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The browser add-on TubeBuddy provides a plethora of options for efficiently managing your YouTube channel. It contains productivity, video SEO, data and research, promotion, and bulk processing capabilities. You can make and schedule YouTube videos using TubeBuddy, as well as develop end-screen themes and use previously saved responses for quick content moderation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">2. YouTube Analytics</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">One of the best tools you can use to determine where and how well your channel is performing is YouTube&#39;s own analytics tool. By using it, you can increase the number of views on your YouTube videos and keep your audience interested by learning more about them and the content that appeals to them. Additionally, you may view the number of times your videos have been viewed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">3. vidIQ</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">A browser add-on called VidIQ provides the statistics you need to monitor your YouTube performance. Additionally, you may add rival channels to compare them to your own and set up email notifications to uncover popular themes. Even Facebook Syndication allows you to instantaneously post your video on several social media sites.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The Top 5 YouTube Video Editing Programs Available for Purchase</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">Choose the Best Keywords</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">For YouTube users, descriptions and titles provide crucial information. Users are better able to decide whether to watch your video when you employ the appropriate keywords in the description and title of your YouTube videos. In this section, you&rsquo;ll find YouTube optimization tools that can help you find the keywords that will get your videos ranked and viewed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">4. Auto-suggest on YouTube</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">If you&#39;ve ever used YouTube to search for a video, you are aware that the instant you begin typing, YouTube begins to propose words and phrases to aid you:</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Although it&#39;s a fantastic tool for users, it&#39;s also a really helpful tool for developers. In a manner similar to Google Trends, you can put your keyword or topic into the YouTube search bar and use the autosuggest results to uncover keywords you ought to use in your video&#39;s title, tags, and description.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">5. Google Keyword Planner</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">To help artists locate the ideal keywords to utilize in their content, Google provides a tonne of free tools. A fantastic tool is Google Keyword Planner. You can utilize Google Keyword Planner without running advertisements by going to your Google Ads dashboard. It will assist you in identifying the keywords that are most valuable for Google searches so you can incorporate them into the titles and descriptions of your YouTube videos.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">6. Keyword Tool (Keywordtool.io)</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Using the freemium product Keyword Tool, you may discover themes that your readers might be interested in based on the searches they&#39;re most likely to make. Simply type a broad phrase or topic into the Keyword Tool, and it will provide you with recommendations that include questions, prepositions, and even hashtags. You can obtain search volumes, cost-per-click, competition data, and trends with the subscription edition, which has a monthly starting price of $69 just.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">7. Rank&nbsp;Tracker</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Another freemium tool for keyword research is Rank Tracker. You can use it to extract terms from YouTube&#39;s suggested keywords list and analyze information such as search traffic, competition, anticipated visitors, and more. Finding keywords that will qualify your videos for the coveted featured snippet position, which places you at the top of the search results, is easy with Rank Tracker. The cost of the paid version is $72 per year.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">8. Ahrefs Keywords Explorer</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">One of the biggest datasets of YouTube keywords may be found in Ahrefs Keywords Explorer. In order to determine how many people search for a particular term on YouTube each month, you can search for your keyword and find local and worldwide search volume, clicks, click percentage, and clickstream data. There are studies on keyword suggestions as well, which can help you come up with some excellent keywords or topics.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">9. Kparser</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Another simple-to-use paid keyword research tool that emphasizes long-tail keywords is Kparser. Similar to Term.io, you can add keywords before and after your target keyword, however, Kparser gives you the option to select the level of parsing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">10. YTRank</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">You may track the YouTube ranks for a chosen keyword using the incredibly straightforward free tool YTRank. Simply select the desired location, enter the YouTube video&#39;s URL, and then enter some keywords.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Research ProfitableTags</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">YouTube tags are words and phrases that inform YouTube about the subject matter of your video. Similar to keywords, tags play a significant role in search results on YouTube. You may find YouTube optimization tools right here that can assist you in identifying the most lucrative tags for your YouTube videos.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">11. RapidTags</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">RapidTags is a free tool that produces tags for YouTube quickly. For some areas, a language filter can be used. You may acquire a list of tags to utilize on your YouTube videos by just typing your desired keyword into the search box.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">12. TagsYouTube</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Tags are comparable to RapidTags.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">You can enter your goal keyword on YouTube to get a list of relevant tags to use for your YouTube content. A thumbnail generator, an elaborate title, and a detailed description are other capabilities of this program.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Discover what your rivals are doing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">An excellent method to develop your own video marketing strategy and find ideas for fresh material is to research your competitors on YouTube. You&#39;ll find YouTube optimization tools in this section that will give you an advantage over your rivals.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">13. Rival&nbsp;IQ</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">With the use of Rival IQ&#39;s YouTube analytics data, you can better understand your rivals and decide how to run your own channel to achieve better outcomes. With the help of Rival IQ, you can see how frequently your rivals publish new material as well as how much engagement, subscribers, views, comments, and other metrics their posts receive.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">14. SE Ranking</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">With the help of the keyword tracking tool SE Ranking, customers may check YouTube rankings on a daily basis from any place or device. Even better, you can specify a target URL for each search, in which case all non-target URLs will be highlighted in red. Rankings across five search engines and up to five rival sites can be monitored.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">15. SerpStat</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Using the keyword research tool SerpStat, you can see what your rivals are doing. SerpStat can propose keywords you can rank for based on one goal keyword you provide it, as well as discover search terms that potential leads use.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">16. TagsForYouTube</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">By selecting &quot;see more&quot; next to the video description, the free TagsForYouTube Chrome extension allows you to view the video tags for any video. Finding out what tags your rivals are using in their films is a wonderful approach to use those tags yourself.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Clean Up Your Comments</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">It&#39;s crucial to moderate your YouTube comments. Not only can comments affect YouTube&#39;s algorithm, but keeping them civil also contributes to the accuracy of the information your audience receives and builds trust in your company. Here are some methods for optimizing YouTube that might help you keep your comment sections secure.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">17. YouTube&#39;s Comment Moderation</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The built-in comment moderation feature on YouTube allows you to modify parameters to automatically weed out undesirable remarks. You can enter a list of phrases you want to restrict, add certain persons to approve their comments automatically, and block messages that contain hashtags and URLs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">18. Smart &nbsp;moderation</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">For social media networks, smart moderation is a paid technology that offers comment moderation. As comments are written, it links to your social media profiles and removes unwanted ones. Since it is AI-based, it can censor comments almost as well as a human. The AI also allows the product to learn as you use it more. Prices begin at $79 per month.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">19.&nbsp;Google Trends</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">An easy-to-use tool for locating great video themes is Google Trends. Enter your general topic or keyword and choose YouTube Search in the text box. To receive the most pertinent results, you can then select a location, category, and time frame.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">20. Camtasia</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">For those of us who conduct webinars, tutorials, and presentations, Camtasia is an excellent YouTube optimization tool since it allows you to record your screen, including mouse and keystroke movements. Then, you may edit your movies to include music or narration, effects, animations, annotations, quizzes, and more.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">21. Canva</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">One of the greatest programmes for producing eye-catching YouTube video thumbnails is Canva. You can create your design from scratch or choose one of Canva&#39;s thousands of lovely templates. Canva&#39;s drag-and-drop interface makes it incredibly simple to produce captivating visuals that will draw attention to your YouTube videos.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">22. FotoJet</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Alternative to Canva, FotoJet has a sophisticated YouTube thumbnail maker. It enables you to fully customize and adjust your thumbnail by including filters, cropping and resizing photographs, rotating images, and a whole lot more. Similar to Canva, FotoJet provides a user-friendly drag-and-drop interface.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">23. Snappa</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The all-in-one graphic design programme Snappa includes a tonne of fantastic themes that make it simple to build beautiful YouTube thumbnails. For individuals who lack design expertise, Snappa also guides you step-by-step through the design process.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">24. iMovie</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">You probably already know quite a bit about this video editing programme if you use an Apple product to make your YouTube videos. Users of iMovie may effortlessly crop, edit, and rearrange videos whatever they like thanks to the program&#39;s user-friendly interface. You may also effortlessly publish to YouTube and add visual effects and titles.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">25. Blender</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Free video editing software called Blender has some cutting-edge features. VFX, animation, modeling, rendering, 3D, and even video game development are all possible with Blender. In addition to these entertaining features, Blender enables you to cut videos, add filters, and incorporate transitions to create original and entertaining YouTube videos.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">26. Corel VideoStudio</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The premium Windows-only video editing program Corel VideoStudio comes with all the usual tools (crop, resize, trim, rearrange, etc.), as well as a split-screen interface, stop motion animation, and other features. Even better, you may use the software to directly post your videos to YouTube.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">27. Morningfame</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">MorningFame is the greatest YouTube optimization tool available. Why? Because it gives you comprehensible information instead of just spitting out data and graphs. YouTube Analytics is more enjoyable with Morningfame. Here are several justifications for using Morningfame.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">You can use it to make your YouTube videos search-engine-friendly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">It gives you tailored advice on how to enhance your YouTube channel.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">It gives you the freedom to build on what works and discard what doesn&#39;t.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Even if Morningfame may sound too good to be true, there is a catch. Morningfame is not accessible to everyone. The platform is invite-only. Only users who have already used it can utilize it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Price: The monthly minimum is $4.90.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">28.Tunics</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">A useful YouTube SEO tool called Tubics can help you come up with ideas, increase views, and even test different thumbnail variations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">For businesses, this product offers a one-stop SEO solution. Even big businesses like Samsung and L&#39;Or&eacute;al currently employ it. Tubics assists you in your SEO journey by providing a step-by-step SEO checklist and a sizable user base.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">It aids in developing video ideas.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">You may create videos with the help of Tubics, from the script to keyword research.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">automated recommendations for SEO</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Price: Enterprise-level plans begin at $790 per month.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">29. NoxInfluencer: For Competitor Research</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">NoxInfluencer: What is it? It serves as a tool to link brands with prospective sponsors and influencers. This implies that even if your marketing team wishes to utilize their premium software for other purposes, it won&#39;t be useful for your videos. But they offer useful, cost-free tools that are quite helpful! Some of the tools it offers are listed below.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">YouTube channel value calculator that provides instant results</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">YouTube video analytics aid in the analysis and optimization of YouTube videos.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">You can compare YouTubers with YouTube Compare. YouTube Live Sub Count provides a real-time, second-by-second sub count.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">You may choose the ideal influencer for your brand with the Influencers Marketing Calculator.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Price: Basic plan starts from $99/month</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">30. AnswerThePublic (ATP)</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Both a free edition and paid plans are available on Answer the Public. It is a unique SEO tool that can assist you in assessing the market. You may find the most popular questions on a certain keyword quickly with Answer the Public. The outcomes are then displayed as data and visualization.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Reports can be divided into three categories: inquiries, prepositions, and comparisons. These reports can be useful for creating new YouTube videos. The accessible CSV reports are also available for download.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Price: Free version available. The basic plan starts from $99/month.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\">Frequently Asked Questions&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\">1. How should SEO be used on YouTube?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Ans:-</strong> It takes more than just producing video after video to increase your YouTube audience and video rankings. Focusing on quality rather than quantity will help you get better results. You may achieve this by adding video keywords, optimizing your video title and YouTube tags, requesting viewer interaction, promoting subscriptions, and generating a fantastic, captivating thumbnail. That is how you can consistently rank your videos first, or at the very least, get them to appear on the first page of YouTube search results.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">By including features like playlists, metadata, keyword-rich descriptions, and videos created specifically for the platform, you can optimize your channel for YouTube. You may position your videos for success on YouTube and elsewhere, such as Google search, by using YouTube SEO. This will help you rank higher, take the top spot, and dramatically increase your video views and subscribers. You can also stop making subpar films only to reach arbitrary quotas.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\">2. What are the best SEO tools for YouTube?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Ans:- These YouTube SEO tools serve the purpose-</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">TubeBuddy</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">YouTube Analytics</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">vidIQ</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">YouTube Autosuggest</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Google Keyword Planner</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Keyword Tool (Keywordtool.io)</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Rank Tracker</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Ahrefs Keywords Explorer</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Kparser</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">YTRank</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\">3. How can your YouTube rankings be improved?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Ans:-</strong> Increased YouTube ranks are directly related to SEO. Follow these three simple procedures for the best SEO results! Get to know your audience and their search patterns well first. The foundation of SEO is the understanding of your target audience. Secondly, adjust your website and movies to your audience&#39;s preferences. Plan to increase sales from website visitors and video viewers, third.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\">4. How can your YouTube rankings be improved more quickly?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Ans:-</strong> It&#39;s difficult to expand your audience, get more views on your videos, and climb the YouTube ranks. You must spend time optimising your YouTube channel and videos for search if you want to see results. You may achieve this by adding video keywords, optimizing your video title and YouTube tags, requesting viewer interaction, promoting subscriptions, and generating a fantastic, captivating thumbnail. That is how you can consistently rank the top of your video, or at the very least, get them to appear on the first page of YouTube search results.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">If you are looking for the best <strong><a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/\">digital marketing agency in Navi Mumbai</a>,</strong> reach out to us thereby growing your business.</p>', 'However, as anyone who has attempted to broaden their audience and increase video views on YouTube will attest, it isn\'t simple. Fortunately, we\'ve discovered 30 amazing YouTube SEO tools that help speed up your journey to a substantial and active YouTube audience.', '30-top-youtube-seo-tools-to-boost-your-reach-and-rankings', 'youtube seo, youtube seo tools, top youtube seo tools, seo tips, youtube rankings, youtube seo tools free, best youtube seo tools', 'Ayushi', '2022-11-24 00:13:42', '2022-11-24 00:19:24');
INSERT INTO `blog` (`id`, `blog_title`, `blog_category`, `image1`, `image2`, `description`, `description1`, `blog_url`, `tags`, `author_name`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(51, '301 vs. 302 Redirects for SEO: Complete Guide', 'SEO', '301-vs-302-redirects-for-seo-complete-guide.png', NULL, '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Before diving in with 301 vs. 302 redirects for modern day SEO, let us encounter the idea of redirection. One website can be reached by several links thanks to the fundamental Internet technique known as redirection. Redirecting HTTP requests is still a rather baffling problem for webmasters and search engines in 2020. Redirection can occur at the domain level and at the link level, where another link opens in place of the original.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">If you wish users to be able to access your website using many alternative addresses, for instance: company.com, company.org, and company.us To accomplish this, you can register the required domain names, designate the primary domain name, and set up permanent redirection for the secondary domain names.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Redirects are most frequently used for the following reasons:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">an unreliable or absent link;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">a fresh webpage or website;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">temporary inaccessibility, for instance, you are modifying or restoring a page and you want to redirect users until you are finished working;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">a page that has been deactivated or removed, perhaps for older or discontinued products;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">changing to a different CMS platform;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">You don&#39;t want to undermine the value of the link because someone posted a backlink/inbound link&nbsp;to a broken page or one that is not accessible right now;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Changing or upgrading the site&#39;s navigation;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">slicing a lengthy link;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">to prevent broken links caused by page moves;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">to link several domains together to form one website;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">to link related domain names to the same website, for instance, if you are accounting for the most frequent mistakes;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">to safeguard personal data</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">to stop re-sent POST/ REDIRECT/ GET requests on forms;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">to send visitors to regional or mobile versions of the page;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">switching to a more secure protocol or putting in place an SSL security certificate, for instance;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">in order to conduct A/B testing on various iterations of pages, content, branding, etc.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Hackers frequently employ redirection, for example:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">for tricking search engines;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">to mislead customers;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">to remove referral traffic information;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">for deceptive operations like the propagation of malware or phishing.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;Read more about SPAM and how to protect yourself in this article.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Redirects can be used for a wide range of functions, as you can see. Knowing the fundamental methods for configuring redirects is crucial for maintaining the ranking and user experience of your pages as choosing the right tool is only half the battle. The most common redirects include these:</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Precise Description</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\">301 and 308 are permanent redirects.</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">If a page or resource has been transferred and will be permanently used at its new location, HTML status codes 301 and 308 are applicable. When redesigning a web page or switching to a safer protocol, a permanent redirection is a fantastic option. RFC 7538, which added the 308 redirect, was published in 2015.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The code has not been supported by all browsers, as with all breakthroughs. For instance, Windows 7 and 8 both come with Internet Explorer 11, yet when error number 308 occurred, it simply displayed an empty page.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The client&#39;s response determines how redirects 301 and 308 are handled differently (the browser). In particular, the client must resubmit the identical request on the redirected page if they receive a 308 HTML status code. To put it another way, if you send a POST request and receive a 308 redirect in the response, your browser will need to send a POST request to the website you were sent to. A 301 HTML status code enables you to redirect when changing the request method, which is typically the case with clients.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">To maintain greater compatibility, it is generally advised to stick with 301 code for ongoing redirects. However, you can utilise the 308 redirect if you are confident that all of your customers will be able to correctly comprehend the updated code and if the handling of POST requests is crucial.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\">302, 303, and 307 are temporary redirects.</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The 302 status code for temporary redirects was the sole one specified in the 1996 release of the HTTP/1.0 protocol.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Despite it being stated that clients cannot alter the request method in a redirected request, the majority of browsers always perform GET on the redirect URL. This is the primary justification behind the adoption of the new status codes 303 redirect and 307 redirect in the 1999 update to HTTP/1.1. Temporary redirect codes let users know that a page or resource they&#39;re interested in is actually available at a different address. This means that the end date of temporary redirection limits their lifespan and that content caching is not necessary. For instance, the best course of action is to set up a temporary redirect to the correct landing page if one of your pages needs technical work. For submitting alternative versions of the content or complete sites based on location, device, or other particulars of each user, temporary redirects are also advised.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Regardless of the approach that was initially used, the HTTP 303 status code informs the client that the resource is momentarily available somewhere else and it expressly directs the user to conduct a GET request for the new URL. The client is instructed to retry the request with a different URL and the same request method as they used for the initial request with the status code 307.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Redirects are always carried out as GET requests since, in practise, browsers and search bots interpret code 302 the same way they do code 303.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Despite the passage of sufficient time since the submission of status codes 303 and 307 in 1999, some clients continue to transgress the norm and fail to complete requests in accordance with its specifications. As a result, for compatibility concerns, much as the situation with codes 301 and 308, we generally advise following the 302 redirect.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The Influence on Search Engine Optimization&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The outdated version of the page is substituted for the original one when a Google search bot detects permanent redirection 301 or 308. It makes sense to wonder if this has an impact on the page&#39;s ranking weight. In this video, Matt Cutts explains how employing 301 redirects results in about the same amount of link weight loss as a regular link. Additionally, Matt Cutts addresses in this video if a site or page can have a certain number of permanent redirect codes. Therefore, you do not need to be concerned about persistent redirects harming your SERP ranking.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Temporary redirections are merely aesthetic from Google&#39;s perspective. The search engine is aware that HTTP codes 302, 303, and 307 are transient since they are partially disregarded.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The original page doesn&#39;t change, the ranking factors don&#39;t alter, and not even a little amount of the weight from the original page is transmitted to the temporary links.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Another thing to think about when utilising HTTP redirects is how they may affect performance.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Every redirect adds a few hundredths of a millisecond to the loading time of your page since it requires another HTTP request. While a single redirect is harmless, you should avoid having lengthy redirect chains to prevent user experience degradation and, if at all feasible, lessen the burden on the web server.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\">A 301 redirect would be what? An explanation of the HTTP status code 301</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The HTTP 301 status code indicates that the target resource has a new permanent URL and that any future links to this resource should use the new suggested URLs. Where possible, the link editing clients should update the data on their own to reflect the most recent URL that the server has sent.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">On the server, the URL that you want to permanently redirect traffic to should be listed in the &quot;Location&quot; header field. In this scenario, the user agent can choose the Location field&#39;s value for automated forwarding. In the past, a user agent may and most likely would switch the request method from POST to GET for a later request. Using the 307 status code is advised to prevent changing the request method.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">In two scenarios, this kind of redirection is often&nbsp;used:</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">When purchasing extra domain names, such as when considering the brand name variations, pertinent high-profile domains, or the most frequent misspellings of the site address.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Choosing the link to utilise and show as the default address (for instance, an address without www.).</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\">characteristics of .htaccess</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">On Apache web servers, there is a hidden configuration file called .htaccess that begins with a dot. The directory contains a .htaccess file, which has directives you can use to modify the server settings. The code editor in the file manager, the FTP Protocol, or a text editor installed locally on the computer can all be used to edit .htaccess configuration files.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">You can set up specialised plugins that can automatically configure redirection for various CMS, like WordPress. For instance, you must include the following line in the.htaccess file to configure permanent forwarding with code 301:</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Redirect 301 /old-URL/ http://www.thedomainofcompany.com/new-URL/</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">301 Redirects and Google Officially&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">When do 301 redirects get used? The following situations call for the use of 301 redirects, according Google Webmaster Tools&#39; instructions:</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Altering a domain name or domain. Users who are familiar with your brand and who visit your website frequently will not be confused by a new address.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Several URLs, such as http://example.com/home, http://home.example.com, and http://www.example.com, repeat certain aspects.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">You are combining two sites or replacing an outdated one. Users who access out-of-date pages must be routed to the most recent version.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">John Mueller clarifies that employing the 301 redirect chain should be limited to five links for the Google bot to successfully index your site in a Reddit debate.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Reddit</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">John Mueller also addresses how long it takes for a page to index once 301 redirects are set up in this video. The canonical link is identified by first interpreting code 301 as one of the signals, he added.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">When considering forwarding, consider the following factors:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">internal links;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">sitemap file;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">a set of links leading to the source page.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">If enough positive signals are provided by all of these variables, the new link will only be accepted as canonical for indexing purposes. As a result, updating the site&#39;s current links is just as crucial as setting new redirects. Additionally, it&#39;s critical to get in touch with the website owners of the most relevant backlinks to ask them to update their content. The updated link should be identified as the most up-to-date version with as much clarity and unmistakability as possible. Mueller suggested using the Search Console&#39;s link checking tool to make sure everything is operational.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\">WordPress 301 Redirects Implementing WordPress 301 Redirect</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">How do you set up a 301 redirect? When utilising the WordPress CMS, there are numerous ways to set up a 301 redirect. You are urged to make the appropriate changes to your server&#39;s .htaccess file. Have backups on hand before undertaking any .htaccess tests! To edit .htaccess, you must connect to your website using an FTP programme and open the root directory. In the event that the desired file is not in the root directory:</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">To see if hidden files are displayed, check the FTP client.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The file might not have been produced yet. You may do this by simply opening the Permalinks tab in the WordPress settings and clicking this box. Without changing anything, click &quot;Save Changes.&quot; If no error messages appear, simply update the FTP client. The file should be available.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">If the file is still missing, you can find more patches and more detailed instructions here.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">All that is left to be done is to open the.htaccess file in any text editor and make the necessary changes. For reliability and convenience of use, it is recommended that you add new lines at the end of the file. Consider this:</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">RewriteEngine On</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Redirect 301 /old-version/ http://siteofcompany.com/new-version/</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">A number of WordPress plugins, including Redirection, Yoast, All in One SEO Pack, Rank Math, and analogues, can be used to set up 301 redirects. Our post, Setting Up Yoast SEO vs. All In One, explains how to achieve this.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Note regarding 404</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Additionally, John Mueller stated that there are guidelines for handling the 404 error code using 301 and 302 redirection.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Twitter</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">You must first identify all the pages that return the 404 result before you can utilise redirect codes to enhance the user experience when navigating to non-existent pages. To do this, go to the 404 area under Coverage in the Google search Console. It is advised that you carry this this routinely so that consumers always land on the most recent pages and don&#39;t waste time on default error pages.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Describe a 302 redirect: A Definition of the HTTP 302 Status Code&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The HTTP 302 status code signifies that the target resource has temporarily migrated and is now accessible via a different URL. It is advised that the client keep using the current request URL as the primary URL because redirection could change in the future.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">In the initial implementation of HTTP, the 302 status code returned the value &quot;Temporarily Moved,&quot; however in HTTP 1.1, as specified in the RFC 2616 specification, code 302 now returns the value &quot;Found.&quot; A 302 redirect, to put it simply, is a redirect that tells search engines that a page has temporarily been moved but may one day be accessible at the original location.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The weight of the original link is not transferred when employing 302 redirects, in contrast to 301. 302 redirects in total are used for A/B testing, site maintenance, and updating.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The Distinctive Characteristics of 301 and 302 Redirects</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">A permanent 301 redirect and a temporary 302 redirect differ primarily in two ways. The Google algorithm displays the updated location in the search results as well as the weight of the original link for links with specified permanent redirects. The original location will continue to show up in the search results even though temporary redirection, such as 302, do not receive the weight from the source links. This is so that it is evident from the redirect specification 302 that it is only a temporary page replacement before returning to the original location.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Utilizing 302 Redirects: The &quot;When&quot; question.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Webmasters often strive to avoid using a 302 redirect unless absolutely required.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">However, there are a few situations where this redirect will be useful:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">web page design or functionality A/B testing;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">for gathering user or customer comments on a new page without affecting the ranking of the entire site;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">when you are working on changing a web page or a piece of the site without degrading the user experience.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">302 Redirects: J. Mueller</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">This type of redirection is frequently applied inadvertently. For instance, it is sometimes utilised as if it were permanent, which is against the intent and intent of code 302.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">In this video, John Mueller discussed Google&#39;s approach to similar situations. The previous, original link will still exist when the search bot sees a redirect via the 302 code since it will assume that this is a transient phenomena. However, if the bot notices the same direction repeatedly, it will believe that a mistake was made and that a permanent redirection was intended. The new, or final, link URL will be displayed in the search results in this instance since 302 redirects will be processed similarly to 301 redirects.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Redirects Done Wrong</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Homepage getting linked to 404 error pages</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">John Mueller criticises this strategy as an example of webmasters&#39; laziness because the search engine still considers these links to be illegitimate.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Twitter</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Setting an appropriate redirect and working on a memorable 404 page are necessary to manage such requests, offer visitors similar content, and give them the option of using the site search or other navigation choices. Alternative sanctions may be imposed.</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Redirection of Errors for Mobile Pages</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The desktop site should mirror its mobile equivalent if a sub-domain is utilised for the mobile version. For example:</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">A correct redirection form is from &ldquo;companysite/about&rdquo; to &ldquo;mobile.companysite/about&rdquo;;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;whilst</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">An incorrect redirection form is from &ldquo;companysite/about&rdquo; to &ldquo;mobile.companysite&rdquo;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">AMP pages must adhere to the same norm as their canonical pages in terms of their URL structure. For instance, redirecting from &ldquo;companysite/about&rdquo; to &ldquo;amp.companysite/about&rdquo; or companysite/amp/about is the right way but not to &ldquo;optimized.companysite/ourteam&rdquo;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">It&#39;s crucial to keep in mind that AMP versions of the main pages will take some time to develop for sites that employ the technology when upgrading the structure or content. However, it is advised that you set up the relevant redirects as soon as the primary content is updated to guarantee that people reach the most recent version of the AMP page. For instance, from the companysite.com/amp/old page to the companysite.com/amp/new.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">For instance, if the page does not have a mobile version, we advise not redirecting it at all to prevent confusion and fines. In the case of 404 pages, the mobile version should also link to the 404 page if there isn&#39;t a desktop version.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">If you do not have an adapted version, you can configure redirecting mobile clients to the AMP version of the page. Codes 301 and 302 can be used to make redirects permanent or temporary, respectively.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Excessive Redirection</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">This error happens when the redirection chain loops. For instance, you might have put up the page redirection and then forgotten about it. A reverse redirection from the second page back to the first has to be put up after a while. As a result, an error message is returned by an infinite loop.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Redirecting using the Meta Description&#39;s Instructions</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Including a similar directive in the meta-tag is another technique to reroute visitors from one website to another:</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&lt;meta http-equiv=&rdquo;refresh&rdquo; content=&rdquo;0;url=http://companysite.com/new-URL/&rdquo; /&gt;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Although John Mueller acknowledged that such redirection works and this is not expressly forbidden by Google, he also pointed out a number of disadvantages of this strategy.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Twitter</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The user experience is particularly compromised, and HTTP request processing times lengthen. The same is true for JavaScript redirection.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Miscellaneous</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The most frequent mistakes made when configuring permanent redirection include:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">extensive and needless redirection chains;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">utilising the incorrect redirection method;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">internal forwarding whilst the links are not updated;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">sending users to stale pages or content;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">sending users to pages that don&#39;t have a 200 response code.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Examples of Configuration and Use</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\">Heading to HTTPS from HTTP</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Apache</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Navigate to the directory where it is installed by logging into the Apache server;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Create a backup copy of the httpd.conf file by opening the conf folder;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Launching vi or any other editor to view httpd.conf;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The mod rewrite.so module must be loaded;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Mod rewrite.soCopy; LoadModule rewrite module;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Remove any comments from the line above;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">the following words to the file&#39;s end;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">RewriteEngine On;RewriteCond %{HTTPS} off;RewriteRule (.*) https://%{HTTP_HOST}%{REQUEST_URI};</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Restart the Apache webserver.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Nginx&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Log in to the Nginx webserver;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Backup the server directive file (nginx.conf or default.conf);</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Add the following to the server directive;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">return 301 https://$server_name$request_uri;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Save the changes and restart the server.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Cloudflare&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Log in to Cloudflare and select your site;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Go to the SSL/ TLS tab and open the &ldquo;Edge Certificates&rdquo; section;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Enable the &ldquo;Always use HTTPS&rdquo; option.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>cPanel&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Verify that the hosting company offers SSL and that your website has the option activated.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Open the .htaccess file in the manager after logging into cPanel;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Add the following text to the end of the file;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">RewriteEngine On;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">RewriteCond %{HTTPS} off;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">RewriteRule (.*) https://%{HTTP_HOST}%{REQUEST_URI};</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Save the changes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>SUCURI</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Go to&nbsp; HTTPS/SSL tab;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Then select &ldquo;Full HTTPS&rdquo; in SSL mode;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Select &ldquo;HTTPS only site&rdquo; in&nbsp; Protocol Redirection settings;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Save the changes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">www, / and other</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">A new rule needs to be added to the.htaccess file; you can do this however you like, using FTP, SSH, or the control panel.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">When you&#39;ve located and opened the required file, add the following code:</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">To avoid displaying www in the address (i.e. https://companysite.com)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">RewriteEngine On</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">RewriteCond %{HTTP_HOST} ^www.companysite\\.com$ [NC]</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">RewriteRule ^(.*)$ http://companysite.com/$1 [R=301,L]</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">To display www in an address (i.e. https://www.companysite.com)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">RewriteEngine On</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">RewriteCond %{HTTP_HOST} ^companysite\\.com$ [NC]</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">RewriteRule ^(.*)$ http://www.companysite.com/$1 [R=301,L]</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">To avoid using&nbsp; / at the end of a URL (i.e. https://companysite.com/page)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">RewriteCond %{HTTP_HOST} (.*)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">RewriteCond %{REQUEST_URI} /$ [NC]</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">RewriteRule ^(.*)(/)$ $1 [L,R=301]</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">To use / at the end of a URL (i.e. https://companysite.com/page/)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">RewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} !-f</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">RewriteCond %{REQUEST_URI} !(.*)/$</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">RewriteRule ^(.*[^/])$ $1/ [L,R=301]</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">To remove the extra slashes in the address (i.e. companysite.com///page)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">RewriteCond %{REQUEST_URI} ^(.*)//(.*)$</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">RewriteRule . %1/%2 [R=301,L]</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">To remove extra dashes in the address (i.e. companysite.com/page&mdash;1)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">RewriteCond %{REQUEST_URI} ^(.*)&ndash;(.*)$</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">RewriteRule. %1-%2 [R=301,L]<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', 'A 301 redirect indicates that a page has moved to a new URL permanently, whereas a 302 redirect indicates that the transfer is temporary.', '301-vs-302-redirects-for-seo-complete-guide', '301 vs 302 redirect for seo, complete guide 301 vs 302 redirect, 301 redirect, 301 vs 302 redirect seo, 302 redirect htaccess,', 'Ayushi', '2022-11-25 22:39:46', '2022-11-25 22:41:29');
INSERT INTO `blog` (`id`, `blog_title`, `blog_category`, `image1`, `image2`, `description`, `description1`, `blog_url`, `tags`, `author_name`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(52, 'Email Marketing: Ultimate Guide 2022', 'Email Marketing', 'Email Marketing Ultimate Guide .png', NULL, '<p style=\"text-align:justify\">New marketing strategies have been emerging since the turn of the twenty-first century, like mushrooms after rain. <strong>Email marketing</strong> is still effective, offering a staggering 4400% ROI and an average subscription value of $48.87. Companies need to adapt to the worldwide shift toward digitalization and the constantly shifting demands of consumers as they enter the third decade with COVID-19 in tow. The secret to keeping on top of your game next year is excellent email management.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\">How come email marketing?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The use of digital services is becoming more common among consumers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">This year alone, the number of internet users is expected to expand at a rate that will far beyond that of previous years. 40 million new users joined the internet this year in the SEA area alone, compared to 100 million between 2015 and 2019. One in three of these users began using it as a result of COVID-19 lockdowns forcing them to alter their way of life.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The use of digital services is becoming more common among consumers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Source: Temasek and Bain, e-Commerce, Google SEA 2020: Moving forward quickly and resolutely, November 2020.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">As schools and other learning institutions shifted toward using digital classrooms, education topped the list. Groceries and other essentials for daily living came in second as consumers choose to have their products delivered right to their homes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Digital adoption will continue to grow.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">If you want to connect and engage these new audiences, there is a chance as consumers become savvy and have a digital environment that meets their requirements.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">By assisting them in making judgments about purchases and other positive activities that are significant to businesses, email marketing will likely continue to play a significant role.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Today&#39;s environment makes it tough to overestimate email marketing&#39;s effectiveness. This manual will teach you:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The importance of <strong>email marketing</strong> for your campaign.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The main advantages of email advertising in 2022.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">How to create and expand your email databases in 2022.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">When preparing your 2022 marketing strategies, things to watch out for.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Statistics to Consider</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Email marketing will still be a successful strategy for companies trying to connect with clients in 2022. You can structure your email marketing campaigns for the upcoming year using these statistics.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">By 2025, there will be more than 376 billion active emails sent and received each day (Statista)</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Compared to Facebook advertisements or TV commercials, 86% of people prefer receiving marketing emails. (HubSpot)</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Emails that are automatically generated can bring in 320% more money than manual emails. Campaign Watch</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">59% of consumers claim that emails affect their decision to make a purchase. (HubSpot)</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">An email marketing ROI of 4400% is possible. (Clutch.io)</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Social media marketing has a lower conversion rate than email marketing (Entrepreneur)</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">The click-through rate of emails can improve by 158% by including a social sharing button. (Entrepreneur)</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Over 90% of consumers are interested in receiving promotional emails. (Marketingsherpa)</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Millennials use email for more than 30 hours a week (study by Adobe)</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Over 50.7% of consumers&#39; purchasing decisions are influenced by marketing emails (SaleCycle)</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">A flawless sending experience when combined with an efficient <strong>email marketing strategy</strong> can produce fantastic results in 2022 and beyond. Email marketing continues to be a key component of meeting these objectives, whether you&#39;re wanting to expand your client base, crowdfund the money you need to start your next dream project or spread the word about a new product launch.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Make a drip email campaign.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">If your material falls short of expectations, all your efforts to develop a sizable subscriber list and select a collection of templates will be in useless. Your writing is very important. You can nurture your leads by providing pertinent, helpful material that your subscribers will find interesting. Fair enough, you can&#39;t expect your readers to continue to be active subscribers if you don&#39;t consistently share excellent stuff.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Email drip campaigns are a powerful tool that email marketers have at their disposal, which is fortunate. It basically means that a segmented group of subscribers will receive a series of emails automatically. The material is prepared in advance, and it is then sent at the appropriate moment using email marketing software (more on that later). Frequently, particular occurrences, such as shopping cart abandonment, will serve as a trigger.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>POPULAR EMAIL DRIP CAMPAIGN KINDS</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Here are a few of the most typical objectives you can have when developing an email drip campaign.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>a greeting sequence</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">A welcome sequence needs to be developed for every brand. This kind of drip campaign is sent to subscribers shortly after they sign up for your mailing list, and you usually start it by sincerely thanking them for doing so.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Asking them to confirm their email address is another smart move. This extra step can help you improve delivery rates and lessen the likelihood of having to eliminate inactive customers a few months down the road.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">After thanking them and verifying their email address, you could, for instance, send an email asking them to read your most recent blog article as a call to action. Basically, you want to take advantage of this as an opportunity to win over new subscribers and convert them into paying clients.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>A short course</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">You can choose to distribute your lead magnets over the course of a few emails to create a type of drip campaign, even though many lead magnets are available as one-time digital downloads like a cheat sheet or checklist. With this strategy, over the course of a few days or perhaps weeks, you&#39;ll send a number of emails containing useful information.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">This kind of organization is also appropriate when you&#39;re providing a webinar as a lead magnet. After inviting them via email to attend, you may also remind them and follow up with them via email to highlight the main takeaways from the event (in other words, share more valuable content).</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Shopping basket emptied</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">For online stores, abandoned cart recovery emails are essential. Online shops can recover some of those lost purchases with the aid of an automated abandoned cart recovery email series.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">To keep your brand in their minds and to remind them of the things still in their basket, you&#39;ll normally send the first email in this campaign within a few hours. Depending on the response, you can either send a thank-you email for their purchase or a second email with a possible discount coupon to remind clients to finish the transaction.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">For instance, Grammarly provides a staggering $75 off of its annual premium subscriptions. While a significant reduction is not required, it should still be enticing enough to be useful. It&#39;s quite improbable that a 5% discount will work.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">If you&#39;re going to give a reward, you should also specify a deadline, much like Grammarly has. By doing this, you convey a sense of urgency and encourage speedy conversion.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">There are abandoned cart plugins that you may utilize in addition to the capability that the majority of <strong>email marketing</strong> systems should provide to assist with shopping cart abandonment. There is no justification for not following up on abandoned carts as some of them are even free to use.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Cross-selling or upselling</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">It need not be the end of the road once a customer has made a purchase. Additionally, you can design an email drip campaign to promote upselling and cross-selling. You can do this to get repeat business from clients.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">To achieve this, you might, for instance, suggest pertinent accessories before their order is dispatched. As an alternative, you can send them offers for new products when you know it&#39;s time for a new order if the item is consumable, such as dog food.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>5 Important Benefits of Email Marketing</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Many businesses neglect email in favour of paid search, social media marketing, and search engine optimization. The beauty of email marketing is in how easy it is to understand and use, which can provide your company with a competitive edge. Other advantages of putting in place a strong email marketing plan in 2022 include:</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">1. Developing enduring relationships with customers</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Email continues to be the most personalized marketing method for reaching both current and potential customers. It helps create dependable connections and fuels your retention efforts.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">2. Taking Authority Positions</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Email is a direct line to potential clients and customers. By disseminating top-notch educational material, you can solidify your position as an industry leader. Meanwhile, credibility may be established and brand recognition can be raised by consistently disseminating useful information.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">3. Increasing Competitive Advantage</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Small firms may compete with big organizations by putting advanced email management techniques into practise. Regardless of the size of the firm, email has an identical chance of converting a lead.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">4. Making the most of time and money</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Email marketing is a cost-effective method for converting and keeping customers because of its extraordinarily high ROI.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Email conversion rates are reportedly 40 times higher than those of social media sites like Facebook and Twitter.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Our collection of pre-made templates guarantees that you&#39;ll never have to worry about creating the ideal message from the beginning while allowing you the freedom to modify the visuals and copy to fit your company&#39;s requirements. You may focus on other elements of your marketing plan while saving time using email automation alternatives.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align:justify\">5. Aiding Other Marketing Techniques</h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Your other marketing initiatives, like SMM and SEO, might benefit from a well-structured <strong>email marketing strategy</strong>. Emails featuring social sharing buttons encourage social media promotion of your business&#39;s goods and services. In the meanwhile, adding helpful connections to your website will drive more visitors there.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">In conclusion, emails are a very effective marketing tool since they can reach the appropriate audience at the appropriate moment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">You need a list of recipients before you send out your first marketing email.<strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Here are a few strategies for building a strong and healthy customer list:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Create compelling lead magnets. While it could be difficult to persuade people to sign up for your newsletters, providing leads like Ebooks, Swipe files, case studies, etc. may help you increase the number of people that subscribe. A powerful tactic for increasing signups is to use a strong lead magnet.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Improve the homepage of your website to boost email signups.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Offer excellent material in exchange for an email address on your landing pages and in your paid search advertisements. This includes case studies, videos, white papers, and guides.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Use social media to gather email addresses from your followers by holding a contest or giveaway. Promoting websites with useful material can be done using social media accounts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Implement useful exit popups. Just before a visitor exits your website, a message with an offer and an email sharing form can appear on the screen.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Make the revealing of an address necessary when a consumer makes a purchase or completes a contact form on your website.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Add a link to your email signature so that customers may sign up and leave their addresses on a landing page. Do this for all of your workers as well.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">In order to help readers become brand ambassadors, including social sharing and &quot;email to friend&quot; buttons in your emails.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Post QR codes within your brick-and-mortar businesses for rapid signups to collect addresses offline. You can give members that join up for membership discounts at the register.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Once you&#39;ve built up a sizable email list, make sure to keep it clean. While customers may decide they no longer want your material, addresses might be abandoned. Your mails thereafter bounce or land in spam bins. You may maintain a good reputation and keep bounce rates down by eliminating such addresses. By removing undesirable addresses for the health of your list, Enginemailer&#39;s Automated Email Cleansing service assists you in achieving this.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Automate your messages by using a mailing list program.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">An email list is crucial for more than simply your <strong>email marketing campaigns</strong>. You can&#39;t get a list this large of contacts with any other marketing strategy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">You only have sporadic followers on social media. You may instantly lose all of your contacts if a bug caused your accounts to vanish. People&#39;s social media profiles aren&#39;t as secure as their email addresses, which can be used for decades.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>2022 Email Marketing Techniques to Use</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Your email marketing strategy might be strengthened with these strategies next year.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Embrace video</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Email is not an exception to how impressively popular videos are becoming across all platforms. 85% of companies utilize videos as a marketing strategy today. People like watching videos. They provide educational and entertaining content without consuming a lot of the viewer&#39;s time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">You may use videos to establish an emotional connection with your customers and foster their loyalty and trust. A video in an email can also enhance the open and click-through rates by 19% and 65%, respectively.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Put email marketing automation to use</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Email marketing automation may greatly enhance your strategy in addition to reducing campaign expenses and freeing up time. Here are some strategies to think about in 2022:</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Check the output from your marketing automation solutions to verify quality.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Create consumer profiles with AI-powered tools using data about their online behavior, social media presence, and purchasing preferences. You can use this information to create automated emails.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Utilize automatic re-engagement emails to pique your past clients&#39; interest without coming off as pushy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">To make email administration easier, implement an email response management system.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">You may streamline your email marketing strategy by gathering crucial client data with the use of artificial intelligence and machine learning. Email automation isn&#39;t simply a great feature; it&#39;s a must in 2022.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Put email marketing automation to use</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Boost Your Material Your content needs to demonstrate that you care about your audience. Make your discussions and emails more insightful and timely in 2022.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Think about using dynamic material that changes based on consumer behavior. Platforms for email marketing can help with that. Personalized content used to nurture leads now results in a 20% boost in sales opportunities.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Be as succinct and direct as you can in your email text. Due to a shortage of time, the average reader&#39;s attention span is increasing shorter every year.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Remove all words and phrases that have no purpose.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">To get the best click-through rates, A/B test the CTA text and placement.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Per paragraph, just one thought is allowed.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">To communicate concise, unambiguous concepts, use bullet points.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Be very watchful with your grammar and punctuation.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Throughout all emails, maintain the tone and voice of your brand.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Use expressions that take advantage of FOMO (Fear of Missing Out).</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">To connect with the reader more personally, go toward a conversational style.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Make sure the footers in your email templates have the essential Calls-To-Actions that you want readers to use.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Bold text is outperforming photos.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Colors, movies, and visuals should elicit a feeling.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Due to the severe eye strain, people suffer when using smartphones, muted colour palettes are becoming more and more popular.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Emails with 3D pictures are becoming more popular.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Utilize emojis and GIFs.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Avoid making the text overly crowded for readers on mobile devices.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">All other aspects of your marketing strategies are essentially meaningless without high-quality content. Therefore, it is essential to devote time and resources to enhance its integrity.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Particular Focus on Performance Reports</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Analyzing your efforts is crucial as you gain from your successful <strong>email marketing strategy</strong>. You can approach the 4400% ROI by tracking the KPIs and dynamically changing your strategy. This can entail experimenting with various send timings or tailoring your material to a certain audience.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">You can select particular email metrics to monitor and use analysis software to get knowledge about the future of your campaign based on your marketing objectives.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Put the customer experience first</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Due to COVID-19&#39;s increased online consumer traffic in 2021, businesses were forced to step up their marketing initiatives. Customers became more critical of the experience as a result of lockdowns, which made them spend their spare time online.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">All of your email marketing initiatives in 2022 ought to be created with the best possible user experience in mind. The recipient should have a highly customized and customer-focused contact, whether you are collecting addresses, sending follow-up emails, or requesting comments.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Due to recent events, 88% of consumers now want businesses to strengthen their digital operations. You don&#39;t want to disappoint them.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Personalization of Email</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The next step is to use the required client data you&#39;ve gathered to individually and specifically target each subscriber with your digital marketing campaigns.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">By creating a sense of connection with your readers, email personalization tactics boost the effectiveness of your messaging.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Marketing professionals employ a variety of personalization methods, such as:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">utilizing customized subject lines.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">sending suggestions for products based on past purchasing information.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">customizing pictures.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Make specialized offers.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Personalization is based on behavior.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Personalized abandoned cart notifications for every subscriber.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Pay close attention to email rules</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Customers benefit from email regulations because they make it clear to them how and why their information is utilized.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The right of the subscriber to receive emails and the right to decide whether they wish to hear from you are protected by laws like the GDPR and CAN-SPAM.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Testing A/B</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Using this method, you can test which email version performs better by sending it to two separate email list segments.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">You may learn what works for you by comparing the results, analyzing the data, and reviewing the reports. A/B testing can be used to examine even little modifications, such as a subject line tweak or an additional grouping, to determine whether they had an effect on open rates.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Timing Emails</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">While there are no hard-and-fast guidelines for when to send an email, one should be aware of the audience being targeted and how they use the internet.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The next step is to choose the optimum day and time of the week to send your marketing emails once this has been recognized. It&#39;s also vital to note that this may fully change depending on the types of businesses and market niches.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The most successful days to send your marketing emails, according to the majority of statistics, are Tuesday, Wednesday, and Thursday.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Segmenting a list</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Your list can be divided using email segmentation tactics depending on a variety of factors, including demographics, psychographics, interests, opinions, website/internet behavior, purchasing patterns, preferences, and more.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">You may deliver specific, distinctive content that is pertinent to each of your consumers using a segmented list. Overall, it improves the ROI and increases the effectiveness of an email marketing campaign.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Consider using mobile responsive designs.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">In 2022 and beyond, mobile responsive layouts won&#39;t simply be significant; they&#39;ll be absolutely necessary.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Since most consumers prefer to read their emails on their mobile devices, it&#39;s critical that your message appears beautiful and works properly on all gadgets, including tablets, iPhones, Android phones, and other mobile devices.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Following Your Campaigns</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The most neglected but essential phase in email marketing campaign tracking is frequently ignored.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Use data like open rate, CTR, bounce rate, unsubscribe rate, conversion rate, etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">This is a great opportunity to discover the sweet spots that draw in your audience in addition to helping you identify any weaknesses in your methods.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Having a Strong <strong>Email Marketing Strategy</strong> for the New Year</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Email marketing will still be prevalent in 2022. You can obtain a competitive advantage and boost the financial performance of your business by adapting your email management strategies to the most recent trends.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">To get more insights on local marketing and marketing ideas for small businesses, <a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/\">stay updated.</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Looking out for the<a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/\"> <strong>best digital marketing agency in Navi Mumbai</strong></a>, reach out to us in order to grow your business.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', 'Email marketing is still effective, offering a staggering 4400% ROI and an average subscription value of $48.87. Companies need to adapt to the worldwide shift toward digitalization and the constantly shifting demands of consumers as they enter the third decade with COVID-19 in tow.', 'email-marketing-ultimate-guide', 'email marketing, email marketing ultimate guide, email marketing strategy, email marketing tips, email marketing statistics, email marketing tricks', 'Ayushi', '2022-11-25 23:59:35', '2022-11-26 00:02:34'),
(53, 'Keyword Cannibalization: What is it & How to Fix it', 'SEO', 'keyword-cannibalization.webp', NULL, '<p>Your rankings may suffer from keyword cannibalization if you optimize your content for related search phrases because you&#39;ll be &quot;devouring&quot; your own chances to rank in Google! It&#39;s likely that your content may begin to compete with itself, especially as your site expands.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The majority of digital marketing teams use keyword optimization to raise the visibility of their content in search results. More keywords, in theory, equate to higher optimization.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In order to improve your chances of ranking, it can be tempting to employ the same keywords on many sites.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If your postings are in competition with each other for the same term, this tactic can backfire.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Consider this: You won&#39;t know which link to click on if you&#39;re looking for &quot;the greatest running shoes&quot; and you come across two articles from the same publisher with these terms in the headline.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In this article, I&#39;ll discuss how keyword cannibalism can harm SEO, how to spot it, and what you can do to stop it.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What is the term &quot;keyword cannibalization&quot;?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>If you have multiple blog posts or articles on your website that can rank for the same Google search term, this is known as keyword cannibalization. Either because you optimized them for the same keyphrase or because the topics they cover are too similar. Similar search keywords are eaten up by posts and articles you optimize for them, decreasing their chances of ranking. For any given query, Google typically displays no more than 1 or 2 results from the same domain. If your domain has a lot of authority, you might earn 3.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Why is keyword cannibalism detrimental to SEO?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Cannibalizing your own keywords puts you in a Google search engine ranking battle with yourself. Let&#39;s imagine you wrote two articles on the same subject. In that circumstance, Google is unable to determine which article ought to appear first for a certain query. In addition, crucial elements like backlinks and CTR are spread out among multiple postings rather than just one. They will most likely both rank lower as a result. As a result, if you optimize a post for a focus keyword you&#39;ve already used, our SEO analysis will display a red bullet.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, if you optimize posts for emphasis keywords that are nearly the same but not quite the same, keyword cannibalism may also happen. For instance, I discussed the topic of readability as a ranking criteria in two posts. However, the post titled &quot;Does readability rank?&quot; was targeted for the keyword &quot;does readability rank,&quot; whereas the one titled &quot;Readability ranks!&quot; was enhanced for the focus keyword &quot;readability ranking factor.&quot; Although they had a slightly varied slant, the posts were essentially identical. It is challenging for Google to determine which of the two articles is more crucial.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Did you see the same article recently? Yes, this cannibalization problem has been resolved by this point, however, we kept this example to serve as an example.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>How can you spot it?</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>It&#39;s simple to determine if your website exhibits keyword cannibalism. You merely do a search for your website using any exact keyword you believe may return more than one result. &nbsp;Google &quot;site:yoast.com readability ranks&quot;;&nbsp; The first two results are the pieces would possibly have been&nbsp;cannibalized.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Searching for &quot;site:domain.com&quot; You can quickly determine whether you have keyword cannibalism by searching for &quot;keyword.&quot; By entering the same query into Google (using a private browser or a local search result checker like https://valentin.app/), you can confirm your findings. What pages from your website do you see in the search results, and where do they appear? Of course, it&#39;s not a problem if two of your pages for the same keyword are ranked #1 and #2. Do you, however, see your articles, say, on positions 7 and 8? Then, it&#39;s time to resolve the situation!</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>How Do One Find Cannibalized Keywords?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Don&#39;t worry if you think that your website may be using the same keywords more than once. By following a few straightforward procedures, you can locate and solve them with ease.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>You can use the following methods to look for keyword cannibalization.</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h4>Look Up Information on Your Website</h4>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>An easy technique to find keyword cannibalization is to seek up relevant search terms for your industry.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If your business provides digital marketing services, for instance, and you routinely post articles on SEO and marketing-related issues, you might Google some of the keywords you frequently use.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>These might present themselves as &quot;SEO methods&quot; or &quot;simple marketing advise.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Such a search returns all websites that are rated for this inquiry. See if any of your posts are in competition with one another for a position.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h4>Create a matrix of keywords.</h4>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Using a spreadsheet or keyword mapping tool, you may compile a list of all the main URLs on your website together with the terms related to each page to determine whether or not keyword cannibalism is taking place. Even while listing everything could be time-consuming, it&#39;s also a pretty thorough technique of looking for duplicates, especially if your site has amassed a lot of pages over time. Look closely at your main pages to check for any duplicate entries that would indicate term cannibalization is taking place.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h4>Site Search tailored to Google</h4>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Entering the name of your website before the search term will help you detect keyword cannibalization more quickly. The Google search results seem as follows:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Keyword cannibalization: Google</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Use of External Tools-To make things simpler and obtain thorough data for better keyword planning, you can also use keyword research tools like Ubersuggest. This can speed up the process of identifying keyword cannibalization and lower the time, cost, and effort needed to remove competitor pages from your website.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Solving keyword cannibalization</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We have a thorough post by Joost that describes how to identify and address cannibalization problems on your site. The four steps you should follow to tackle this kind of problem are clearly described:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Inspect your content.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Perform a content analysis</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Choose which to keep.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Act: combine, remove, and redirect</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>You can choose which articles to keep, merge, or eliminate with the help of the first two steps. Combining and eliminating content will frequently be the acting part; nevertheless, improving internal linking on your site is also important:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Combine or merge articles</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>When two pieces have the same readership and essentially convey the same message, you should combine them. Rewrite the two posts to create one magnificent, epic piece. That will improve your ranks (Google loves long, well-written articles) and eliminate term cannibalization.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With our two blogs on readability as a ranking factor, we actually did just that. You will ultimately delete one of the two articles and modify the other. Clone one of the posts using the Yoast Duplicate Post plugin, then continues from there. Remember to always redirect the post you delete to the one you maintain; don&#39;t just hit the delete button!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you&#39;re having trouble with that, Yoast SEO Premium can be of assistance: It makes it simple to create redirects!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Upgrading internal linking</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>By creating an effective internal linking structure, you may assist Google in determining which content is the most important. The posts that are most significant to you should be linked to posts that are less important. Google will be able to determine which links you want to appear at the top of search results by clicking on them.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Your keyword cannibalization issues might be partially resolved by your internal linking structure. Consider which article is most significant to you, then link from the lesser-importance long-tail articles to that article. In my essay about ranking using cornerstone content, I go into greater detail about how to do this.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Develop a Strategic Keyword Plan</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>If you&#39;ve been involved in digital marketing for some time, you are aware of the importance of keyword strategy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The positive news? To the point where there is no competition and problematic overlap, one of the easiest methods to avoid keyword cannibalization is to fine-tune your chosen keyword approach.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This basically entails optimizing various pages to target various keywords and search queries.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You can therefore optimize each page for a different but related search term like &quot;digital marketing strategy,&quot; &quot;marketing strategies,&quot; &quot;SEO for beginners,&quot; etc. rather than having five sites competing for the search term &quot;SEO advice.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>By doing so, you may stay on topic while providing unique material for a range of relevant search terms for your sector.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Here are some paid and free resources for keyword planning and research:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Ubersuggest</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Google Trends</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Answer the public</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Search Console by Google</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Moz Keyword Explorer</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Cannibalization of keywords and online stores</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Now that product pages are targeting comparable keywords, you might be concerned if you own an online store. It makes it logical for online stores to have many pages for similar products. In this situation, it&#39;s crucial to think carefully about the site&#39;s structure. A smart move is to link back to your category page, which you should rank well, from each product page. Additionally, keep a look out for outdated product pages which might potentially replace more crucial pages and delete and redirect those &mdash; Yoast SEO Premium&#39;s helpful redirect manager could make that easier!</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Growing websites will be affected by keyword cannibalism.</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>The risk that keyword cannibalism may affect your website increases as it grows. You&#39;ll unknowingly write essays on your favorite subjects that are very similar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>That is what also occurred to me. You should periodically examine the terms you want to rank for most. Make sure to determine if you are keyword cannibalizing. You&#39;ll probably need to occasionally update the layout of your website or rewrite a few articles.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Five Steps to Avoid Keyword Cannibalization</h3>\r\n\r\n<h4>Blend Content</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Consider consolidating all of the content from two websites that perform comparable functions, such as one that recommends healthy dog food and another that identifies unhealthy dog food.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>While it won&#39;t always be the best option, combining material can frequently make things easier while also improving your website&#39;s search engine optimization.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Discard Content</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Although it is extreme, you might want to think about completely eliminating problematic web content&mdash;especially if it isn&#39;t longer pertinent to your website. Delete the material if your company has expanded and that previous, lesser professional, individual blog post employing a certain set of keywords is still showing up above your targeted site content. Both the issue and the substance are gone if they were ever-present.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Eliminate Keywords</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Removal of a keyword is always a possibility if one wishes to keep certain content for other reasons and the former&rsquo;s presence isn&#39;t essential. The good thing about this method is that it is simple and easy to use, even though manual solutions are usually longer and harder. Change the internal linking.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you have web material that links to other information on your website, you may be able to improve the connections themselves. Links generate importance for search&nbsp;engines such as Google, thus if you connect to some other piece of content or website, the linked content may be ranked higher by the search engine.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Try expanding or altering your website&#39;s internal linking so that less significant content links to the material you wish to emphasize and prioritize. You are telling the search engine results page (SERP) that the linked material should take precedence by doing this. Being successful on SERP is still crucial.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>Requests to Change Inbound Links</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Although it will be one of the most challenging cannibalization forms&nbsp;to handle, it can be crucial. How many other individuals have linked back to your content is a feature that SEO takes into account when ranking search results. If you conduct a search on your website, you can discover that one of the factors that contribute to less significant content continuing to rank higher than your more recent, relevant content is the building of links from other websites.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You can use software to track backlinks if you have the resources and the time to do so, especially if the websites with which the connections are associated are very powerful ones. After that, you can get in touch with the webmasters to ask them to modify or remove the links. In the ideal scenario, they will swap the outdated links you don&#39;t want for the fresh ones you want to favour, which will really improve your SEO ranking.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>Make Comprehensive Pages</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Content teams may decide to divide some topics into multiple posts because they appear too complicated to be covered in a single blog post.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For instance, &quot;how to make money blogging&quot; is a difficult topic, hence you frequently see several entries addressing various aspects of the issue.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A fast Google search for &quot;how to make money blogging&quot; yields three different outcomes. One discusses blogging for novices, the second discusses monetizing your site in 2021, and the third discusses the challenges of timing blog monetization.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Imagine that these were all from your site rather than from three different sites.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This leads to a lot of unneeded competition because the majority of these deal with concepts that are similar. Additionally, keyword cannibalization occurs because the majority of them rank for comparable search terms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Instead of publishing a unique blog post for each query, the audience might have, you can prevent this by developing a single comprehensive page that covers all the pertinent subtopics.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As you can target long-tail keywords, include pertinent headers, include several search queries on a single page, and avoid competing with yourself, this is better for SEO.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Consider including a clickable table of contents so readers can quickly find the portions they need because this could make for a very long blog post.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>Conclusion</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>When it comes to determining search rankings, modern search algorithms are significantly more intelligent and discriminating.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The key to ranking well on search engines is always going to be having quality material, and avoiding keyword cannibalization can help you better highlight and draw attention to your intended content.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A few years ago, individuals thought that filling their content with keywords and utilizing the same keyword on multiple pages would help it rank higher. This is no longer accurate, though.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You are now forced to compete with yourself and reduce your success because several pages are ranking for the same keywords and search queries.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Instead, it is much preferable to concentrate on focused keywords for certain content, give subjects precedence over keyword stuffing, and develop thorough landing pages rather than brief blog entries.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This may help you rank higher in search engine results, which will eventually help you reach a wider audience organically.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It is extremely simple to correct keyword cannibalizing, even if you have already encountered it. Reconsider your SEO alternatives, remove articles that raise competition but don&#39;t advance your marketing objectives, and concentrate on combining competing material whenever it is possible.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To get more insights on local marketing and marketing ideas for small businesses, <a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/blog/\" target=\"_blank\">stay updated.</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Looking out for the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/\">best digital marketing agency in Navi Mumbai</a>, reach out to us in order to grow your business. &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', 'Don\'t let your website become a battleground for keywords! Avoid the chaos of keyword cannibalization and keep your search engine rankings strong. Discover how now.', 'keyword-cannibalizations-what-is-it-and-how-to-fix-it', 'keyword cannibalization, cannibalization seo, seo keyword cannibalization, content cannibalization, keyword cannibalization in seo', 'Ayushi', '2023-02-21 20:41:58', '2023-02-21 22:09:28');
INSERT INTO `blog` (`id`, `blog_title`, `blog_category`, `image1`, `image2`, `description`, `description1`, `blog_url`, `tags`, `author_name`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(54, 'Mobile SEO: Complete Guide', 'SEO', 'mobile-seo-complete-guide.webp', NULL, '<p>The process of optimising your website for mobile devices involves making sure it looks nice and works properly on mobile devices. When you use mobile SEO, users will have a positive experience on your site because it looks great on all devices, regardless of screen size.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Consumers currently use mobile devices for 76% of their shopping, and as smart devices become more widely available, this percentage is only anticipated to rise.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Mobile SEO: An exhaustive manual for mobile devices SEO</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>On mobile devices, more than 51% of all online transactions have been made. In order to achieve the greatest results for your website, mobile SEO has become an essential component of your entire SEO strategy. If you want your business to succeed, you can&#39;t ignore it. You may use our guide to aid with any mobile search optimizations!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Many businesses are unaware of the value of a mobile-friendly website, but if you don&#39;t have one, it will harm both your SEO and how your audience views your company. In fact, a poor mobile experience makes users 52% less likely to interact with your business again.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>What is Mobile SEO?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>For websites that target mobile devices, there is a sort of search engine optimization known as mobile SEO. Additionally, using mobile search engine optimization tactics guarantees that your website is compatible with mobile browsers. The practice of mobile SEO involves optimising your content to get better user experience and higher ranks. Mobile SEO is crucial since it guarantees that mobile users get a positive, mobile-device-optimized experience. Site design, site structure, page speed, and on-page mobile SEO techniques are crucial elements of mobile SEO.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>How Does Mobile SEO Work?&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Mobile SEO is a method of website optimization that aims to ensure that it functions properly on mobile devices. With the proper optimization, a website can be made to be more user-friendly and adapt to all types of devices, which will help it rank higher in search results.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The growth in mobile traffic, conversion rate, and lead generation is a result of long-term mobile SEO efforts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Problems that websites created for desktop shouldn&#39;t experience should also be addressed by effective mobile optimization (or at least not on such a scale). These, for instance, include:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Because of this, it is significantly more difficult to incorporate all the elements on a website.</li>\r\n	<li>Numerous devices &ndash; it is challenging to develop one solution that will work well on all sorts of mobiles, and mobile browser compatibility &ndash; not all forms of code will display appropriately on each browser.</li>\r\n	<li>Why Optimize For Mobile? Statistics</li>\r\n	<li>Is mobile SEO even worth the time and money spent on it?</li>\r\n	<li>Is a desktop-optimized website insufficient to guarantee business success?</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Well, not having a website that is optimised for mobile browsing prevents you from growing your company. And now for the evidence:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>In June 2022, mobile devices accounted for 59.74% of all web traffic, while desktops made for 37.99%. (source: gs.statcounter.com). Mobile device prices have been rising for a number of years. Comparatively, 62.38% of website traffic in January 2015 came from desktops, while 31.06% of it came from mobile devices.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Statistics for mobile SEO</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>90% of Amazon consumers reported using a smartphone to make a purchase at least once already in 2016. (source: State of Amazon 2016).</li>\r\n	<li>By 2021, mobile devices will account for almost 50% of all internet transactions.</li>\r\n	<li>74% of users are willing to come back to a site that is optimized for mobile devices.</li>\r\n	<li>52% of users are less willing to engage with a brand once they had a negative mobile experience.</li>\r\n	<li>74% of visitors are eager to return to a site that is mobile-friendly.</li>\r\n	<li>After having a bad mobile experience, 52% of users are less likely to engage with a company.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>How Can I Monitor Mobile Traffic?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Simply logging into your Google Analytics account will allow you to see whether your website receives a lot of mobile traffic.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Simply go to Audience and then select Mobile. You may view the number of visits made by various sorts of devices to your website over time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Mobile device SEO</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Verify the site&#39;s mobile friendliness<br />\r\nIt is vital to determine whether your website is currently in good health before you go on your mobile SEO adventure. Fortunately, you have access to a variety of tools that can assist you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. Start by using Mobile-Friendly Test, a totally free tool made available by Google. Simply enter your website&#39;s URL, and the tool will provide a report listing all the components that need mobile optimization.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n2. Mobile-friendly website loading test<br />\r\nGoogle Search Console is the greatest option if you want to determine whether your website has any problems with mobile crawling.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. Head over to the Coverage section. Here, you may check to see if there are any issues with how your website appears on mobile devices.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>What makes mobile SEO so crucial?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>We&#39;ve already covered the advantages of mobile SEO for your business, but let&#39;s look at some statistics to make the point:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>70% of people&#39;s online time is spent on mobile devices.</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;70% of the time when consumers browse the internet, they do so on portable devices. You must make sure users enjoy their time on your site if they spend the majority of their browsing time on mobile devices.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;If you&nbsp;don&#39;t&nbsp;change, you run the danger of losing plenty of leads for your company because of bad mobile experiences.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>74% of visitors are more inclined to return to a website that is mobile-friendly.</strong><br />\r\n	It stands to reason that people will return to your sites more frequently if they have a good mobile experience on your site. Returning to your website can make a big difference in whether or not visitors turn into leads for your company. Adapting your website to give your audience the greatest experience possible is a significant component of mobile SEO. Without a mobile-friendly website, you run the danger of consumers having a bad impression of your&nbsp;company and leaving your pages, which lowers your ranking. More than 60% of users who find your business will have a more favorable perception of it if your website is mobile-friendly.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Users are more likely to make a purchase from a firm that is mobile-friendly (67%).</strong><br />\r\n	Your conversion rate is impacted by your mobile friendliness. Your audience is more likely to buy things from your firm if your website functions effectively on smartphones. Your business will experience more conversions if your website is mobile-friendly.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>When crawling and indexing websites, Google puts mobile first.</strong><br />\r\n	Google has changed to a &quot;mobile-first index&quot; since more and more people are using their phones to search the web. Google&#39;s crawlers will now read your mobile site first, according to this. Your website&#39;s ranking in the search results will suffer if it isn&#39;t mobile-friendly, which will affect customer traffic, lead generation, and sales for your company.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Guide to Mobile SEO Optimization: 10 Crucial Elements</h3>\r\n\r\n<h4>1. Site speed</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>This is without a doubt among the most crucial elements of mobile website optimization.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We frequently observe that the pace of page loading on mobile devices is substantially slower than on desktops when we first begin working with new clients. It turns out that even if you increase the speed at which a page loads on desktops, it won&#39;t necessarily do so on mobile devices.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Remember that this is one of the key ranking elements for search engines and that a poor page load time will also result in a higher bounce rate. Therefore, never ignore it!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>How can the elements that need to be optimized for faster page loading on mobile devices be identified? PageSpeed Insights will provide you with a wealth of useful advice!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This is a free tool developed by Google to assess how well any website performs on desktops and mobile devices. You can use this tool to find out what needs to be improved on your website by just entering the URL.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mobile SEO accelerate</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The following factors have the biggest impact on a mobile website&#39;s slow loading time:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>unoptimized and uncompressed pictures, unminified HTML, CSS, and JavaScript code, a slow server response, an excessive number of redirects, and a disregard for CDN (Content Delivery Network).</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>2. Design that is responsive</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Responsive design, in its simplest form, refers to the adaption of the page layout to different devices (desktops, tablets, and mobile devices) on displays of varied sizes. It is crucial that consumers can access all website features and that they remain consistent across all device types.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Want to quickly see how your website will appear on mobile devices?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This is possible with a web browser like Google Chrome. When you right-click and choose Inspect, you will notice a choice to change the page layout to fit different screen widths. I went with an iPhone 6/7/8/Plus, and as you can see below, our website&#39;s design is responsive and optimized for mobile devices.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Optimizing mobile devices for search<br />\r\nAlso, WooRank, a fantastic SEO tool that is free of charge displays mobile rendering so you can see a preview of your website on both mobile and tablet devices.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>3. Dynamic Serving&nbsp;</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>While many people have not yet heard of dynamic serving, it looks to be a crucial component when dealing with website optimization for various device kinds.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This method allows the server to respond to the same URL using various HTML and CSS codes depending on the device (desktop, mobile, or tablet). This is primarily made feasible by the Vary HTTP Header, which tells a web browser how to display a page&#39;s content differently based on the user agent.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Google has put together a thorough developer&#39;s guide if you&#39;d like to learn more about how to detect user-agents correctly.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>4. Unique URLs</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>You must use distinct URLs to aid in the proper interpretation because Google is unable to recognise that your website has two different versions for desktops and mobile devices.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For desktop users, separate URLs often show as www.address.com and for mobile users, m.address.com.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Examples of separate URLs for mobile SEO</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>How do you let Google and web crawlers know that they are dealing with two different sites? Well, getting there requires some effort:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You must add a rel=&quot;alternate&quot; tag to your page&#39;s desktop version so that it links to the matching mobile page.<br />\r\nHowever, you must add a rel=&quot;canonical&quot; tag to the mobile version of your website so that it links to the matching desktop page.<br />\r\nRemember that creating distinct URLs requires some complexity and that if done incorrectly, it may result in issues. For this reason, I advise you to approach your developer to put this solution into practice.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>5. Regional SEO</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Local users may find your business and make a purchase considerably faster with so-called near me searches (keywords containing phrases such as &quot;near me,&quot; &quot;closest,&quot; &quot;open,&quot; and &quot;nearby&quot;).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You don&#39;t think it&#39;s true?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In a Google survey, it was shown that up to 76% of mobile users who are seeking nearby businesses visit one in a single day. Additionally, 28% of these searches result in conversion, or a purchase (source: thinkwithgoogle.com).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As you can see, concentrating on local SEO results in a significant increase in the growth of your organization. Of course, this also applies to desktop users, but it bears mentioning that mobile users are much more crucial.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>How can local SEO be improved?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Create a Google Business Profile account &ndash; add all necessary information: company address, contact information, opening hours,</li>\r\n	<li>Reviews &ndash; the more positive the reviews, the better; users really pay attention to them, especially the ones added recently,</li>\r\n	<li>Add images to your Google My Business account.</li>\r\n	<li>Create material that is focused on the local area; mention the city or neighborhood where your business is located in the content on your website; this will affect where you appear in local search results. Phone number and e-mail address &ndash; add clickable contact details on your site so that users can get in touch with you more easily.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h4>6. Meta description and title optimization</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Due to the significantly smaller size of mobile screens, it is crucial to provide users with as much information as you can about your website in the search results.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A snippet on desktops has more characters than on mobile devices, as you can see in the example below. Simply said, you sacrifice numerous characters while optimizing your website for mobile devices.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>mobile SEO search<br />\r\nMake sure to place the most pertinent keywords at the front of your title tag and meta description for the best results. This will guarantee that the keyword is visible to mobile users.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Remember that increasing your meta description&#39;s click-through rate is as simple as adding a brief CTA (Call To Action).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Emojis should also be used, even if they don&#39;t really affect how well a page ranks in search results, they do catch users&#39; eyes and intrigue them.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><br />\r\n7. Structured Data in Schema</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Structural data is unquestionably one of the most crucial SEO components right now. Google simply favours and rewards well-organized web pages!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>What benefits may you expect as a result of the correctly created Schema.org?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>First of all, there is a form of dialogue going on between your website and the Google robots as you tell them what each piece on your site means. Additionally, a search engine will provide these details in the so-called rich snippet as payment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The vitality of mobile SEO<br />\r\nStructured data may increase your CTR as well.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Why is that so?<br />\r\nPages containing structured data take up more space, as seen in the search results screen above, making them more visible and appealing to consumers. Additionally, there are evaluations or votes for the recipes, which may persuade consumers to use this website.<br />\r\nImplement structured data to observe how it can impact your mobile SEO for yourself!</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><br />\r\n8. User Experience</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Users are increasingly using mobile devices instead of desktop computers to search for websites. Simply said, it is more practical for them.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Be aware that even if consumers access your website from a desktop computer, they have likely already used a mobile device to interact with it. A user just won&#39;t return to your website and will instead choose one of your competitors if it takes forever to fully load on a mobile device or if the information is unreadable.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Therefore, always prioritize the mobile user experience, and strive to provide a great first impression!</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>What is it about websites on mobile devices that make users go crazy?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>sluggish website loading</li>\r\n	<li>Unreadable content: To increase visibility, use a font size that is appropriate for the background colour.</li>\r\n	<li>Make sure that all of the buttons on your phone are large enough for your fingertips (be fat-finger friendly),</li>\r\n	<li>Users don&#39;t want to copy or rewrite your phone number, so give them a clickable one instead. Unclickable contact numbers</li>\r\n	<li>Ensure a transparent content organization and visual hierarchy when using a chaotic design.</li>\r\n	<li>Choosing mobile controls instead of online controls enables more user interaction.</li>\r\n	<li>using SEO, enhance organic traffic<br />\r\n	&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h4>9. Pop-Up Ads</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Google has implemented an algorithm that penalizes websites with several huge pop-ups that obscure the content and make it more challenging for people to access a particular page because it wants websites on mobile devices to be accessible to all users.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Don&#39;t disturb users with a lot of pop-ups or interstitials that ask them to join up for the newsletter or subscribe.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I&#39;m not saying pop-ups are a terrible thing; rather, you&#39;ll get a good response if you introduce them in a way that doesn&#39;t irritate people and abides by Google&#39;s guidelines.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Always include a large enough closing button because customers detest pop-ups that are awkward to close, which is even more challenging for them on mobile devices.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>10. Voice Search</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Have you ever given voice search&#39;s significance in SEO techniques any thought?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It turns out that mobile users are actually beginning to trust voice search, despite the fact that many SEO experts still choose to dismiss it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This issue has been for a while, but recently, because of the quick advancement of Google&#39;s Home assistant or Apple&#39;s Siri, things have really started to shift much more quickly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Ways to get ready for voice search</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Focus on conversational long-tail keywords; as mobile users speak more naturally, choose keywords that are long sentences or questions, such &quot;How to make a beautiful cheesecake,&quot; if you want to boost mobile traffic.<br />\r\nChoose a lengthier structure for your content so that it has a better chance of showing in so-called featured snippets. Create content that meets people&#39; requirements and offers solutions. Take a quick glance at Google&#39;s auto-fill feature for plenty of suggestions if you&#39;re seeking for questions to address with your article.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nTo get more insights on the latest mobile SEO services, stay updated here. Find out more about our content marketing stories by visiting our campaigns page. Feel like collaborating with us? Don&rsquo;t shy away from <a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com\" target=\"_blank\">contacting us</a>, one of the <a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com\" target=\"_blank\">best mobile SEO agencies in Mumbai</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'Discover the latest trends and strategies for optimizing your website for mobile SEO. Our blog offers expert insights and actionable tips to improve your mobile presence.', 'mobile-seo-complete-guide', 'Mobile SEO, Mobile SEO Optimization, What is Mobile SEO, mobile seo tools , mobile seo guide, mobile seo services in Navi Mumbai', 'Ayushi', '2023-02-23 18:29:53', '2023-02-23 18:33:03'),
(55, 'PPC Marketing: Ultimate Guide for Beginners', 'Marketing', 'ppc-marketing-ultimate-guide-for-beginners.webp', NULL, '<p>Did you know that you could make up to $8 back for every dollar you spent on Google Ads? You&#39;re passing up a great chance to get qualified leads for your company that result in conversions if you don&#39;t invest in pay-per-click (PPC) marketing. Fortunately, we have all the PPC knowledge you require to begin using this results-oriented approach.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In this PPC guide, we&#39;ll address your pressing inquiries like:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>PPC Marketing: What Is It?</li>\r\n	<li>What is the PPC Marketing Process?</li>\r\n	<li>How To Start A PPC Marketing Campaign</li>\r\n	<li>Does PPC Marketing Make Sense?</li>\r\n	<li>Advice For Successfully Launching PPC Marketing Ads</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3><br />\r\nPPC Marketing: What Is It?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Pay-per-click advertising is a sort of digital marketing that is used to drive website traffic, store visits, transactions, quote requests, and other activities. PPC marketing advertising may show up on websites included in the ad network as well as search engine results pages.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>What is the PPC Marketing Process?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Let&#39;s examine PPC marketing&#39;s operation now that you are familiar with its term.&nbsp;<br />\r\nWhat can you anticipate when you start a paid search advertising campaign? We&#39;ll use Google Ads as an illustration of their model.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When a user conducts a search on their search engine, Google examines the pool of advertisers placing bids on the user&#39;s term. Google examines several aspects of each company&#39;s advertisement, but the two most important aspects are:<br />\r\n&bull; Quality Score<br />\r\n&bull; Bid amount</p>\r\n\r\n<p>These two elements, among others, will be used by Google to offer the most pertinent adverts. The entire procedure takes place in a matter of milliseconds, and the searcher is completely unaware of it.<br />\r\nFollowing the conclusion of the auction, the searcher will be seeing advertisements in the search results that Google considers are the most pertinent to the search query.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>How To Start A PPC Marketing Campaign</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Now that you are aware of what PPC marketing is and how it operates, you are prepared to learn how to start your own campaign. The following four elements are essential for starting a sponsored search advertising campaign:</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>1. Carry out a keyword search</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Researching keywords is one of the most crucial topics we&#39;ll cover in this PPC tutorial. Users&#39; searches cause your advertisement to show up in search results. You must bid on the appropriate keywords if you want your ad to generate relevant leads.<br />\r\nYou can locate applicable terms for your advertisement by using keyword research tools like KeywordsFX. You should concentrate on long-tail keywords, which are those that have three or more words, when looking for keywords for your PPC advertisements. For your PPC advertising campaigns, long-tail keywords are ideal for two reasons:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Long-tail keywords generate more qualified traffic since they are more precise and make it possible to quickly ascertain the purpose of the search.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You can tell someone is interested in your firm if they search using certain terms linked to it.<br />\r\nLong-tail keywords have a cheaper cost per click since there is less competition for them because they are more specialised. You have a reduced cost per click (CPC) for your company because fewer companies are bidding on these keywords. It enables you to get the most leads for your money.<br />\r\nThe second crucial consideration, setting your bid, may be your main emphasis after you have a keyword list to target.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><br />\r\n2. Select the bid amount.</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>You&#39;ll place a bid once you&#39;ve decided on your keywords. However, how do you figure out how much to bid each click? You may get the average CPC for select keywords through keyword research tools like LSIGraph and Google Keyword Planner.<br />\r\nYou can use it to help you choose how much to bid for the keyword. You&#39;ll need to experiment with your bidding strategy if you&#39;re utilising a tool for keyword research that lacks CPC data. You might have to choose your price range before keeping an eye on your advertisement and making adjustments as needed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For instance, you can set your offer at 30 cents per click and keep an eye on your advertising. After a while, you might notice that searchers aren&#39;t seeing your ads. This suggests that a rival is outbidding you with a more pertinent ad. You can then return to your ad and increase your bid price till your ad appears as frequently as your company prefers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When choosing your bid amount, keep in mind that you should never overbid. Don&#39;t pick a high number just to try to win the competition-free top slot. The best course of action is to start off with a lower bid and progressively increase it until your ad performs as you would expect.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To generate qualified leads through your ads and rank higher using the previous example, you might discover that increasing your bid from 30 cents to 50 cents per click is sufficient.<br />\r\nYou wouldn&#39;t realise that a lower quantity may produce the same outcomes at a lower cost if you began out by bidding $2 per click.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>3. Develop catchy ad copy</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Let&#39;s move on to discussing ad copy in this guide on creating PPC ads. When your ad shows in search results, users will see your ad copy. You should make sure that the ad copy you write for it is intriguing and enticing in order to persuade leads to click on it. You run the danger of leads clicking on a competitor&#39;s ad if your copy isn&#39;t compelling.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Follow these basic practises to assist you in producing high-quality ad copy:<br />\r\nTo persuade your audience to pick you, emphasise the advantages of your organisation, product, or service.<br />\r\nTo elicit a response and a click from your audience, appeal to their emotions.<br />\r\nUse intriguing language to draw your audience in and make your offer stand out.<br />\r\nGive your viewers important information up front so they are informed.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>4. Design a unique landing page</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>A customised landing page is an essential part of an effective paid search advertising strategy. Using compelling ad language to entice leads to click on your advertising is half the battle. Once they click, you can&#39;t let them down; you must provide an outstanding landing page experience.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A common error made by businesses is to use a page from their website as a landing page. This method has a flaw in that the pages it produces frequently lack specificity and have a lot of distractions. A customised landing page, on the other hand, offers a targeted and concentrated experience for your audience.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>They seem to be more likely to convert when your audience remains focused on the reason they clicked on your advertisement. You can make a persuading personalised landing page by:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Including the distinctive design of your brand</li>\r\n	<li>Utilizing images and videos that are pertinent to your ads</li>\r\n	<li>using directional indicators, like as arrows, to bring visitors to your page</li>\r\n	<li>Having one stand-out call to action (CTA) button on the page<br />\r\n	&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Does PPC Marketing Make Sense?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>You might be unsure about the suitability of paid search advertising for your company after learning how to start your own PPC advertising campaign. To learn more, respond to these inquiries:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Do you want to give your company&#39;s brand more exposure?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Do you want to increase the number of qualified leads your business receives?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Do you want to increase sales and conversions?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Do you desire to be in charge of your spending?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Do you wish to be able to reach those most likely to be interested in your company?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you indicated yes to any of these, PPC marketing is the best approach for you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>93% of WebFX clients are very happy with the outcomes of their digital marketing campaigns.<br />\r\n&quot;When working with WebFX, everything is very well planned out. Even though our cooperation is only a year old, our expectations have already been exceeded.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>View Additional Client Reviews</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>4 suggestions for successfully establishing PPC marketing advertising</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Let&#39;s examine four suggestions for writing PPC ads that provide greater results for your company in the final section of our PPC guide!</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>1. Use ad extensions</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Use ad extensions in your PPC marketing if you want to succeed. Ad extensions let you add more content to your ad that encourages people to click. You can utilise a variety of ad extensions to increase the number of clicks on your advertisements, including:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Structured snippet: You can draw attention to your goods and services using the structured snippet extension to pique the curiosity of your target market.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Callout: Callout extensions allow you to draw attention to features that distinguish your company from the competitors, such as a customer-centric approach.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Call: Using the call extension, you may give leads a way to reach your company by adding a contact information to your listing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sitelink: Sitelink extensions let you add links to various pages on your website in an effort to encourage visitors to click.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Message: Just like the phone extension, the message extension allows users to text you directly from the advertisement.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Price: To encourage users to click, you can highlight the prices of your goods or services using the price extension.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Location: You can include an address in your PPC ad using the location extension so that people can come visit you there.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To get users to click on your advertising, you can combine any of these extensions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>2. Include offensive keywords</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Let&#39;s move on to the next topic in this PPC primer: negative keywords. Negative keywords are those that you don&#39;t want to appear in search results for your ads. Say you want to be found when people search for things like &quot;women&#39;s black hiking boots&quot; and &quot;black hiking boots.&quot; Once your advertisement has run, you discover that you are showing up in search results for the phrase &quot;children&#39;s black hiking boots.&quot; The Issue?<br />\r\nYou don&#39;t have a pair of black hiking boots for kids. However, because your advertisement still appears in the search results for this phrase, you are squandering money by sending people to your website who won&#39;t be able to purchase what they need from you. You can thus specify &quot;children&#39;s&quot; as a negative keyword for your ad to avoid this issue.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>By doing this, your advertisement will show up for &quot;black hiking boots&quot; rather than &quot;children&#39;s black hiking boots.&quot; To ensure that only qualified leads see your ads, use negative keywords. This will help you increase the qualified visitors to your website.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>3. Keep track of the results of your PPC marketing campaigns</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>You must keep an eye on your ad performance to achieve the best outcomes and stay clear of problems with your PPC campaigns. Ads shouldn&#39;t be launched and then ignored forever. You can determine what&#39;s working and make adjustments to your campaign by keeping track of the success of your ads.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Establishing your key performance indicators can help you monitor your efforts successfully (KPIs). These analytics will show you whether your campaigns are successful. There are several metrics you can monitor, including:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Impressions</li>\r\n	<li>Clicks</li>\r\n	<li>CPC</li>\r\n	<li>Click-through rate (CTR)</li>\r\n	<li>Conversion</li>\r\n	<li>Cost per conversion</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>You may learn more about how your audience interacts with your advertisements by monitoring these KPIs.<br />\r\nYou can enhance your adverts if you notice that some of these indicators are performing poorly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>4. Evaluate your ads</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>A/B testing is one of the best strategies to enhance your advertisements. You can test several website components using A/B testing to see which will work best for your company. You can test parts such as your:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Ad text</li>\r\n	<li>Design of landing pages</li>\r\n	<li>Your landing page&#39;s visual components</li>\r\n	<li>Orientation cues</li>\r\n	<li>CTA placement, size, colour, and text</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Let&#39;s take an example where you&#39;re monitoring your PPC advertisements and you find that clicks on your ads don&#39;t result in conversions.<br />\r\nYou utilise heatmaps to evaluate your landing page and discover that your CTA button isn&#39;t being seen by visitors. As a result, you experiment with your CTA to see which one produces the most results.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It&#39;s time to increase your sales.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With the aid of marketing techniques that have been shown to raise key performance indicators like revenue and conversions, our extensive variety of services enables you to expand every facet of your organisation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We&#39;ve handled more than 12.9 MILLION transactions for our clientele over the last five years.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>Enter your website</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Utilize PPC marketing to launch your sponsored advertising strategy.<br />\r\nPPC marketing is a great approach for your company to connect with more qualified leads that are interested in your goods or services. After reading this PPC primer, if you&#39;re ready to start your campaign, WebFX is here to assist.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We have a staff of over 450 marketing specialists who can work with you to create a unique PPC campaign designed to help your business succeed online. We are skilled in creating campaigns that produce outcomes. For our clients, we have generated more than 7.8 million leads and over $3 billion in sales in just the last five years.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Benefits of using PPC</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Are you still not persuaded that you require PPC? Here are a few advantages that you need to be aware of.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Only after pepople click on your ad do you pay&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Even though we just touched on this, it&#39;s crucial to underline how inexpensive PPC advertisements are. You essentially display your advertisement for free and just pay when someone is persuaded to click on.<br />\r\nThis economic approach is growing more efficient and kinder to your ROI. You have a higher than average chance of getting results because more PPC engines match your advertising to users based on their actions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Raise the bar on your marketing strategy&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>PPC is a fantastic approach to drive website traffic and raise awareness, and the results show up more quickly than with other marketing techniques like SEO.<br />\r\nHowever, working with a professional will ensure the greatest outcomes. You&#39;ll be able to increase your ROI and be sure you&#39;re bidding on the relevant advertising.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Methodical Results&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you want to know if your efforts are effective, you must monitor your progress.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Fortunately, evaluating your PPC results is simple. Some KPIs, such as views, impressions, leads, and click-through rates, are available for tracking.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>How do you gauge PPC success?</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Google Ads will offer a report of its own. There are various campaign tracking platforms you can utilise if you use other PPC platforms and search engines. To gauge these results, you can also consult a PPC specialist.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Due to Actions</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The foundation of many marketing strategies, including SEO and social media marketing, is exposure. PPC, however, is driven by actions. Your users go through the marketing funnel more quickly when they click your advertiing.<br />\r\nFor instance, when your prospects see your advertisement, they are at the awareness stage.<br />\r\nBut as soon as they click your advertisement, they move from awareness to consideration, indicating that they are actively looking for goods and services.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>A campaign can always be pauperated or ended</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>PPC is more adaptable than you may realise. You can quickly remove your adverts because there are no payments that are guaranteed for you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Although you&#39;ll need to invest a lot of time in your campaign to make it successful, don&#39;t worry&mdash;you can easily terminate it at any point.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But what if you hire a professional to handle your PPC marketing?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The terms of their cancellation will determine how you conclude your campaign. The best course of action is to select a PPC marketing firm without lengthy commitments so all you have to do is terminate the account.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To get more insights on the latest <a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/technical-seo-complete-guide\" target=\"_blank\">SEO techniques</a>, <a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com\" target=\"_blank\">stay updated here</a>. Find out more about our content marketing stories by visiting our campaigns page. Feel like collaborating with us? Don&rsquo;t shy away from <a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com\" target=\"_blank\">contacting us</a> at any of our branches!</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', 'Ready to take your advertising game to the next level? Check out our ultimate guide to PPC marketing for beginners and start driving conversions today!', 'ppc-marketing-ultimate-guide-for-beginners', 'PPC Marketing, guide to ppc marketing, ppc marketing examples, What is PPC and how it works, Pay-Per-Click (PPC), digital marketing company in navi mumbai', 'Ayushi', '2023-02-23 20:18:40', '2023-02-23 20:18:40');
INSERT INTO `blog` (`id`, `blog_title`, `blog_category`, `image1`, `image2`, `description`, `description1`, `blog_url`, `tags`, `author_name`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(56, 'Top 20 Online Reputation Management (ORM) Tools in 2023', 'ORM', 'top-online-reputation-management-tools.webp', NULL, '<p>Companies and brands make a concerted effort to steer clear of unfavorable evaluations since they might harm their bottom line and online reputation. In fact, 94% of customers claim that a negative review caused them to steer clear of a company. It&#39;s critical to keep a respectable and reliable reputation in the eyes of your clients, particularly online. Online reputation management tools exist as a result, and they can assist you in controlling how consumers perceive your brand.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What Is Online Reputation Management?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>A positive and reliable brand image on the internet is created and maintained through online reputation management (ORM). In order for customers to keep purchasing your goods and services, you want them to have a positive perception of your brand.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Companies utilize a variety of tools and tactics while implementing ORM to keep track of what people are saying about their business operations on various platforms. They keep an eye on review sites, social media, and the blog for company. It&#39;s wise for businesses to reply as soon as possible to complaints or unfavorable comments. This lessens any harm the review or criticism might create and demonstrates to others how well the business interacts with and responds to its clients.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>20 Best Tools for Online Reputation Management</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>There are numerous technologies available for use by businesses to manage their online reputation. Some of these programmes follow as under:</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>1. Reputology</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Reviews are gathered by <a href=\"https://www.reputology.com\" target=\"_blank\">Reputology</a> from employee review websites, Google, and Facebook. Then, it combined them on a single dashboard for examination by your team. You may interact with your audience and respond to reviews right from the home screen. A variety of criteria are used by the application to evaluate your online reputation and performance so you can identify exactly where you need to make improvements. Companies can develop new strategies to increase client loyalty by better understanding their online performance.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>&nbsp;2. Mention</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Businesses can track online mentions of them with <a href=\"https://mention.com/en\" target=\"_blank\">Mention</a>. It gathers data about client opinions of your business from websites, blogs, forums, and social media pages. Additionally, brands utilise Mention to add content to their own social media profiles and schedule postings. Even better, it offers a feature that produces data on your present web reputation, allowing you to tweak your marketing or customer service tactics to win over more supporters.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>3. The Brand Grader</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Mention offers a free tool called The <a href=\"https://mention.com/brand-grader\" target=\"_blank\">Brand Grader</a>. It offers brief summaries of brands&#39; current web reputations. It contains details like the most recent forum or news mentions, the proportion of good and negative evaluations, and the number of mentions a business receives across several platforms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Although the tool only shows data from the previous 30 days, it can provide you with a fantastic snapshot of your brand at any moment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>4. Buzzsumo</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Companies can check their current internet performance using <a href=\"https://buzzsumo.com\" target=\"_blank\">Buzzsumo</a>, a digital marketing tool. It also includes other beneficial features that enable businesses to do competitive analysis and find out about current trends or popular content. By looking into a brand&#39;s online mentions as well as those of its rivals and other well-known companies, Buzzsumo is able to achieve this. You may strengthen your marketing strategy and discover fresh approaches to draw in your target market by examining how your firm is doing in comparison to its rivals.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Looking for further strategies to strengthen your marketing efforts and beat out the competition? The top three competitors are compared in a content analysis tool provided by CopyPress. It offers insight into the kind of content that resonate most with your audience and identifies areas where you can make changes to garner even more traction. If your existing content marketing plan has any holes, get your content analysis right away!<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>5. Buffer</h4>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://buffer.com\" target=\"_blank\">Buffer</a> is a social media management application that enables companies to keep tabs on their accounts, gauge engagement, and answer customer questions or comments. Despite the fact that a company&#39;s online image extends beyond social media, it&#39;s crucial for businesses to have a robust social media presence and communicate with customers frequently. Using this program, you can consistently manage your social media. By replying to all comments&mdash;positive and negative&mdash;on these platforms, you can demonstrate to your customers that you care about their happiness and well-being, thereby reducing the impact of any adverse remarks on these channels.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>6. BrandMentions</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>With the use of the tool <a href=\"https://brandmentions.com\" target=\"_blank\">BrandMentions</a>, businesses may more efficiently monitor their operations and brand. It can look up and show relevant hashtags, search for customer mentions of a brand on social media, and monitor those mentions. Additionally, it gives businesses information on how customers are connecting with their brand and how well they are performing currently online. You may gain a better understanding of your target market by being aware of when and how they connect with your business online.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This can encourage more customers to make purchases and help you maintain them as loyal customers for longer.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>7. GatherUp</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Businesses can examine brand reviews from several sources in one location thanks to <a href=\"https://gatherup.com\" target=\"_blank\">GatherUp</a>. Additionally, it can provide reports and gather information on a brand&#39;s reputation. Other characteristics include:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Addressing client grievances and feedback</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Creating automated processes to engage with clients more frequently</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Using images and phrases from customer evaluations to create interesting social media posts</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>You can use this tool to better understand how internet users view your business. This might assist you in developing a greater understanding of what your clients want from your business.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>8. YouScan</h4>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://youscan.io\" target=\"_blank\">YouScan</a> is a social media monitoring programme that gathers all of the online mentions of your business and shows them on the program&#39;s dashboard. Many of its capabilities are interchangeable with those of other software packages, but its image recognition capability sets it apart. This application can detect and recognise various company logos on social media posts to help users better understand when someone is showcasing or promoting a brand. With this tool, you can check to see who is mentioning your business or who is mentioning one of your rivals.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>9. Brand24</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>With the help of <a href=\"https://brand24.com\" target=\"_blank\">Brand24</a>, businesses can quickly respond to what customers are saying about their brand. The tool compiles all mentions and reviews of the brand in a single area that is simple for businesses to access and control. This application can help you respond more rapidly to clients who may have complaints or criticisms about your company. Responding demonstrates your interest in your customers&#39; opinions. Reading reviews can give you priceless insight on how to better your goods, services, and business as a whole.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>10. ReviewPush</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Companies can keep an eye on online reviews that customers leave about them thanks to <a href=\"https://www.reviewpush.com\" target=\"_blank\">ReviewPush</a>. Companies can use the application to manage the reputation of numerous business locations, browse a collection of evaluations from various review sites, and respond to feedback directly through email.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This application enables you to quickly and easily examine all the reviews if your business oversees a franchise or numerous branches. Utilize ReviewPush to categorize reviews according to the region and identify any areas of your company that aren&#39;t operating as expected.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>11. Google Alerts</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>With <a href=\"https://www.google.co.in/alerts\" target=\"_blank\">Google Alerts</a>, users may sign up to receive email notifications whenever Google adds new, particular content to its search index. Select the keywords and subjects you want to focus on to stay current in various areas of your industry or to find out how your brand is being mentioned online. Using this tool, businesses may find out when someone creates material that specifically mentions their brand.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>12. Chatmeter</h4>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.chatmeter.com\" target=\"_blank\">Chatmeter</a> gathers evaluations from throughout the web, including social media, and organizes them for use by businesses. This enables firms to address customer feedback immediately and determine whether any particular aspects of their operation require modification. The tool compares a brand&#39;s reviews to those of its rivals and assesses the quantity and quality of reviews submitted for the brand. Because you can arrange evaluations based on location and mode of operation, Chatmeter, like ReviewPush, is a terrific resource for companies with several branches or stores.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>13. BrandYourself</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Companies can monitor customer feedback for both their brand and the specific employees that represent it with <a href=\"https://brandyourself.com\" target=\"_blank\">BrandYourself</a>. It gives you access to many methods for doing competitive analysis, comprehending modern trends, and mass client response using a minimal number of message-specific building pieces. By providing customers with information more quickly, having a quick and simple means to respond to them will help you preserve your online reputation. The more quickly you address a problem or bad review, the better you&#39;ll look in your audience&#39;s eyes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>14. Reputation.com</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Companies can manage and track all evaluations and mentions of their brands through <a href=\"https://reputation.com\" target=\"_blank\">reputation</a> in one convenient area. You can track and manage your social media presence with the programme as well.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To better understand what customers want from your company and to produce more interesting content, you may even design surveys to distribute to customers. Additional options are available through reputation that might aid with your digital marketing efforts. By using these tools, you may increase your sales and revenue while also better understanding your target market and developing more useful products and services for them.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>&nbsp;15. Meltwater</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>A social listening platform from <a href=\"https://www.meltwater.com/en\" target=\"_blank\">Meltwater</a> gives businesses access to what consumers are saying about their brands, goods, and services. The application examines all material types, such as blogs and podcasts, to find out what people are saying about your business and who is listening to them. You may locate influencers to work with by being aware of who online has sway over public perception of your business. You may market and sell your goods and services with the aid of these influencers. They can also assist you in connecting with your target market and learning what your target market wants from your business.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>16. Reputation&nbsp;Health</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>An ORM tool created exclusively for healthcare facilities is called <a href=\"https://reputation-health.com\" target=\"_blank\">Reputation Health</a>. It enables urgent care centers, hospitals, and doctor&#39;s offices to track reviews from the tool&#39;s dashboard and reply to them. Additionally, it enables medical facilities to view analytics and reports on their procedures and internet reputations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This information can be used to evaluate rivals, compare various care facilities, and look up reviews for particular doctors. You can increase patient happiness and train your staff to provide better care by making sure that your institution responds to client concerns and feedback.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>17. SentiOne</h4>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://sentione.com\" target=\"_blank\">SentiOne</a> is a technology that assists businesses in doing online listening through both internal and external social media networks. Businesses can use it to find out who is talking about them online and see exactly what is being said about their brand. Additionally, it aids with crisis management for brands by enabling quick customer answers across the web from a single, handy location. Additionally, the programme offers an AI customer care automation tool that enables users to call or chat with someone who can help them with routine activities or questions around-the-clock.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>18. HootSuite</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Initially and foremost, <a href=\"https://www.hootsuite.com\" target=\"_blank\">HootSuite</a> is a social media monitoring tool. But it also functions well for keeping track of consumer perceptions of your brand. By giving you space to reply to comments and private messages, HootSuite assists you in engaging with your audience. You may quickly address inquiries and client problems without switching applications or devices if you have the flexibility to reply to messages from various accounts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In order to promptly respond to bad internet reviews, HootSuite may integrate with ReviewTracker. To understand your present online reputation and whether you need to make changes to your marketing, it&#39;s vital to be aware of what individuals have to say about your business on social media.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>19. Brandwatch</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Companies can use <a href=\"https://www.brandwatch.com\" target=\"_blank\">Brandwatch</a>&#39;s crisis management capabilities to monitor customer sentiment in real time and respond accordingly. It also aids in gathering information about current trends and demonstrates to businesses what their target market is most enthusiastic or interested in. The platform then presents that data in a dashboard that can be easily shared, allowing everyone in the marketing division to analyse it and determine what needs to be improved or targeted. You may design more successful marketing materials that can draw in more clients if there is agreement inside your organization about what you need to work on or target.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>20. BirdEye</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>With the help of <a href=\"https://birdeye.com\" target=\"_blank\">BirdEye</a>, businesses can view and reply to every online review a client has received. To strengthen a brand&#39;s reputation and online rating, it also produces additional reports concerning customer reviews and feedback. Businesses can use BirdEye&#39;s tools to ask customers for reviews, which are then posted directly to Google, Facebook, and other websites. Both soliciting and responding to reviews is crucial. It aids businesses in obtaining a higher overall rating and important input to enhance their operations and brand.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Looking out for the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com\" target=\"_blank\">best digital marketing agency in Navi Mumbai</a>, reach out to us in order to grow your business and boost the ORM practices you wish to embibe.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', 'Protect and enhance your online reputation with the top 20 ORM tools of 2023. Discover the best solutions to monitor, manage, and improve your brand\'s digital presence.', 'top-online-reputation-management-tools', 'ORM, Online Reputation Management , Online Reputation Management tools, best ORM tools in 2023, top Online Reputation Management tools, What is the best ORM tool?', 'Ayushi', '2023-02-23 21:11:11', '2023-02-23 22:18:42'),
(57, 'Google Local Pack: what is it?', 'SEO', 'google-local-pack.webp', NULL, '<p>In the modern world, clients frequently turn to search engines to get pertinent solutions to the majority of their inquiries and worries. Thus, Google has established itself as a crucial component of online consumers&#39; ability to find new goods and services in their area.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Google has introduced a local pack of three results with simple-to-use features to help local businesses get more exposure and to help people find answers. Many small and local businesses have the chance to enhance traffic and their internet visibility by taking advantage of Google Local Pack.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Because of the intense rivalry and the ubiquity of household names in the market, many small and local firms occasionally risk being missed. However, with this function, you can both expand the reach of your local business and enhance sales in both the online and offline sectors. In order to fulfil all of your business objectives, you would undoubtedly want to be listed on the Google local pack ranking list as a local business owner.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This post has covered all the information you need to know about the 3-pack local feature, citations, and how to raise your search engine rating.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What does Google Local pack mean?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>When a user types in terms like &quot;near me&quot; or &quot;near (location),&quot; Google will provide a list of rankings that includes the top three local companies. In addition to the address or location of the local business, Google frequently displays prospective business results that closely match users&#39; queries. You can use the Google Map Pack function to find a company&#39;s location close to where you live. The three top and most pertinent search results from Google Local Pack are displayed in a separate section at the top of the search result pages.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It is significant to remember that the results can change depending on the user&#39;s location and query. The results that are most relevant to the user&#39;s search and closest to their location are frequently listed by Google. 93% of the time when a local search is done, the Google local pack search results come up first. A local company can thus have the chance to outrank international and other national businesses for queries that are local in nature. As a result, it is more crucial than ever to adopt different Google local pack or Google map pack techniques and optimise your local search result ranking to increase traffic or clickthrough rates to your local business website.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Redesign of the Google Local Pack</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Over the past few years, the Google local pack has undergone numerous modifications. In order for you to clearly comprehend these changes, we have broken them down into two pieces. Let&#39;s now investigate the modifications Google has made to the Local Pack&#39;s design over the past few years.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Former&nbsp;Google Local Pack design</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Google local pack was first launched in 2014 as part of the Google Pigeon update, and it used to show 10 local company results originally. Later, that number was reduced to seven, and in August 2015, it was only allowed to show three local searches. By limiting local search results to the top three local firms, Google enhanced the effectiveness and level of competition among local company owners. The search result featured few options, and users frequently had to click on the listings to acquire additional business-related information, as per the old local pack design. The consumers were taken to a different page after selecting the listing, where they could access a number of options and a list of additional related companies operating in the market.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Current&nbsp;Google Local Pack</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The address of the company is now shown by Google together with additional details like the business&#39;s open and closing times, per the new Local pack style. Users can now simply find the company without having to click on numerous additional options thanks to this Google map pack feature. Additionally, thanks to the recent modifications made by Google, you now have the chance to have your small business listed even if leads don&#39;t click on your advertising.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Difference between Organic results and the Google Local Pack Results</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The algorithm for Google&#39;s local 3-pack results is different from the listing algorithms for organic search results. The information provided on the website that enables consumers to choose local companies that will satisfy their search query is a major factor in the Google local pack. However, organic results typically come after local pack results. The information linked to the specific search question is also included in the organic search results, however these listings do not include crucial data like a business&#39;s contact information and opening hours.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you&#39;re wondering which ranking outcome would be best for your business, both are. It is perfectly possible to rank in both search categories and significantly increase your company&#39;s visibility because the local pack and organic search results rankings are not mutually exclusive. These elements can increase the worth of your company and help it rank at the top of search results. However, as they both use separate algorithm settings, you might need to use alternative techniques on your local business websites in order to rank on both parts.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>How can I enter the Google Local 3 Pack?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Your ranking on Google&#39;s local 3-pack section might be influenced by a variety of variables. We&#39;ve included a list of some of the most effective strategies that can help you improve your rankings as soon as feasible.</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<h4>Improve your Google My Business profile&nbsp;</h4>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>For a potential consumer, your Google Business Profile is the main source of information about your company. Google gives important information about your company with the use of the data stated in this part, enabling your ranking on the list for pertinent local searches. You must make sure to keep your information current so that your customers don&#39;t overlook crucial details about your company. You update your Google My Business(GMB) profile with images, list your working and non-working hours, and reply to both favourable and helpful reviews or customer comments.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Your Google My Business page gives you the chance to give your clients access to the most fundamental and important details about your nearby businesses. Always be sure to complete every field in your Google My Business profile with information you want clients to be aware of.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>2. Double-check the accuracy of your NAP citations</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>The NAP citations on your website stand for &quot;Name, Address, and Phone Number&quot; information. The most important details about your company that aid customers in differentiating your local business from your rivals are represented by your NAP or local citations. The better your website will be, the more NAP citations it will have. You will be able to convey relevance signals to Google with the aid of these citations. Citation errors can have a significant impact on how well your local business is ranked by search engines. For your client&#39;s convenience, you may also note any changes to your contact information, such as a new phone number or email address, in the NAP citation area.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>3. Complete On-Page Optimisation</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>The on-page optimization has a significant impact on how visible your page is to search engines. It is the practise of altering your websites to raise their placement on different search engine result pages. Content, internal links, image optimization, URL and title optimization, and meta description optimization are some of the standard <a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com/technical-seo-vs-on-page-seo\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>on-page SEO techniques</strong></a>. With the aid of on-page SEO, you may efficiently draw in large numbers of your target market while enhancing your Google business profile. On-page optimization is quite affordable, which is one of its main benefits. It is by far thought to be the least expensive strategy for advertising your company online. This type of SEO trend can work wonders for small and local business owners and deliver excellent results rapidly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>4. Build Your Social Media Presence</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Social media is crucial for enhancing your company&#39;s online presence and growth rate in the modern digital age. The majority of clients frequently engage with your social media profiles before going to your website. In this manner, you have the chance to get to know your clients on a personal level and successfully inform them about your company. Make sure to regularly update your social media profiles with new information. You can also include links to your website in the description box, allowing customers to view it with just one click. Customers frequently post critical and helpful comments on your social media accounts; you should reply to these reviews and address your customers&#39; issues right away.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>5. Get Reviews on Your GMB profile</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>For your neighbourhood companies, your internet reviews have the power to make or break them. In order to use your products or services, many potential buyers rely on user reviews. The more in-depth reviews you have, the more customers will be drawn to interact with your brand. To increase the clickability and visibility of your website, you can request that your former customers post frank comments or reviews on it. In your review section, make an effort to answer every consumer question. Once you&#39;ve answered their questions, you can ping them again to deepen your connection and win them over as devoted clients.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>6. Building Local Links Will Help Your Ranking</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Backlinks can assist you to affect your search engine ranking by letting Google know exactly where you are. These connections can increase the geographic reach and importance of your company website. You will need links from neighbourhood websites, such as the home page of the church, the high school down the street, or other websites with a similar subject matter. These links will boost your search engine results and increase traffic to your website. By supporting charitable or other activities for these neighbourhood companies or nearby academic institutions in your area, you can gain these backlinks. By doing so, you can increase the number of reviews and visitors to your website and raise your organic search ranking.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Let&#39;s Position Your Company in the New Google Local Pack</p>\r\n\r\n<p>These were some essential elements of Google&#39;s local pack that you must take into account if you want to successfully and efficiently use local SEO best practices to improve your local business.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Looking out for the<a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com\" target=\"_blank\"> best digital marketing agency in Navi Mumbai</a>, reach out to us in order to grow your business.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'Discover the Google Local Pack and how it can impact your business\'s visibility in local search results. Learn what it is and how to optimize for it.', 'google-local-pack', 'Google Local Pack, What is the Google Local Pack?, How to improve your local ranking on Google, local pack seo, local seo, local pack ranking', 'Ayushi', '2023-03-03 20:28:59', '2023-03-03 20:30:05');
INSERT INTO `blog` (`id`, `blog_title`, `blog_category`, `image1`, `image2`, `description`, `description1`, `blog_url`, `tags`, `author_name`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(58, 'What is voice search & How does it work?', 'Voice Search', 'voice-search.webp', NULL, '<p>The year 2019 is passed, and we have just entered the year 2020. As more businesses and consumers place a greater emphasis on mobility and automation, voice search usage is anticipated to reach an all-time high this year. Voice search is widely used by customers to identify local companies, ask questions, make decisions, and more.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Many small and large organisations are incorporating speech into their customer care to enhance the experience for their clients. You won&#39;t be shocked to learn that 65% of millennials and members of Gen&nbsp;Z only use voice for internet searches at least once each day. The use of voice search will continue in the future. According to 71% of smart device owners, speaking rather than typing would be their preferred method of search.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Because voice assistants are now used by over 93% of people, voice search is gaining popularity day by day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, there are still some people who are unaware of what it is, its background, and the reasons behind its rapid growth and anticipated future growth.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Let&#39;s start by defining it.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What Is Voice Search?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Voice-search is essentially a cutting-edge technology strategy that employs voice-enabled commands to conduct a search on the phone, the web browser, or any application. To practically retrieve any online information, it comprises an open-domain short keyword query. Among the voice assistants that conduct voice searches are Alexa, Siri, and Google Voice search.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In essence, it is a form of dialogue system with rounds of dialogue. Additionally, you can tell the system more about your search. This enables you to obtain more precise findings.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In other words, search by voice is a method where technology use an audio recognition system to accurately grasp what the speaker is saying. Although it may seem like a recent development, the technology has actually been around for some time. Text-to-speech programmes are excellent illustrations of voice search.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Any gadget with a voice assistant or dialogue system can be made voice search-friendly. Speech assistants, on the other hand, use search by voice capabilities and streamline your procedure.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Voice Search History</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>When Bell Laboratories created the &quot;Audrey&quot; in 1952, the speech search or voice recognition technology was born. The limited number of words in the English language might be understood by this apparatus. Additionally, it has a 90% accuracy rate for recognising numbers from 0 to 9.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After that, in 1962, a sizable computer company called IBM created &quot;The Shoebox.&quot; Using a text-to-speech conversion method, this device was capable of understanding 16 English words.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Harpy began to exist after 1976. More than 1000 English words may be recognised by this DARPA technology. Voice recognition was developing at this period. More than 20,000 spoken words in the English language may be recognised by the TANGORA technology, which was made available by IBM.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The most significant development in this field was made by IBM, which created MedSpeak in 1996, a device that could comprehend continuous speech from the speaker.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Voice recognition and text-to-speech technology became so popular in 2002 that Microsoft included it in some of its own products.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The growth of artificial intelligence during this time period gave rise to personal voice assistants. Not any longer, as Apple introduced Siri, a personal voice assistant, to every product after Google released a voice search app.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Why Is Voice Search Growing So Quickly?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>There is increased interest in voice search, and you are not the only one who has noticed this. There are reasons why this movement is being embraced by everyone. For its rapid success both now and in the future, three factors are responsible.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It is 3.7 times faster than typing, therefore that is the first benefit. Searching more quickly would lead to finding answers more quickly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In fact, 60% of mobile phone users conduct the majority of their searches by voice, therefore it works great with portable electronic devices like mobile phones, tablets, and other similar ones. Thirdly, it is easier to use. Compared to using a keyboard, it is better. In other words, voice search isn&#39;t as popular as it once was. It is a trend that will not go away. In fact, it has started to have an impact on search engine SEO ranks as well.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Why Is Voice Search Important?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>You may be trying to figure out why the majority of individuals find this trend to be noteworthy. Look at the below-market numbers even if you are not currently using it. These statistics will help you understand why everyone is choosing it and why it&#39;s time for you to start using it too:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull; Voice searches would account for 50% of all web queries by 2020.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull; When looking for products, 50% of individuals utilise voice search on browsers and social media sites.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull; Voice search is used for routine online searches by 40% of adults worldwide.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>What Does Voice Search Look Like?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The Google search bar has a microphone icon right inside it, which you may access by typing. You can actually use keywords to speak for your question by clicking on this icon. But allow me to elaborate further with a specific illustration.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Following a search on the Google bar, prominent boxes would appear. In essence, Google refers to them as featured snippets.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When you type a question, Google uses the keywords to find the most relevant response from the articles and displays it in the snippets. There are three types of featured snippets. A one-word response ranks first, followed by a data set or list, then a paragraph in third place. Simply because it is exceedingly challenging to extract specific data from the data collection, Google typically displays paragraphs and lists instead. As a result, the user&#39;s search is constrained and he is rendered uninformed of the current online information.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The main benefit of featured snippets is that you can incorporate sentences from your website even if you are not rated top. If you are among the top 10, you can surpass other websites and take the top spot.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Many online professionals refer to this space as Position Zero.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>How Does Voice Search Work?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The operation of voice search is rather straightforward. It only reads the conclusions drawn from the information in the featured excerpts taken from the articles. As a result, anytime you ask your voice assistant a question, it responds with information from the featured snippets.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Businesses that interact with other businesses generally benefit from it. Your website&#39;s SEO ranking rises after it appears in the highlighted snippets because both desktop and mobile users now primarily utilise voice search.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>If you have a website, voice search has many advantages, including the following:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull; Brand recognition and awareness.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull; An increase in website traffic.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull; Outstanding click-through rate.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>How to Turn on Voice Search?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull; Using voice search is rather easy once it has been enabled. Open the Google App on your Android tablet or phone.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull; You could see &quot;More&quot; in the bottom right corner. Click it, then &quot;settings,&quot; and then choose &quot;Voice.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull; Enable voice matching so that the help can use your microphone.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>How to Turn Off Voice Search?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>To disable voice search, take the following actions:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull; On Google App, find the &quot;settings&quot; section.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull; Select the tab labeled General.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull; The Input and Language choice can be found under the &quot;Personal&quot; option. Just click it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull; Next, press the &quot;GOOGLE OK&quot; indicator.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To turn it off, slide the slider to the left.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull; You&#39;ve successfully disabled your Android phone or tablet.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Voice Search Optimization?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Basically, voice search optimization is search engine optimization for voice. It now has a significant impact on the SEO market and the SEO rankings of every website.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The goal of voice engine optimization is to improve your SEO ranks through the results of voice searches. To do this, you must optimise your services, content, location, website, and corporate information.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The rise of search by voice optimization began in 2017. These days, quick answers are used with it. Similar to SEO, but with greater opposition.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Unlike regular searches, there are only 3 outcomes. You are the last one standing if you are not one of them.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>How to Optimize for Voice Search?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>In order to maximize the potential of search marketing, voice search optimization is crucial. People are anxious to learn about unique ongoing offers, packages, products, news, or any other type of information as soon as possible, and fortunately, they have discovered how to do so. Obviously, using voice search.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>In order to optimize for voice search, you would wish to consider the following 5 significant changes:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<h4>&bull; Keyword Research for Voice Search</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>You must first understand that everyone speaks differently. One person may use a word that the other person does not. Particularly when asking verbally, people have diverse ways of doing so. Therefore, you should come up with a list of all the questions relating to your company or product for which customers would be looking for answers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You can use a variety of methods to find the best brand-related question. You can use the tools provided by Answer the Public to help you generate as many questions as you can using a specific keyword.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A nice Google feature that gives you additional question inspiration is People Also Ask.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>&bull; Site architecture and content creation</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>You must be accessible throughout the entire search by voice customer care process. Any question a person has regarding your business should be able to get an answer from you. The following are some areas you can concentrate on when creating and curating more effective content for voice search:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Awareness.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Evaluation.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Interest.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Customer Support.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Purchase</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Loyalty.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Try classifying the inquiries and questions you came up with after brainstorming. You may then map out your customers&#39; journey more effectively.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The best way to handle this issue is to include FAQs on each page of your website.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>&bull; Optimization of Structured Data</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Making your material as relevant to the query as you can is the key to optimizing. Make sure Google can readily access the pages of your website. Create a website map for this as soon as you can, then upload it to the Google Console. Bots are another area you might concentrate on. To ensure that Google bots can best grasp your material, use the schema markup technique. Describe your brand, product, location, contact details, and other pertinent information to Google bots.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You can also disseminate information about numerous publications, groups, seminars, events, menus, and reviews that are relevant to your business.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>&bull; You may want to create Alexa skills</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>You can create personalized Alexa or Google assistant skills to make your content more available to personal voice assistants. In order to make Google&#39;s operations even more seamless, you must adapt your software to voice assistants.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>By enhancing Google activities so that users of voice commands may converse with your content or application back and forth, you can improve the experience for voice command users.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Mobile-Friendly</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Instead of being desktop-friendly, search engine marketing places a greater emphasis on content and searches that are mobile-friendly. The majority of voice searches do, in fact, originate from mobile devices. As a result, when you optimize for mobile-friendly searches, you are also optimizing for voice searches.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Voice Search Devices</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>The top 6 gadgets are as follows:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>One is Google Home.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Echo/Alexa from Amazon.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. The iPhone&#39;s Siri.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4. The Google Assistant</p>\r\n\r\n<p>5. Android mobile phones and gadgets.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>6. Microsoft Cortana.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Here are some figures to illustrate its significance and applications in 2020:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull; 22%&nbsp;of individuals use voice search to make direct purchases.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull; 17%&nbsp;of customers who use voice search to place repeat orders.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull; 58%&nbsp;of people who use voice search to find local businesses use personal voice assistants to do it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull; The caller rate is 28%&nbsp;greater than the web rate when it comes to retention.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In their living rooms, 52%&nbsp;of individuals have voice-activated technology.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Voice Search Vs. Web Search</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Compared to standard Google web searches, voice search is radically different. Simply putting your query into the search field and browsing through the top search engine results is how you do a web search. But employing certain keywords to ask queries verbally is part of voice search. Modern search engines that have voice assistants can understand what users are seeking for and respond with featured snippets that have been taken from reliable sources.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Important Differences of Voice Search You Should Know</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>You should be aware of the following key distinctions between voice search and text search:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>&bull; Voice Search Users Make Different Queries Differently</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Voice search users speak in a variety of ways. They can use a variety of terms and sentence patterns when posing inquiries concerning their personal voice assistant. They inquire differently as a result, and they receive responses very differently.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>They frequently anticipate one-word or one-line responses, which is what voice-optimized search engines respond with. The voice assistants select the optimal response based on keywords, featured snippets, and Google crawling.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>&bull; Location Is More Important</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you utilize voice search, location is very important. Typically, queries are asked informally. For instance, if you asked your voice assistant, &quot;Tell me the greatest restaurant nearby,&quot; it would conduct a location-based search and return an appropriate result.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>&bull; Mobile Predominance</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The voice search platform that is most widely used is on a mobile device. Regarding text search, this is highly unlikely. Now that voice search is widely used on mobile phones, text search used to typically be a PC activity.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The website must be both mobile- and voice-friendly. If it isn&#39;t, it doesn&#39;t meet the requirements to be included in the excerpts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>&bull; Makes use of Natural Language</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>You don&#39;t speak computer language when you ask questions utilising a voice search. You converse in a native language, or more precisely, a human language.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As a result, voice searches take substantially longer than text searches.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>&bull; More question words are used.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>More inquiry words like &quot;why,&quot; &quot;what,&quot; &quot;when,&quot; &quot;how,&quot; and others are used in voice search.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>&bull; Voice Search Has One and Only One Response</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Unlike text search, which shows the top results, voice search typically returns just one result from the voice assistants.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n<h3>What Should You Do Today Given the Impact of Voice Search?</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Half of searches will be voice-based in 2020 due to the simplicity it offers and the significant improvement in user experience it brings.</li>\r\n	<li>Google and other search engines are increasingly concentrating on becoming more and more speech optimised due to its high usage.</li>\r\n	<li>Users place a lot of importance on search engine optimization, or SEO, because search engines rank websites based on the most accurate information available.</li>\r\n	<li>What we&#39;re attempting to argue is that SEO significantly affects voice search. The SEO rankings of websites are being significantly improved by voice-enabled search.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>This is how using voice search affects you:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;More questions are being posed in natural language now rather than text searches.</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;More people are conducting local searches.</li>\r\n	<li>More people are conducting action searches.</li>\r\n	<li>The following 5 steps are for you to take:</li>\r\n	<li>Work on optimising your content for voice searches.</li>\r\n	<li>Due of the length of voice searches, focus on long-tail keywords.</li>\r\n	<li>Aim for Google&#39;s highlighted snippets.</li>\r\n	<li>Enhance natural language.</li>\r\n	<li>To make it easier for search engines to comprehend you, use structured and meta data.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Voice Search Technology</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Technology for voice searches is not new. Ever since Audrey came out, it has been there. However, it is presently increasing. Voice assistants are in use, and 420 million of them have been sold as of this writing. This is expanding swiftly because voice search using artificial intelligence is more effective and efficient than text search.Google claims that its accuracy has improved to 95%.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In a nutshell, it is an antiquated technology that is becoming more well-liked due to the proliferation of voice assistants in cell phones.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Voice Search Tips</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>You could adhere to the following advice:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The majority of the voice search results are written at or below the ninth-grade reading level, so make sure to include filler and question words as well as to avoid fancy and jargon phrases.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Make your website faster.</li>\r\n	<li>Boost the authority of your domain.</li>\r\n	<li>The likelihood of receiving more voice search traffic increases with the amount of content you have on your website.</li>\r\n	<li>Enhance your content voice-based search Place location-based content there.</li>\r\n	<li>Positioning your videos in search engine results.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Voice Search&#39;s Future</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>It will be crucial for both big and small firms to incorporate a strong voice search strategy into their digital marketing efforts given the proliferation of speech technology.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Along with the advancement in SEO, it is providing businesses with a chance to improve customer service.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Additionally, it would be a fantastic tool for businesses to raise website traffic and brand recognition.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Vocal Search Patterns</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The following are 3 significant trends to be aware of:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. The majority of individuals use while driving.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. A large number of consumers keep their voice-activated technology in their living rooms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. The majority of consumers utilise for locations and directions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Common Questions Regarding Voice Search</h3>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>How can you install voice search?</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>If you own an Apple or Android smart device, you don&#39;t need to install voice search.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>However, you can turn on voice assistance by navigating to settings on the Google app. Just tap on Voice Match to access your voice assistant.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>What is the Free Voice Search List?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>The following list includes:&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Cortana by Microsoft</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Use Google Allo</p>\r\n\r\n<p>AIVC</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Interactive Prometheus</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>UI Apps</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;Bing</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;Magdalm</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Voice Search and Assistant&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Hound</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Vlingo</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;Bixby</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>How Can Voice Search Be Removed?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Simply uninstall the voice search app to remove voice search. You must disable voice search for voice assistants in Apple and Android phones, though.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Why does voice search not work properly?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>There are two possible reasons why your voice search isn&#39;t working. It&#39;s possible that the internet is both switched off and not working at the same time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Conclusion</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>As voice search has been shown to enhance brand exposure, income, and client base, investing in it has been a wise move for organizations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Voice search has become very popular, but it&#39;s still growing. However, if you voice-optimize your website right away, you&#39;ll be one step ahead of the competition.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Looking out for the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.idotcommers.com\" target=\"_blank\">best digital marketing agency in Navi Mumbai</a>, reach out to us in order to grow your business.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'Curious about voice search? Learn what it is, how it works, and how it\'s changing the way we search for information online. Start optimizing for voice today!', 'what-is-voice-search-and-how-does-it-work', 'What is voice search, voice search, voice search optimization, importance of voice search optimization, how does it work voice search,', 'Ayushi', '2023-03-03 22:07:24', '2023-03-03 22:16:47');
